title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Saute onion and celery in butter; stir in other ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed whole wheat shells
directions: Brown
onion
and
ground
beef, then add olives, wheat germ, cheese
and
bread.
Parboil shells for 8 minutes, then stuff with beef mixture and put in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour soup
over	all and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover with foil and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: crustless cranberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Butter 9-inch pie plate. Put cranberries in the plate, sprinkle with the granulated sugar, nuts and raisins. Beat eggs thoroughly, gradually beat in light brown sugar. Stir in flour and melted butter, blending well. Pour the mix over the cranberries. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: potato lovers' casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place frozen hash brown potatoes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1/2 cup of butter and pour over potatoes.
Set aside.
In a 2-quart bowl, mix sour cream, onion, cheese, soup, salt and black pepper.
Pour over potatoes and mix well.
Combine 2 cups of crushed cornflakes and the other 1/2 cup melted butter.
Spread over potato mixture.
Bake for 1 hour. Yield:
9 cups.
Makes 18 servings (1/2 cup each).

title: venison lasagna
directions: Brown venison and onion.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add all other ingredients except noodles, beaten eggs and cream cheese.
Lay noodles in greased baking dish.
Add a layer of ground venison and a layer of cream cheese.
Keep adding layers until everything is gone.
Top with shredded cheese and cook in oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup and 1/2 can of the onions. Pour into casserole.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Add remaining onions to top of the casserole the last 10 minutes of cooking.

title: block party beans
directions: In a large Dutch oven, brown beef; drain fat.
Add onion and celery; cook until tender.
Mix undiluted tomato soup, tomato paste and ketchup; simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Spoon into large baking dish or roaster.
Add drained green beans, lima beans and wax beans.
Add undrained chili beans, pork and beans, packed brown sugar and prepared mustard.
Stir well.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 24.

title: meghan's banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add all other ingredients; mix.
Mash in bananas and then add walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dad's vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix, freeze and enjoy.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken until tender, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Pick chicken off the bones and place in the bottom of a greased casserole dish.
Cover with the sliced mushrooms.
Mix together sour cream and mushroom soup and pour over chicken.
Top with mixture made of poppy seed, melted butter and cracker crumbs. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: oatmeal caramel bars
directions: Mix the cake mix, oatmeal, brown sugar, oil and egg.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Divide the dough in half.
Pat half into bottom of pan.
Pour the topping over dough, spreading it evenly.
Crumble remaining dough over topping.
Be sure all topping is covered.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.
Cut and cool.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine zucchini, onions and salt and let stand overnight. Next day, drain the mixture and rinse twice.
Add remaining ingredients; cook for 30 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.
Use a boiling hot water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 pints.

title: frozen cabbage slaw
directions: Grate the cabbage; mix with the salt and let stand in a bowl for 1 hour.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and boil for 1 minute.
Cool.
Drain the cabbage well to remove the liquid.
Add the boiling sauce to the cabbage and mix well.
Freeze the slaw in portions suitable for your family.
Thaw before serving.

title: easy french toast(kids recipe)
directions: Put slice of bread in toaster.
Spread with butter; cut into pieces.
Add syrup.

title: four layer chocolate pie
directions: Mix ingredients and press in oblong pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°, or until browned lightly.

title: orange pineapple punch
directions: Mix and chill pineapple juice and orangeade.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix ground beef and pizza or spaghetti sauce together.
Put in bottom of casserole dish.
Add Mozzarella cheese.
Mix Bisquick mix, milk and eggs together.
Pour this over top and bake approximately 1 hour or until golden brown, at 350°.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Moisten bread crumbs with pineapple juice.
Mix butter, sugar and eggs.
Combine with drained pineapple.
Fold mixture into bread crumbs.
Pour into 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes to 1 hour or until golden.
Great with ham.

title: ever so easy fruitcake
directions: Butter a 9-inch tube pan.
Line with waxed paper; butter again.
In large bowl, combine eggs, sweetened condensed milk, mincemeat, fruits and nuts; mix well.
Add corn flake crumbs and baking soda.
Blend well.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake in slow (300°) oven for 2 hours (or until cake tester somes out clean). Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Turn out of pan; remove paper.
Cool if desired.
Garnish with glazed cherries.
To store, wrap well in aluminum foil; refrigerate or freeze.

title: puffy popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat milk, flour, salt and butter together.
Add eggs and beat again.
Pour batter into a greased muffin pan until they are 3/4 full.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then lower the heat to 350° and bake for 20 more minutes.
Serve fresh from oven while warm.
Makes 9 or 10 popovers.

title: ye olde waterford apple cake
directions: Mix cinnamon with 6 tablespoons sugar.
Sprinkle over apples and nuts; set aside.
Beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Add dry ingredients and juice alternately.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Pour 1/2 batter in pan.
Sprinkle on 1/2 of apple/nut mixture.
Add remaining batter and sprinkle on remaining apple/nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: grandma's frozen cookies
directions: Form into bars.
Freeze.
Slice.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: salsa
directions: Chop the vegetables finely.
Stir in seasonings and allow to marinate at least 15 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9 baking dish. Place 6 slices bread in dish. Place 1 slice cheese on each piece of bread. Spread 1/2 cooked sausage on top. Repeat. Pour beaten eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard on top. Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: vegetable-beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender, about 15 minutes. Drain.
Lightly brown the onion in margarine.
Add the ground beef and cook slowly until brown. Blend in the flour and cooked noodles.
Add can of vegetables including liquid, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple over bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole or baking dish.
Spread apple pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix over apple pie filling.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix and pour melted oleo over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pocket book rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and 1 1/4 c. flour.
Beat well.
Add egg and shortening and remaining flour. Add enough additional flour to make dough workable.
Let rise till double in size.
Roll dough to 3/8-inch thickness. Cut with 2 1/2 inch biscuit cutter.
Fold in half and place close together in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brush with butter.
Let rise till double.
Bake 400° for about 18 minutes.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 doz. small rolls.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, Sugar Twin and spices until well blended. Stir in eggs until mixed thoroughly.
Add in milk a little at a time and blend well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for about 40 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: bits of sunshine
directions: Mix all ingredients together to make a thick batter.
Drop by teaspoon into 10x sugar; roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
I've also used chocolate cake mix.
It is real good also.
I think any flavor would work great.

title: fruit pie
directions: Pour pineapple into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not drain.
Pour pie filling over pineapple.
Do not stir.
Pour box of cake mix over fruit; do not stir.
Cover with chopped nuts.
Cut butter into pats and put over pecans.
Cook at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: blueberry-oatmeal bread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal. Combine eggs, milk and corn syrup; mix well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries. Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool loaf in pan for 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely on a wire rack. Yield:
1 loaf.

title: jam cake
directions: Spray tube pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Sift 2 1/2 cups flour, salt, cinnamon, cloves and soda together.
Set aside.
Whip together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add sifted ingredients. Take the other 1/2 cup of flour and mix with raisins and nuts. Add jam to cake mixture.
Add applesauce and mix well.
Fold in floured nuts and raisins.
Put in tube pan and bake 2 hours at 300°.
Good!

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zippy shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Chill.
Serve with chips, crackers or vegetable dippers.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all together and beat until smooth.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: georgia blackberry cobbler(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 9-inch pan, melt oleo; set aside. Combine flour and baking powder in small bowl.
Add 1/2 cup apple juice, 1/4 cup fructose and water.
Mix well.
Pour batter over melted butter.
In separate bowl, combine blackberries, 1/4 cup apple juice, 2 tablespoons fructose and almond extract.
Stir well and pour over batter.
Bake 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Fry chicken pieces and sausage in small amount of cooking oil until brown.
Add onions, celery and garlic and fry until brown. Add water and simmer until chicken is tender.
Add washed rice, parsley, onion tops, salt and pepper.
Stir lightly, lower fire, cover and cook until done (about 30 minutes).
Stir occasionally.

title: potato soup without milk
directions: To butter add 3 pints of boiling water, 1 1/2 pints of sliced potatoes, 3 diced

onions. Boil 1/2 hour and season with salt, pepper and parsley to suit the taste. When cooked take 2 tbsp. of flour with 1 tbsp of butter and fry in a pan stirring, until changed into a brown color, stir in potatoes and serve immediately.

title: pea salad
directions: Add all ingredients. Mix well.

title: delicious dessert quickie
directions: Blend sugar, cocoa and water in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions, but add vanilla to batter.
Spoon batter over the mixture in the pan.
Top with nuts.
Bake in 350° oven about 50 minutes.
Allow to cool slightly, then cut into serving size pieces and serve, sauce side up.

title: dutch oven cornbread
directions: Prepare a
good bed of live hardwood coals.
Heat Dutch oven and
melt
cup all-purpose shortening.
Break 2 eggs into clean mixing
bowl.
Add 2 cups buttermilk and beat until eggs are thoroughly	mixed with milk.
Reserve small amount of cornmeal. Add remaining
cups
cornmeal to mixture and mix until smooth. Stir
in
cracklins.
Remove
melted shortening from Dutch oven and
pour
into
mixture and stir thoroughly. Sprinkle small quantity
of
dry
cornmeal into greased Dutch oven, then pour batter
into
Dutch oven.
Place lid on Dutch oven and place
on bed
of coals large enough to cover entire bottom of cooker. Shovel
layer
of
live coals on Dutch oven lid and allow to cook 1 hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and cocoa together; set aside.
Cream sugar and oil in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and beat well.
Pour in greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: apple topped cream pie
directions: Using wire whisk, beat milk gradually into cream cheese in large bowl until smooth.
Add pudding mix and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes.
Spread evenly in crust.
Spread apple pie filling over pudding mix.
Refrigerate 4 hours. Sprinkle with almonds.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Wash and cut chicken into serving size pieces.
Dredge chicken in flour in shallow bowl.
Heat olive oil in large frying pan and place chicken cutlets in pan immediately.
Brown both sides of cutlets.
Add onions and cook until onions are soft.
Add chicken broth and Marsala wine.
Cook on high heat until mixture boils. Add mushrooms; cook 10 to 15 minutes until mixture (mushrooms and meat) is tender.
Serve immediately.

title: green tomato and pepper relish
directions: Wash, chop and mix together.
Add salt.
Let stand several hours or overnight; drain liquid and discard.
Tie spices in bag. Combine all ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Ladle hot mixture into hot jars and seal at once.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.

title: creamy noodles 'n' vegetables
directions: In a large saucepan, bring 4 cups hot water to boiling.
Add pasta and return to boiling.
Reduce heat and gently boil for 5 minutes, then add frozen vegetables.
Return to boiling, then reduce heat.
Gently boil about 4 minutes more or until pasta is tender and vegetables are nearly done.
Drain mixture, then return it to the saucepan.
Add cream cheese and milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until cream cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Make 4 servings.

title: pistachio chip cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and pudding mix. Blend in egg, then flour and baking soda.
Add chocolate chips. Drop by rounded teaspoon on lightly greased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Keep adding until good consistency.
Mix and let rest 15 minutes before rolling.

title: lo-cal eggnog
directions: Mix all together and store in refrigerator for at least 2 hours, then serve.

title: glaze for ham
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Spoon over ham the last 15 minutes of baking.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Drain fruit, reserving 6 tablespoons pineapple juice.
Combine sugar and flour.
Add reserved juice.
Add cheese, fruit and carrots. Mix well. Place in oblong baking dish.

title: cream cheese icing(to go with carrot cake)
directions: Soften cream cheese and margarine.
Add vanilla.
Mix in gradually the powdered sugar.
Spread on cake.
Top with walnuts.

title: collector's cocoa cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes for 8-inch, 30 to 35 minutes for 9-inch pans.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.

title: chocolate chip honey cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Cream shortening gradually; add honey and egg and beat until light and fluffy and add dry ingredients.
Mix in chocolate chips and vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for about 12 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pack into a greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°.
Drain liquid; let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: beef stew
directions: Layer,	in
a
roaster	or
crock-pot,	meat,
carrots, potatoes, onion, green beans with liquid, tapioca, then tomato sauce.
Cover
and bake at 250° for 6 hours (don't stir) or in a crock-pot for 4 to 5 hours.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook wild rice as directed. Brown hamburger and onion. Add to wild rice. Add all remaining ingredients. Heat well and serve.

title: garden glory vegetables
directions: Saute carrots and celery in margarine until crisp and tender. Reduce heat to low.
Add peas, walnuts and pepper.
Mix lightly. Add milk and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Place 1/2 in casserole dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, then crush Ritz crackers over top. Repeat.
Pour 1/8 cup milk over top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until brown.

title: dessert
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Break up a small angel food cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour first mixture on cake.
Pour pie filling over all.
Refrigerate.
You can use any pie filling (good with blueberry).

title: one-dish strawberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Reserve 1 cup whole strawberries for garnish; slice remaining berries.
In a blender container puree enough berries to equal 1 cup liquid (1 3/4 cups sliced berries equals 1 cup pureed berries).
Add biscuit baking mix, sugar, butter, eggs and evaporated milk to blender.
Stir slightly to mix ingredients together.
Blend on High for 1 minute.
Stir in remaining sliced berries, food color and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 9-inch deep dish pie plate.
Bake for about 55 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Garnish with whipped cream and whole berries.

title: hamburger and corn casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions until tender, but not too brown; drain. Add next 7 ingredients.
Stir in cooked noodles.
Mix crumbs with butter.
Sprinkle over top.
Place in a greased casserole dish. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: play dough
directions: Mix in saucepan.
Heat and stir quickly on stove.
In
few minutes, it's done.
It should not stick to your fingers.

title: new england toll house muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
In another bowl, whisk egg, milk, sour cream, melted butter and vanilla.
Make a "well" in the dry ingredients; add the wet ingredients, blending lightly.
Quickly fold in chocolate morsels.
Do not overmix the batter.
Spoon into greased (Pam sprayed) muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: cold mixed vegetable salad(salade nicoise)
directions: Sprinkle potatoes with vinegar; let stand 1 hour.
In another bowl, toss tomatoes and green beans with vinaigrette; let stand 1 hour.

title: onion dill bread
directions: Dissolve yeast with 1/2 cup warm water in a large mixing bowl. Add 1/2 cup warm water, margarine, eggs, salt and one cup flour. Beat on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in remaining flour until smooth.
Add onion and dill weed.
Scrape dough from sides of pan; cover and let rise until double in size (30 minutes or more).
Batter is ready if indentation remains. Stir down by beating 25 strokes.

title: quick ham salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: chafing dish mushroom dip
directions: Wash, dry and slice lengthwise mushrooms.
Melt butter, add remaining ingredients except sour cream and cook over medium heat 7 to 10 minutes.
Fold in sour cream.
Taste test for more salt. Serve hot on Melba rounds.
Yields 72 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine catsup and horseradish to make a cocktail sauce; enough to cover top of shrimp mixture.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Add vanilla and flour; mix well.
Add crushed chips.
Add nuts last (if using).

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix all ingredients together; cook over medium heat until it thickens, stirring constantly.
Serve over toast or homemade biscuits.
Really good for breakfast!

title: vegetable pizza(10 x 15-inch or 12 x 16-inch)
directions: Any vegetables can be used.

title: spinach chicken gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in egg, then in stuffing mix until well coated.
Saute chicken in a large skillet in butter until it begins to brown.
Turn once, lower heat and add wine. Simmer until wine has almost evaporated.
Remove chicken.
Stir broth, garlic, marjoram, basil and cream into pan juices to make a sauce.
Place half the spinach in bottom of buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Add chicken and top with remaining spinach.
Pour sauce over top, sprinkle with cheese and bake uncovered for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pecan breakfast cake
directions: Butter a tube cake or Bundt cake pan.
Put in chopped pecans. Evenly scatter frozen rolls in pan.
Sprinkle pudding mix over rolls.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over pudding.
Sprinkle cinnamon over sugar.
Drizzle melted margarine over all.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Leave setting out on counter overnight.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put the uncooked rice in an ungreased oven dish.
Place the chicken pieces, skin side down, on the rice.

title: li'l cheddar meat loaves
directions: In a bowl, beat the egg and milk.
Stir in cheese, oats, onion and salt.
Add beef and mix well.
Shape into eight loaves; place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish.
Combine ketchup, brown sugar and mustard; spoon over loaves.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until the meat is no longer pink.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: cheese and vegetable casserole
directions: Heat milk; pour over bread crumbs.
Add pimiento, parsley, onion, grated cheese and seasonings, then add eggs.
Put the vegetables in a greased or oiled 1 1/2-quart casserole and pour milk and cheese mixture over them.
Set in pan of warm water. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour or until firm.
Serves 6.

title: woody's barbecue baked beans
directions: Combine cooking oil and margarine in a large pot and heat. When oil is hot, add green peppers and onions.
Saute onion and pepper mixture until tender and onions are transparent.
Add garlic powder and black pepper.
Stir well to blend seasoning. Add tomato sauce and water.
Add kidney beans.
Simmer for 30 to 40 minutes until a red gray sauce forms.
Cook 10 minutes more and serve over rice.

title: easy swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper, and garlic powder.
Coat both sides of steak.
Brown meat and onion in hot shortening.
Add tomatoes and cover.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat in tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle steak seasoning over chicken.
Peel and cut potatoes in cubes; place over chicken. Dice onions; spread over potatoes.
Season well with salt, pepper and steak seasoning.
Place spoons of butter on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: buckeyes candy
directions: Mix all together, except chocolate chips and wax.
Melt chips and wax in double boiler.
Dip each ball shape into chocolate with a fork.
Lay out on wax paper until dry.
Store in airtight container.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and pineapple together in a buttered casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Melt butter and saute crackers with butter.
Place on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pizza burger
directions: Combine meat, salt, onion powder, oregano and 3 tablespoons of the tomato sauce.
Shape into 6 patties.
Broil hamburgers until nearly done.
Top with mushrooms, cheese and remaining tomato sauce.
Broil another 2 to 3 minutes until cheese melts.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine and beat 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 large or 6 small greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swiss broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange broccoli in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Layer eggs, 1/2 can onions, soup and cheese over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: chicken broccoli orientale
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium high heat, in hot oil, cook chicken, 1/2 at a time, until browned.
Add onion and peppers. Cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover, simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve over rice. Makes 4 servings.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Cook time:
20 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill for 1 hour.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger with your choice of optional ingredients.
Shape into balls and fry.

title: parmesan squash
directions: Slice squash and onions into thin slices.
Place in microwave-safe dish in layers beginning with squash, onion cheese and garlic powder.

title: cream cheese pastry
directions: Stir flour and salt; cut cream cheese and butter into pea size pieces.
Using a fork, stir in water and vinegar until all dough is moistened.
Using your fingers, gently knead dough just until ball forms.
Flatten into disc; proceed rolling into crust. Bake in pan at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: christmas salad
directions: Prepare first 2 jellos according to package directions in separate shallow pans.
Let set.
Cut into cubes.
Prepare lemon jello; let stand until slightly set.
Beat until fluffy and mix with whipped cream and pineapple.
Fold in cubed jello.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into balls or drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blend soup and Cheez Whiz and melt in saucepan over low heat. Saute onion, celery and 3/4 stick oleo.
Add Minute rice and broccoli.
Add soup and cheese mixture; mix all together.
Add mushrooms, if desired.
Put into greased casserole.
Top with 2 tablespoons melted oleo and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Combine all in a 9 x 13-inch casserole and bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pickled polish sausage
directions: Layer Polish sausage, onion and crushed red pepper in a gallon jug.
In a large saucepan, combine water, sugar, whole cloves, salt, celery seed and mustard seed.
When this mixture comes to a boil, lower heat and add 4 cups white vinegar.
Pour solution over fixings in gallon jug.
Keep in fridge.
Ready in 4 or 5 days.

title: science class fudge
directions: Mix butter, salt, sugar and evaporated milk in saucepan.
Cook on medium heat. After mixture comes to boil, continue cooking for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: chicken dish
directions: Roll chicken
breast
with
bacon
around each.
Put in dish. Mix
other ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil. Cook 4
hours at 225°.
Serve over cooked rice (I use a 9-inch square baking dish).

title: nana's instant hot chocolate
directions: Store in closed container.
When ready to use, add 1/3 cup to each cup of hot water.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in shortening until blended.
Beat egg; add water and vinegar and add to dry ingredients.
Stir with a fork until moistened.
Divide into five balls of dough, slightly flatten, wrap in wax paper and chill.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into serving pieces.
Peel and slice into thin slices.
Lay ribs in shallow 13 x 9-inch roast pan; lay onion slices on ribs.
Roast 30 minutes at 425°.
Discard onion slices. In 2-quart saucepan, combine catsup, Worcestershire sauce, water, salt and chili powder; bring to boil, stirring with spoon.
Pour 1/4 of barbecue sauce over ribs; roast 1 hour at 375°, basting ribs every 15 minutes with remaining sauce.
Serves 8.

title: onion rings
directions: Combine all ingredients except onions and blend together until smooth.
Separate onion slices into individual rings.
Dip each ring into batter and then again into plain flour one at a time. Fry in hot oil for 1 1/2 minutes or until light brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve as a side dish.

title: no sugar brownies
directions: Spray 8-inch square pan with non-stick cooking spray.
In bowl, stir fructose, Sweet-One, margarine, eggs, Butter Buds and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients just until blended.
Spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mom's brownies
directions: Melt over low heat the butter and chocolate.
Stir lightly in bowl the eggs.
Add sugar; stir.
Add flour; stir.
Add salt.
Add chocolate mixture.
Add nuts if desired.
Stir hard until mixture appears dull.
Then add vanilla.
Pour into a buttered pan and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls into cookie sheet to form crust.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing mix and spread on cooled crust.
Top with vegetables and sprinkle with cheese.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Cut in small squares.

title: miniature lasagna tarts
directions: Brown in skillet the pork sausage, ground beef and onion. Drain well. Mix in garlic powder, parsley flakes, leaf oregano, salt and pepper, basil, Parmesan cheese, tomato paste and sugar.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add last 5 ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a greased and slightly floured pan about 35 minutes or until done.
Cool before removing from pans.

title: crisp cheddar cheese potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, butter, salt and onion.
Mix well.
In a 9x13 baking dish alternate layer of potatoes and cheese ending with cheese.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 425 degrees for 30 minutes, covering potatoes the first 15 minutes of baking time.

title: christmas fruit bars
directions: Sprinkle pecans over greased and floured 10 x 5 x 1-inch pan. Cream oleo and add sugar.
Continue creaming.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Continue beating.
Then add flour and vanilla; mix well. Press batter down over nuts (wetting your hands helps).
Spread dates, then cherries and pineapple over batter.
Wet hands and press down.
Bake at 275° to 300° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Yields about 60 bars.

title: cheesecake
directions: Let cream cheese, sour cream and oleo stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Then mix them all together.
Add other ingredients and blend in mixture, except eggs.
Beat each egg individually into batter; pour into 10-inch greased spring pan.
Place spring pan into a large roasting pan that has been half-filled with hot water. Bake at 375° in preheated oven 1 hour.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Graham cracker crust is optional.

title: peach pie
directions: Let peaches and sugar set until sugar melts.
Bake pie shell. Pour peaches in shell.
Mix Jell-O, sugar and flour.
Add water; mix well.
Cook over low heat, stirring until it comes to a boil. Boil about 5 minutes.
This will be thick.
Pour over peaches, spreading evenly.
Keep in refrigerator until pie is cold.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pasta salad
directions: Toss all the ingredients in a big bowl, then add your favorite vegetables (i.e. tomatoes, mushrooms, onions, red, green or yellow peppers).
You may also add sliced grilled chicken breast, chopped black olives and Feta cheese.
Serve with your choice of dressing.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix sour cream, cheese, soup, salts, and 1/2 of melted butter. Stir well, add defrosted potatoes. Put in 9 X 13 oven proof pan. Sprinkle crushed corn flakes over top with other half melted butter. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350 degrees.

title: guava chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces; pat dry.
Place in
a large baking dish. Squeeze juice of 1 lemon over the
chicken.
Stir guava jelly with a fork until loose and liquidy.
Pour	jelly
over chicken. Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at
325°.	Baste
3 to
4	times with jelly and juices from	pan.
Remove
chicken from oven.
Pour the juices into a
saucepan;
thoroughly stir in cornstarch with a whisk.
Add food
coloring;
sauce should be a rosy color.	Cook sauce over low heat until thickened and clear.
Pour
sauce over the chicken;
sprinkle
with
sesame seed.	Return chicken and sauce to oven at once
for	at least 15 minutes, or until ready to serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: old-fashioned nut bread
directions: Mix together and bake for 15 minutes at 375°, then 45 minutes at 325°.
Place batter into greased loaf pan.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage or bacon, cool. Beat eggs and add milk, salt and mustard. Beat again. Add cheese and sausage or bacon. Stir and put in 1 quart greased casserole. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until brown around edges. Serves 6.

title: weight watchers cheesecake
directions: Blend at high speed until frothy.
Pour in 8-inch pie pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Chill 2 hours.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a shallow baking dish.
Cut cabbage into 12 wedges.
Pour water into large skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of salt and cabbage.
Cook, covered, over medium heat for 10 minutes; drain well.
Put into baking dish. Sprinkle with mixture of flour, sugar, 1/2 teaspoon of salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Pour hot milk over.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix yeast, warm water and salt and pepper and let stand 10 minutes.
Add oil and flour.
Knead and let rise 2 hours.
Punch down and let rise half hour more.
Spread on ungreased cookie sheet.
Top with favorite topping.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Grease 13 x 9 dish.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix all vegetables together and sprinkle with the garlic salt, oregano, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour the oil and vinegar over the vegetables.
A good summer dish!

title: pesto cheese spread
directions: Blend parsley, basil, green onion, garlic and Parmesan cheese in a food processor or blender until well-blended.
Add cream cheese and margarine; blend thoroughly.
Spoon into serving bowl and chill.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat together and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry float
directions: Place 1/2 cup ice cream or yogurt, strawberries and milk into blender.
Mix on low and then on high until smooth.
Pour into tall glass.
Top with a 2nd scoop of ice cream or yogurt.
Top with whipped cream and sprinkles.

title: tangy meat loaf
directions: In large bowl combine, catsup, brown sugar, and mustard. Reserve 4 Tbsp. mixture for topping.
To remaining mixture add Worcestershire sauce, seasoned salt, onion powder, garlic powder, black pepper, and egg.
Blend well.
Stir in green peppers and Wheat Chex.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Break up Wheat Chex.
Add ground beef.
Mix well.
Shape into loaf in shallow baking pan. Bake in 350° oven for 65 minutes.
Spread top with reserved catsup mixture.
Bake additional 15 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: marshmallow creme fudge
directions: Place sugar, evaporated milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook to soft-ball stage or 236° on thermometer, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and chocolate chips.
Stir until ingredients are melted.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Yield: 3 pounds.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables.
Mix sugar, salt, vinegar and oil.
Pour over vegetables.
Marinate several hours.
Drain before serving.

title: cheddar pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops; drain off fat.
Salt and pepper chops; pour cheese soup over chops.
Also pour half soup can of milk and onion.
Place potatoes around pork chops; cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Stir 2 to 3 times.

title: charleston chews
directions: Heat brown sugar and butter in pan or in microwave just until melted.
Stir in eggs one at a time.
Stir in 1 cup of flour. Stir, then add other cup.
Stir.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir. Grease a square pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cut when cool.
Very good.

title: oreo pudding
directions: In 2 bowls, mix separate.
In first bowl, mix instant pudding with 3 cups milk and set aside.
Then beat on mixer, butter, cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Then add Cool Whip and pudding mixture.
In a large dish, add broken Oreo cookies (1/2 of them), then 1/2 mixture, then the rest of the Oreos and then the rest of the mixture.
Save enough single Oreos to garnish the top. Refrigerate 3 hours before serving.

title: ritz cracker torte
directions: Beat egg whites until they stand in soft peaks.
Gradually add sugar.
Mix baking powder with crackers.
Gently fold this, vanilla and nuts into egg whites.
Pile into greased pie pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool; cover with Cool Whip at least two hours before serving.
Top with any fresh or drained frozen fruit.

title: baked mushrooms, noodles and ham mornay
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter.
Add flour; stir with wire whisk.
When blended, add milk, stirring rapidly. Add salt, pepper, nutmeg and the cheese, stirring until melted. Add cream; bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Melt remaining butter.
Add onions, stirring.
Add mushrooms; cook until wilted. Add ham; heat through.

title: polynesian pork
directions: Put meat on rack in shallow roasting pan and sprinkle with salt, pepper and rosemary.
Roast pork in moderate oven at 350° for about 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until tender when tested with a fork.
Baste frequently with mixture of soy sauce, catsup, honey and garlic.
Transfer pork to heated platter; garnish with watercress.
This serves a crowd and is so easy to fix!

title: chicken perini
directions: Grease bottom of casserole dish.
Layer vegetables and then chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and curry powder together and spread over top of chicken.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese and bread crumbs over top.
Apply pats of butter if desired.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat the margarine, sugars and peanut butter until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in chocolate.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350° or until light brown. Let cool 2 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: roman apple cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add shortening and mix as if for biscuits.
Add milk and 2 eggs, slightly beaten.
Add vanilla. Fold in 3 to 4 medium apples (chopped fine).

title: lovely lemon cake
directions: In large bowl, add the lemon cake mix, eggs, lemon Jell-O, oil and water, mixing thoroughly. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes. Remove from oven. Pierce with fork all over top of cake. Combine powdered sugar and lemon juice. Pour all over top of cake while hot. The longer this cake stands, the better it tastes.

title: cereal mix(low-fat)
directions: Combine fruit bits, nuts and oats in small bowl.
Layer corn flakes, bran flakes and nut mixture in sealable container, such as a Rubbermaid Cereal Keeper.
Serve with skim milk.
Makes 10 servings.

title: applause winning baked lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Spoon off excess fat.
Add next 6 ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Meanwhile, combine cottage cheese with eggs, seasonings and Parmesan cheese. Layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish starting with lasagna, tomato sauce, Mozzarella cheese and cottage cheese mix.

title: peach leather
directions: Stew peaches in the sugar, cooking until they are a smooth paste. Spread on a greased cookie sheet. Place in sun and allow to dry. When dry, roll up like leather and wrap in wax paper to store. This will keep for months.

title: bottled hell
directions: Mix hot peppers and 1/2 cup vinegar.
Add remaining vinegar and catsup.
Simmer 15 minutes and pour into jars.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into 2-inch pieces.
Heat oil with salt and pepper in skillet.
Add meat and brown.
Remove meat and set aside.
Add green peppers, onions, garlic and celery.
Quick-fry.
Add bouillon, cover and cook vegetables 10 minutes.
Combine cornstarch, water and soy sauce.
Slowly add and stir into vegetable mixture.
Add meat and cook 5 minutes.
Serve with hot cooked rice or noodles.

title: german apple cake
directions: Frost while cake is hot.

title: sausage-lasagne
directions: Break sausage in small pieces and brown slowly in a large iron pan.
Remove sausage and drain, except for 4 tablespoons drippings. Add onions and garlic; simmer until tender.
Return sausage; blend in tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, salt and spaghetti sauce mix. Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: kona banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to banana mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Bake at 350° in a bread pan for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook and drain meat.
Combine onion, garlic, tomato sauce, onion salt and oregano and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain, spread light layer of meat sauce in 9 x 13 dish and then layer noodles and sauce and cheeses.
Save a little cottage cheese to spread on top before baking
in a 350 degree oven
minutes.
Let cool
before serving.

title: meat balls on picks
directions: Beat egg and water.
Combine with remaining ingredients. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake in shallow pan at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve on cocktail picks.

title: apricot oat squares
directions: Butter a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place first 4 ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Add butter and work in until the oat mixture is crumbly using fingers.
Set 2 cups of it aside.
Press remaining mixture onto bottom of buttered pan. Spread preserves over top and crumble the rest of the oat mixture on top.
Pat gently but firmly.
Bake squares at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely and then cut into small squares.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Heat 2 cups water to boiling.
Add tea bags, cinnamon and cloves.
Steep for 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags and spices.
Add 10 cups water, orange juice, lemon juice and sugar.
Heat all ingredients together.

title: tuna and potato chip hot dish
directions: Mix well together in small casserole dish.
Place whole chips on top.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter or oleo, shortening or oil and sugar until smooth.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Add milk and flour; beat good.
Add extract and salt.
Put in cold oven.
Turn oven to 325° and bake for 20 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 300° and cook for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: sommersalad
directions: Wash and cut veggies into small strips, julienne.
Mix together mint leaf, parsley, pepper, salt, lemon J. and oil.
Mix and cut veggies and add homemade salad dressing.
Let stand for an hour so veggies can absorb the dressing.

title: feather cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Break eggs into 1 cup measuring cup and finish filling that cup with whole milk. Add the above
to
creamed	mixture.
Add flour and flavoring. Blend well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Bake in 375° oven until center
springs
back
from
touch.
Cool	to lukewarm while preparing
frosting.
(Or
you may add your own favorite chocolate or lemon frosting.)

title: buckeyes
directions: Make sure margarine is at room temperature.
Blend margarine and peanut butter until smooth.
Start adding powdered sugar gradually.
It will be moist at first, then become harder to mix. At end, you may have to use your hands to mix.
Roll into balls with your hands.
Refrigerate overnight or put in freezer for awhile.
Prepare chocolate by melting chocolate chips and paraffin. Dip balls in chocolate after firm.
If toothpick comes out while dipping, they are not hard enough.
Place on wax paper to harden. Makes 15 dozen.

title: apple salad with cheese
directions: In a medium size bowl, whisk together vinegar, lemon juice, honey, salt and pepper. Gradually drizzle in olive oil, continuing to whisk until thick and well blended.

title: crock-pot corn bread dressing
directions: Crumble breads together. Add all other ingredients. Pour in crock-pot and dot with margarine. Cook on high for at least 2 hours, on low for at least 3 hours.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into greased or sprayed muffin pan.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and blend well.
Mix flour, soda and salt; add to mixture.
Stir in mashed bananas, walnuts and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely.
Wrap and let stand for 24 hours.

title: vince's rabbit
directions: Parboil rabbits 45 minutes in large kettle with enough water to cover rabbits.
To water add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over bottom of large roaster. Place rabbit pieces in roaster.
Sprinkle parsley flakes and seasoning envelope over rabbits.
Mix the soups and half and half together and pour over rabbits.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, covered.
Baste and turn pieces every 45 minutes.
Brown off, if necessary, uncovered, toward last of cooking time.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together the flour and sugar.
In a large pan, combine cocoa, oleo, water and oil; bring to a boil and pour over sugar and flour.
Stir well and add 1/2 cup buttermilk
and eggs, slightly beaten.
Add cinnamon, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in greased pan (17 x 11 x 1-inch) and bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: quiche supreme
directions: Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: beef burgundy(for crock-pot)
directions: Put all ingredients except mushrooms and flour into slow cooker and mix.
Cover pot; turn on low and cook 8 to 10 hours or until beef is tender.
Add mushrooms during last hour of cooking. To thicken sauce, remove 2 cups sauce from pot; stir until sauce is smooth and slightly thickened.
Slice when slightly cooled.

title: banana strawberry smoothie
directions: Peel bananas and cut off tops of strawberries.
Put into blender with ice, ice cream, vanilla and milk.
Whirl away!

title: hamburger stretch
directions: In mixing bowl, slightly beat egg.
Add bread pieces, onion, Worcestershire sauce and salt and pepper; mix together.
Add enough milk to moisten.
Crumble ground chuck into bowl and mix well.
Form into patties and fry in small amount of oil over medium heat.

title: aunt sarah buckner's chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until done, remove from broth, remove skin and debone.
If there's not enough broth, add 1 can chicken broth or cream of chicken soup.

title: chocolate crunch bars
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients.
Add the unsweetened chocolate and nuts and beat 1/2 minute more.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from oven and, while bars are still warm, add marshmallow cream.
Put in oven and bake another 3 minutes.
Take out; spread the marshmallow cream and cool.
When cool, melt chocolate chips with peanut butter.
To this, add Rice Krispies. Spread over cooled bars and refrigerate.
Freezes well.

title: stewed tomatoes with corn
directions: Saute celery, onions and peppers until tender, then stir in tomatoes and liquid.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Then add whole kernel corn.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes more.

title: blend of the bayou casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In nonstick skillet, melt butter and saute onion, bell pepper and celery.
Add cream cheese and melt. Stir in soup, mushrooms and seasonings.
Take off fire and add crabmeat and cooked shrimp.
Fold in cooked rice.
Pour into a 9 x 13 dish which has been sprayed with Pam.
Top with grated cheese and bake for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pudding delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine flour, ground nuts and margarine. Mix well and press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: cheese and broccoli soup
directions: Melt oleo and saute onion for 5 minutes or until onions are tender.
Mix in flour until blended.
Add water, bouillon, garlic powder, pepper and broccoli and cook for 10 minutes.
Add milk, half and half and cheese.
Cook on low until cheese melts.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Roll crackers with rolling pin, mix eggs until foamy, heat oil. Dip chop in flour, then in eggs, then in crackers.
Fry until golden brown.
Very good and tender.

title: broccoli-n-cheese
directions: Separately, cook rice and broccoli as directed on boxes.
Chop onion and celery.
Drain water from broccoli, yielding 1 cup.
In large pot (broccoli should be cooked in), add all ingredients. Use the 1 cup water that was yielded from the cooked broccoli. Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour, uncovered, at 350°.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.

title: old-fashioned rhubarb cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg.
Beat well.
Combine buttermilk and vanilla; set aside.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Stir in rhubarb. Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon; sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: dodie cookie
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients on medium heat until it boils.
Boil until thickened.
Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients (except whole graham crackers).
Line 9 x 13 pan with whole graham crackers, pour filling mixture over them.
Put on a top layer of graham crackers and push down gently.
Ice with powdered sugar icing and cover.
Let set in refrigerator for at least 2 hours (so it softens a little) then cut into bar type servings.

title: ham chowder soup
directions: Boil potatoes in water until tender.
Add ham and onions. Cook 10 minutes more.
Add soups, corn and milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir, heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Serve with corn muffins.

title: canine crunchies
directions: Mix together the flours, corn meal, salt, powdered milk, yeast and chicken or beef stock.
Roll out dough.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Place on nonstick cookie sheets and brush with mixture of beaten egg and milk.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour tofu and veggies
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in 2 tablespoons water.
Add 1/4 cup pineapple juice, 1/4 cup water, vinegar, honey, soy sauce, ginger and touch of pepper; set aside.
Spray wok or large skillet with Pam.
Add onion; stir over high heat until strong smell starts to go away.
Add carrot; stir a little more.
Add tofu; stir until lightly browned.
Add green pepper; stir a minute more.
Reduce heat to medium; cook, covered, until carrot is partly softened. Add pineapple chunks and liquid.
Uncover; cook for about 10 minutes, until thickened and flavors are blended.
Nice sprinkled with sunflower seeds or chopped peanuts.
Serve over rice or chow mein noodles.
Serves 4.

title: round rye bread dip
directions: Remove bread from inside loaf and make a shell for dip.
Tear extra bread into bite size pieces and store in plastic bag.
Mix all other ingredients together and place in bread shell to serve.

title: olive barbecued chicken
directions: Brown chicken pieces in hot shortening. Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan and simmer over low heat until thoroughly blended. Spoon sauce over browned chicken. Cover and simmer until chicken is tender. Baste with sauce occasionally. This can be frozen and reheated. This can also be placed in a casserole and baked at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Add cheese and Bisquick.
Make into balls.
Cook in oven at 350° for about 10 minutes or until you think done.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Cook in salted water until just tender.
Drain well.
Add peppers and onions to carrots.
Mix together soup, salad oil, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over carrots while warm.
Put in refrigerator and marinate at least 2 or 3 days.
Drain marinade and serve cold.

title: baked salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat. Add onions and cook until tender.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Remove skin and bones from salmon and flake salmon with a fork.
Add lemon juice, 1/2 cup corn flakes and the white sauce, stirring well. Refrigerate mixture until chilled.
Shape into croquettes.
Roll in remaining corn flakes.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: a little bit of heaven
directions: Mix mashed strawberries, lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk together.
Then add Cool Whip.
Add torn cake to mixture and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with strawberries on top.

title: caramel oatmeal chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 12 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine oats, flour, brown sugar, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in margarine, mixing well until blended.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press remaining onto bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: holiday scottish shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Grease an 8 inch square baking pan and set aside.
In a small bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in flour until well mixed.
Pat dough evenly into bottom of pan.
With tines of fork, prick dough all over to prevent bubbles from forming during baking.
Bake 1 hour or until pale golden. Do not allow to brown. Remove from oven.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Add 3/4 cup cold water to 1 1/2 envelopes unflavored gelatin to soften.
Add 2/3 cup boiling water.
Cool mixture.
Blend or chop cranberries in blender.
Add celery, sugar and walnuts.
In large bowl, mix gelatin and cranberry mixture.
Fold in miniature marshmallows and the Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet.
If you use chopped onion, cook it until transparent; minced onion you just add to the mixture.
Add all ingredients; let simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve over hamburger buns.

title: kathie's seasoning for rib-eye roast
directions: Combine and rub on outside of rib-eye roast before cooking. Cook as desired.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Using a pastry cutter, combine cake mix and margarine.
Set aside one cup of mixture.
Spread pie filling in 9x12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining cup of mixture over filling.
Sprinkle nuts over mixture.
Bake at 325 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: crisp squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk and flour.
Beat well and spread dough evenly in jelly roll pan (15 x 10-inch).
Beat egg white slightly.
Brush top of dough with egg.
Smooth with fingertips.
Sprinkle with nuts over dough and press in.
Do not grease pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
While hot, cut squares to keep from crumbling.

title: festive mullet
directions: Dip fillets in dressing.
Coat with cracker crumbs.
Place on well greased baking sheet.
Drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 500° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: slovak halubki
directions: Fully cook rice and let stand and cool down.
Combine ground meat, rice, eggs and seasoning.
Mix well.
Core cabbage and parboil.
Peel off each leaf with 2 forks.
Take a handful of the combined mixture.
Place the mixture to the back of the cabbage leaf; roll until the mixture is covered by the leaf, then fold the sides in and finish the roll.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Make into ball and chill.
Roll in 1 cup chopped pecans.
Delicious!

title: bret's puffy french toast(a saturday morning favorite!)
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend milk and egg.
Add to the dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Dip bread into batter and fry in fat heated to 375° for 4 or 5 minutes.
Serve with butter and warm syrup.
Batter may be prepared ahead of time. Serves 4.

title: hamburger pizza spread
directions: Mix together.
Spread the meat mixture on bun or bread. Microwave 1/2
to
minute
or
under oven broiler for a few minutes.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Shape into 4 patties. Coat with bread crumbs.
Heat corn oil on medium heat.
Add patties and fry about 5 minutes, browning both sides.
Serve on rolls with your favorite cole slaw.
Serves 4.

title: sausage casserole 1
directions: Mix all ingredients in an 11 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.

title: white barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together syrup, wine, oil, mustard, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper.
Stir in onions.
Pour over chicken or ribs for grilling.
The longer the meat is marinated the better the flavor. Makes 1 1/2 cups of sauce.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Boil lima beans until tender.
While they are boiling, fry bacon until crisp and break into bits.
Grate the cheese and have it ready.
When beans are tender, drain off water and add onion to hot beans along with the bits of bacon and 1 or 2 tablespoons of bacon drippings.
Add cheese and soup and mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish; sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken marsala with artichoke hearts
directions: Mix cheese, flour and pepper.
Coat chicken and brown in butter.
Set chicken aside.
In same pan, saute mushrooms.
Add butter if needed.
Blend in remaining flour mixture.
Mix broth and wine; mix in pan with mushrooms until thickened, adding broth if too thick.
Cook slowly until sauce is desired consistency. Put chicken in 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Spread artichoke hearts on top, then pour mushrooms with gravy on top.
Add some juice from artichoke jars.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: peanut rounders
directions: Combine all ingredients, except peanuts and powdered sugar. Bring to a full boil, add peanuts and cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add 1 cup powdered sugar.
Pour into greased muffin tins or drop onto wax paper.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables, onion and celery in oleo; drain.
Mix cheese with mayonnaise; add to vegetables.
Put into baking dish.
Top with crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 300° until lightly browned.

title: microwave yogurt
directions: Fill a Coleman ice chest 3 to 4-inches deep with water heated to 110°.
Close and set aside.
In a 2-quart Pyrex mixing bowl, heat milk to 180° using microwave oven temperature probe.
Ladle milk into glass jars and let cool to 110°.
Add yogurt to starter, a heaping teaspoonful per pint of milk and vanilla to taste.
Place 110° jars of milk into cooler of 110° water.
Leave closed for 8 to 9 hours.
For flavoring, add your homemade jams or fresh fruit.

title: kraut and sausage
directions: Cook sausage on low heat for about 5 minutes.
Remove from pan. Add kraut to drippings from sausage.
Put sausage in kraut and cook about 10 more minutes.
Cut sausage in small pieces before cooking.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain but save fruit cocktail and pineapple juice.
Blend juice with instant pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip and fruit.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix and break hearts with a fork.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Carve out a large hole in a mound of pumpernickel or dark rye bread.
Fill with the warm mixture.
Cut up the carved out section of bread and serve with the dip.

title: tater topped casserole
directions: Brown onions, celery, ground beef and pepper in pan.
Add salt and pepper; pour into baking dish and pour soup over top. Add Tater Tots and butter to top.
Bake 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and 1/2 of the butter.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine remaining butter and chips.
Place on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple crunch(serves 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix apples with brown sugar in greased baking dish; set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon together in bowl.
Add egg; spread over apples.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake for 45 minutes, or until lightly browned. Serve warm.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place rolls flat on cookie pan and bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Let cool.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together.
Put in loaf pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: turkey and stuffing quiche
directions: If using stuffing mix, prepare as directed.
Press stuffing into greased 9-inch pie plate or quiche pan, forming crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
In small bowl, combine turkey and Swiss cheese, set aside.
In separate bowl, beat eggs, milk and pepper.
Sprinkle turkey and cheese mixture over hot crust.
Pour egg mixture over turkey.
Lower oven temperature to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Grease and flour cookie sheet.
Mix crust ingredients (corn meal, flour, baking powder, milk and oil).
Spread on pan.
(I use the side of a glass to roll it.)
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Brown chicken pieces in a skillet; set aside.
Mix next 5 ingredients in a medium saucepan and heat to boiling point.
Put browned chicken pieces in crock-pot and pour heated mixture over chicken.
Cook all day on LOW.
Serve over hot cooked rice. Serves 4 to 6.

title: brandy balls
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine chocolate pieces and milk.
Cook and stir until chocolate melts. Remove from heat. Add wafers, 1/2 cup pecans, powdered sugar and brandy.
Stir well. Cover. Chill for 1 hour. Form mixture into 3/4-inch balls and roll in remaining pecans. Store in refrigerator for as long as one month. Makes about 60 balls.

title: syrup cake
directions: Put all the dry ingredients in a large bowl and mix.
Add eggs, oil and syrup.
Beat well, then add 1 cup boiling water.
Beat until the batter is very thin and pour into a large, long greased and floured cake pan.
Bake in 350° oven until brown and sort of shiny.
Test for doneness.
This cake will stay quite moist.

title: corn stuffing nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt 1/2 stick butter
in medium saucepan;
saute
onion
and
celery until soft.
Remove
from heat;
add
corn
and
cup
water.
Stir.
Bring to boil. Remove from heat.
Place stuffing mix in large bowl; pour corn mixture
over.
Mix lightly.
Add egg yolks.
Shape into 10 to 12 balls.
Spray
shallow
baking dish with vegetable cooking spray. Place
balls in dish.
Pour 1 stick melted butter over balls. Bake until brown, about 20 minutes.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated or frozen.
If made ahead, do not add melted butter until
ready
to bake.
If frozen, thaw before baking. Serves 6.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl except Blue cheese.
Mix with mixer.
Stir in Blue cheese with fork.
Refrigerate.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cheese, add pinapple.
Mix all together and place in buttered casserole dish.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cream together eggs, oleo and sugar.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: irish bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add caraway seed and raisins.
Add milk; mix.
Add eggs; mix.
Add shortening; mix.
Place in greased, floured pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour for large loaf pan (40 to 45 minutes for 2 small pans).

title: pepper-cheese stuffed burgers
directions: Divide ground beef into 8 equal portions. Shape each into 4-inch patties.
Place equal amounts of cheese in the center of 4 patties.
Top with remaining patties and press edges together to seal.

title: peanut butter dessert
directions: Make graham cracker crust according to recipe on box in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix next 4 ingredients with mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put over graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle with graham crumbs on top.
Freeze in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter spice cupcakes
directions: Cream
together
peanut
butter
and butter.
Add sugar gradually,	creaming until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time,
beating
after
each.
Stir	together
flour, baking powder,
salt, cloves and cinnamon.
Combine milk and vanilla. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning
and ending with dry ingredients.
Spoon batter into greased
and
floured cupcake pans.
(Or line pans with baking cups.)
Bake
at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Cool and frost as desired.
Makes 2 dozen medium cupcakes.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Mix together and chill.
Add Chinese noodles just before serving.

title: farmer's casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover hamburger with sliced potatoes, about 2 or 3 slices thick.
Spread a layer of sliced onions, then add another layer of sliced potatoes, not quite as thick as first layer.
Add a layer of partially cooked green beans.
Mix Cheddar cheese and cream of celery soup, undiluted, in saucepan.
Mix and heat slightly.
Spread on top of green beans.
Season layers of meat and vegetables as desired.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until potatoes are fork-tender.

title: apple-cranberry pie
directions: Combine sugars, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Toss in large bowl with apples and cranberries.
Divide mixture between the two pie shells.
Pat on topping and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until bubbly and golden brown on top.
This is a juicy pie, so put something on rack under pie to catch drippings.

title: leta's impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and milk.
Add flour, vanilla, butter and coconut.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into 2 pie pans sprayed with Pam.
Bake 30 minutes or until set.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter and powdered sugar with hands.
Roll into little balls.
Melt paraffin wax and chocolate chips in top of double boiler.
Dip peanut butter balls, one at a time and put on waxed paper.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Combine oil and sugar; add egg and beat.
Stir in syrup. Combine dry ingredients and mix together.
Roll dough in 1-inch balls.
Using 1/3 cup of granulated sugar, roll balls in sugar and place 2-inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Makes about 48 cookies.

title: romaine-broccoli salad
directions: Break up Ramen noodles while still in the package.
Discard flavor packet.
Saute walnuts and noodles in butter until brown. Cool on paper towels.
Make dressing from oil, sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Toss together broccoli, lettuce, green onions, and walnut-noodle combination.
Pour dressing over and serve.
Serves about 15 to 18.

title: mcgobin hash browns
directions: Peel potatoes and grate them into a large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, except oil, mixing well.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in heavy saucepan. Whisk together eggs and milk. Whisk into dry ingredients. Cook over medium heat, whisking constantly, 6 to 8 minutes until smooth and thick. Remove from heat. Add vanilla. Cool. Layer half of wafers in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Slice 2 bananas and layer over wafers. Repeat layers. Pour pudding over bananas. Top with whipped topping. Cover. Chill at least 3 hours.

title: girdle buster dessert
directions: (Layer 1)
Mix flour, butter and pecans together. Bake 15 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: san francisco cheesecake
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: luscious peach pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and extract.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill about 3 hours.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Mix and bake 4 hours at 250°.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix sour cream with mayonnaise. Add package of Ranch dressing; mix well. Use minced onion to taste or if prefer, 3 drops of onion extract. Mix well and refrigerate.

title: scottish scones
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening and butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs, then mix in oats and currants.
Add milk, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface and knead gently 5 times.
Roll to form a 6 or 7-inch circle. Brush dough with 1 tablespoon melted butter and sprinkle with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Cut into 6 pie shaped wedges. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.
Serve warm with clotted cream or marmalade.

title: peppermint patties
directions: In bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients.
Add milk and mix well.
Roll into 1 - inch balls and place on wax paper lined cookie sheet. Chill for 20 minutes.
Flatten with glass to 1/4 inch thickness.
Chill for 30 minutes.
In double boiler or microwave-safe bowl, melt chocolate chips and shortening.
Dip patties into chocolate and place on wax paper to harden.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: summer squash relish
directions: Mix squash, onions and salt well and let set overnight.
Drain in morning; rinse with water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; cook 15 minutes.
Seal in jars.
Hot water bath 5 minutes.

title: spring salad
directions: Boil the macaroni. Cool completely. In a large bowl, combine salad dressing, sugar, vinegar and milk. Slice in the vegetables, using as many as you want. Add macaroni. Refrigerate overnight.

title: marinated bean salad
directions: Mix together water, vegetable oil, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over vegetables and marinate overnight.

title: marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Marinate chicken, lamb or beef for kabobs.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.	Chop bell pepper and onion.
Mix cabbage, bell pepper, onion, pimentos, mustard seed, and salt.
Bring water, sugar, and vinegar to a boil.
Boil until sugar is dissolved.	Cool and pour over vegetable mixture.
Store in covered container and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Drain before serving.

title: tuna gumbo
directions: Melt margarine in a large pot.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic. Saute for about 5 minutes. Combine flour and chicken broth.
Mix well. Add to onion mixture, stirring constantly. Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Prepare rice according to package directions.
Add tuna and okra to sauce. Simmer for 10 minutes. Stir lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and cayenne pepper.
Serve over rice.

title: red-hot cider
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine juice and candies.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 4 minutes or until candies dissolve. Serve hot or cold.
If desired, garnish with apple wedges or cinnamon sticks.
Makes 8 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: black-eyed pea soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions in enough water to cover them for about 20 minutes.
Cook remaining ingredients for 5 minutes.
Add black-eyed peas (not drained).
Add tomatoes.
Simmer about 30 minutes.

title: california mashed potatoes
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, cover potatoes with water.
Potatoes are peeled and cut into chunks.
Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low and simmer 20 minutes or until tender; drain. Return potatoes to saucepan.
Mash potatoes.
Stir in onion soup mix and parsley blended with hot milk and sour cream.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: apple cream pie
directions: Slice 6 cups apples.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Gently stir into apples.
Arrange apple slices in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Blend in mixer 2 eggs, heavy cream, vanilla and 1/4 cup sugar.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 375° covered with foil for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 additional minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat. Stir in peanut butter.
Add dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Form into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press with back of a fork to make crisscross design.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: fiesta shrimp pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Rinse immediately with cold water and drain well.
Toss with remaining ingredients, except tomatoes.
Pour dressing over all and add oregano.
Toss again. May serve at room temperature or chilled.
Good made the night before.
Spoon salad onto lettuce lined plate.
Slice tomatoes in half and place on top of each serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: lemon icing by tuffy
directions: Boil until thick, stirring constantly.
Set to cool.
Whip 1/2 cup sweet cream.
When cool, put in mixture.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer ingredients in Pyrex dish starting with cream cheese, refried beans, salsa and then shredded cheese.
Heat in microwave about 2 to 3 minutes on High; serve with nacho chips.
Instead of jalapeno peppers, you can use sliced black olives.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix first two ingredients and pat firmly into dish.
Cook the powdered sugar, 1 stick margarine and 2 eggs together until thickened to pudding consistency.
Place sliced bananas on top of crust mixture and cover with drained pineapple.
Pour pudding mixture over pineapple and top with whipped topping.
Cover with cherries and nuts.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Blend mayonnaise, milk, cornstarch and eggs until smooth.
Stir in meat, cheese, onion and pepper. Turn into crust and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown on top and knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: southwestern grilled chicken
directions: Combine ingredients in shallow glass dish; mix well.
Add chicken to marinade; turn to coat.
Cover and refrigerate chicken 4 hours, turning occasionally.
Drain chicken; reserve marinade. Grill chicken over hot coals until done.

title: colleen's salad dressing
directions: Blend well and keep refrigerated.

title: snicker doodle cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly
the
shortening,
eggs
and
1 1/2 cups sugar. Add the flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt; mix all together good and
chill dough.
Make into balls and roll in 2 tablespoons sugar
and
2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: roast beef
directions: Place beef roast on foil that is large enough to wrap roast. Sprinkle roast with tenderizer and pepper.
Mix dry onion soup mix, mushroom soup and water.
Cover roast.
Seal foil.
Bake at 325° for two or three hours, until tender.

title: "italian" style 15 bean soup
directions: In a pan, heat the oil.
Saute the onions until slightly golden.
Add the garlic and celery; saute slightly.
Bring a gallon of water to a boil.
Add the largest beans.
Simmer; remove any scum that forms.
After about 30 minutes, add the next size of beans.
Continue until the split peas and lentils are added.
As any skum forms, skim it from the top.
Add the oil with onions, garlic and celery.
Add the carrots.
Add the vinegar and spices. Add the chicken bouillon or stock.
Stir frequently, but gently. Add the crushed tomatoes (avoid any seeds).
Continue simmering until the beans are soft.
At this point, the soup may be served. However, it may be simmered longer until all of the beans cook into a mush.
If the soup becomes too thick, it may be thinned with chicken stock or water.
Garnish with finely chopped parsley. Serve with crusty bread.

title: chicken cacciatore(low-fat)
directions: In a heavy 12-inch skillet or Dutch oven, brown chicken in hot oil on both sides (4 to 5 minutes total).
Remove chicken; set aside.
Add mushrooms, red pepper, onion and garlic to skillet drippings.
Cook until the vegetables are tender.
Add wine and crushed red pepper into vegetable mixture.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, until almost all liquid evaporates.
Add undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, lemon juice, basil, sugar, thyme, salt and pepper.
Return chicken to pan. Simmer uncovered 15 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: a delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine, sugar and nuts.
Press into pizza pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix and spread on crust cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip.
Add as last layer fruit pie filling.
Then put Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with nuts.
The blueberry pie filling is great.

title: crunchy stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms gently in cool water or wipe with a damp cloth. Remove stems and chop.
Saute onion in butter or margarine.
Add chopped stems, pecans, bread crumbs, lemon juice and salt.
Mix well.
Mound mushroom caps with stuffing.
Broil for 4 minutes, about 4 inches from heat, or cook in microwave oven on High 2 to 3 minutes until heated throughout.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan over low heat. Add remaining ingredients and stir. Pour into pie shell and bake 30 minutes at 400°. Cool. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: potato-cheese soup
directions: Cook all vegetables and chicken cube 15 minutes.
Mix flour and milk until smooth.
Add to potatoes.
Add cubed cheese and cook on medium-low until cheese is melted.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Mix everything together, except butter and vanilla.
Cook until it comes to a soft ball.
Then add butter and vanilla.
Put pot in water and beat until creamy.
Spoon onto waxed paper.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions. Brown flour in butter in heavy skillet.

title: cream cheese filled cupcakes
directions: Prepare chocolate cake mix as directed and fill cupcake tins 1/2 full.
Combine cream cheese, eggs, sugar and salt.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Stir in chips.
Spoon 1 heaping teaspoonful of filling into center of batter.
Bake at directed on box.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese until smooth. Mix milk and instant pudding until smooth.
Combine with cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In a plastic flower pot, make layers with crushed cookies, starting and ending with cookies. Garnish with plastic flowers and gummy worms.
Chill well before serving.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions on package.
Heat oven to 350°.
Pour cake mix in jelly roll pan or 12 x 18 x 1-inch deep pan.
Cool cake.
While cake is cooling, cook vanilla pudding with milk (do not use instant pudding mix).
Cool pudding mix after cooking enough to thicken.
Add 1 large package cream cheese; mix well, blending cheese into pudding until smooth.
Pour blended cheese and pudding mix, then fold in Cool Whip before pouring mixture on top of baked cake.
Spread on cake evenly.
Then sprinkle coconut on top and chopped nuts, spreading evenly over the fine coconut; top with ground nuts.
Then cut drained maraschino cherries fine over top.
Chill and cut into squares to serve. Serves 20 or more.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Place uncooked pork chops in baking dish.
Combine soups, margarine, stuffing mix and chicken broth; mix well.
Pour mixture on pork chops.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes to 1 hour, depending on thickness of pork chops.

title: banana nougat cookies(this was scotty's favorite cookie!)
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg together. Cut in shortening.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, 1/4 cup of the sugar and salt in a saucepan.
