Add pineapple and cook, stirring constantly, until clear and thickened.
Add egg yolks which have been beaten with 1/4 cup of the sugar.
Cook for 1 minute.
Cool.
Then add lemon juice and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with a meringue made by beating the 2 egg whites until quite stiff.

title: cinnamon-applesauce jello
directions: Bring 1 cup water to simmering point.
Dissolve cinnamon hearts, stirring to dissolve.
Add to jello and stir until dissolved.
Add applesauce and chill until set.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked ham
directions: Put brown bag, single ply over ham.
According to size of ham, bake at 325° for 30 minutes per pound.
After ham is baked, score ham as follows; with sharp knife make diagonal cuts 1/8 in. deep and about 3/4 in. apart across entire fat surface of ham. Repeat at an angle make squares or diamonds.
Stud top of ham, in pattern, with whole cloves.
Place a slice of pineapple over ham to decorate.
In center of each pineapple slice place a maraschino cherry.
With brown sugar add juice of pineapple and cherry juice. Stir until fully blended.
Pour brown sugar mix over ham.
Reset oven to 425°.
Return ham to oven, glazing with brown sugar mix over the ham several times.

title: salmon macaroni salad
directions: Drain salmon, remove bone and skin, flake.
Combine salmon, peas and macaroni.
Toss lightly.
Serve on lettuce with sliced hard-cooked eggs.

title: baked chicken breasts supreme
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except chicken and bread crumbs.
Place chicken in mixture and turn to coat.
Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Remove chicken from marinade.
Coat each piece with crumbs.
Arrange on shallow baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until juices run clear.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake in a cast-iron frying pan.
Put shortening in pan while oven is heating so the shortening will be hot and ready to add to cornmeal.

title: caesar pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta like directions; drain.
Rinse in cold water and drain again.
Immerse sun-dried tomatoes in boiling water; let stand 10 minutes or until softened.
Drain well.
Combine pasta, tomato halves, cucumber, bell pepper, cheese and pepper.
Add desired amount of dressing, tossing to coat.
Cover and chill 2 hours before serving.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: crab canapes
directions: Split muffins in half.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on muffins.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cut in 6 to 8 pieces before baking.
(Will cut more easily if you put in freezer for an hour or two before cutting.)
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries with orange peeling.
Add sugar, pecans and pineapple.
Let sit.
Prepare jello as per instructions.
Let it gel just a little.
Then add cranberry mix. Chill completely until gelled.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease an 11 x 7-inch baking pan.
Put flour, sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl of electric mixer and mix on low for 15 seconds.
Add softened butter and mix until butter pieces are size of peas.
You will see loose flour. Mix in egg.

title: french rice
directions: Combine soup and butter in bowl;
mix well.
Drain mushrooms and water chestnuts, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to liquid to measure 1 1/3 cups. Add to soup mixture.
Stir in mushrooms, water chestnuts and rice.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: pecan tassies
directions: For Cheese Pastry:
Let cream cheese and 1/2 cup butter soften at room temperature. Stir in flour. Chill slightly.
Shape in 2 dozen 1-inch balls. Place in tiny ungreased muffin cups.
Press dough against bottom and sides.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water as directed on pkg. In casserole dish cut Velveeta cheese in small pieces, cut up butter, add salt, and when macaroni is done drain water off and add to cheese, etc. Then add milk and stir lightly. Bake in 350 degree oven for about 30 minutes or until bubbles all over top.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with pepper and salt.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Mix other dry ingredients and put in plastic bag.
Dip chicken in buttermilk.
Place a few pieces at a time in dry mixture and shake.
Place chicken in a baking dish which has been sprayed with a nonstick preparation.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes or until chicken is brown and tender.

title: flounder
directions: Place fish in pan.
Top with condensed soup, mixed with sherry. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over fish.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: tuna rice muffinettes
directions: Pour mixture into greased muffin cups. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in skins; cool, peel and cut into cubes. Combine cheese and butter; heat until melted.
Add sour cream, onion and potatoes; stir lightly.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with more shredded cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: israeli salad
directions: Wash and core tomatoes.
Slice in half between stem and core ends; squeeze gently to remove most of watery pulp and seeds; discard.
Finely chop tomatoes and place in mixing bowl.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and line with a single layer of graham crackers.
Add milk to pudding and beat as box directs. Fold Cool Whip into pudding.
Spread 1/2 pudding mixture over crackers.
On top of pudding, add another layer of graham crackers.
Put remaining pudding on top of crackers.
Put one last layer of crackers on and spread frosting to desired thickness. Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Brown onion in butter. Add other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Slice carrots.
Cut broccoli and cauliflower into small flowerets.
Sprinkle dry seasoning over mixture.
Pour liquid Italian dressing over vegetables and mix well.
Refrigerate, covered, at least 24 hours.
Stir or shake frequently.

title: butternut squares(old southern recipe)
directions: Cream 1/2 cup butter, 1/2 cup sugar and egg yolks until fluffy.
Add the sherry.
Work in 1 1/2 cups flour until very stiff.
Roll in two thin sheets.
Place one layer in a greased pan.

title: millionaire pies
directions: Combine milk and lemon juice. Add pineapple and pecans.
Whip the cream with sugar and fold into mixture.
Pour in crusts and chill.

title: grilled venison (deer)
directions: Take small pieces of deer meat and tenderize until very thin. Remove as much stringy fat as possible. Roll meat to about the size of a meat ball. Wrap with 1/2 slice of bacon, securing with toothpick. Combine other ingredients, any amount you need to cover for marinating. Let set at least overnight or 2 days if you want. Remove from marinade and grill. This can be seasoned if you desire. The seasoned pepper needs to be used sparingly, unless you want spicy taste.

title: cheese crepe soup
directions: Beat egg well; mix in flour.
Add water slowly and beat with blender until smooth.
Butter liberally 8-inch frypan.
Heat, then pour in 3 tablespoons batter.
Tilt pan quickly until batter covers bottom.
Cook until pancake is light brown on bottom. Turn and cook other side.
When all are ready.
Sprinkle 2 teaspoons of cheese in center of pancake; roll.
Heat chicken broth.
Put 2 or 3 pancakes in soup bowl.
Pour broth on top.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Peel 2 apples; core and dice.
Core and dice 1 apple, leaving peel on.
Mix with lemon juice.
Add celery, walnuts, mayonnaise and cinnamon.
Stir lightly to mix.
Chill in covered container until ready to serve.
Beat cream with sugar and vanilla in small bowl until stiff and stir into apple mixture.
Serve on greens.

title: lemon chiffon pie(husband favorite)
directions: Blend sugar, gelatin, water, juice and egg yolks in saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until it boils.
Add rind.
Place pan in cold water; cool until mixture mounds when dropped from spoon. Fold into a meringue of egg whites, cream of tartar and sugar.
Pile into cooled baked pie shell.
Chill several hours until set.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute celery, onions and green pepper lightly.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole.
Add the following topping:

title: cel cowan's spoon bread
directions: Beat eggs and milk until frothy.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour in baking dish in which butter has been melted.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes, then at 350° for 5 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: barbie's apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour orange juice over apples.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle evenly over apples.
Combine flour and remaining sugar. Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Spoon over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until apples are tender and crust is brown.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream.

title: barbecue beef sandwich
directions: Mix together.
Cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours uncovered at 325°.
Mash with pastry blender.
Put meat mixture on French rolls.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
Add Cool Whip.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer pudding and graham crackers.
Put icing in microwave and thin down.
Then pour and spread on top. Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: chicken milano
directions: Prepare rice as label directs.
Meanwhile, remove skin and bones from chicken breasts; cut breast meat into 1 1/2 inch chunks.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot butter or margarine, cook onion and garlic until onion is tender, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken chunks; cook until chicken is lightly browned on all sides, stirring frequently.
Stir in undiluted tomato soup and remaining ingredients.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: seafood stew
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and cook over medium heat about 30 minutes.
If you want thicker stew, you may add a small can of tomato sauce to thicken it.
Add shrimp and fish; cook until shrimp are pink and fish is flaky.
Serve piping hot in soup mugs or over cooked rice.

title: fajitas
directions: Marinate beef or chicken strips 2 hours.
Remove meat from marinade.
Saute onion and pepper until lightly browned.
Remove from pan.
Add marinated chicken or beef in pan.
Saute until light brown and tender.
Toss with vegetables and spoon into flour tortillas.
Makes 8 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar together.
Cut biscuits into quarters and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place in greased Bundt pan.
Melt butter and mix with brown sugar.
Pour mixture over biscuits.
Cook at 350° until golden brown.

title: microwave spaghetti squash mexicana
directions: Pierce squash deeply with knife in 2 places.
Place on towel in microwave.
Cook on High 24 to 28 minutes until squash is soft when pressed with fingers.
Let stand 5 minutes, then cut lengthwise in half.
Discard seeds.
Using fork, scrape strands onto serving platter.
To serve, pour salsa sauce over squash on platter.
Makes 4 servings.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: southbridge pea soup
directions: Cover split peas with water in large pot and add rest of ingredients except dried onion soup mix.
Bring to a boil and simmer 3 to 4 hours until peas are mushy.
Remove ham bone and bay leaf and add more water if soup is too thick.
Add 1/2 package dried onion soup mix and cook another 1/2 hour.
Serve with croutons.

title: chicken breasts with curried cream seasoning(serves 4)
directions: Cut the chicken into strips about 1/2-inch wide.
Melt the butter in a skillet and when it is hot, but not brown, add the chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Stir often until the chicken loses its raw appearance, approximately two minutes.
Sprinkle the chicken with the shallots and curry powder. Stir well to blend and saute approximately one minute.
Remove the chicken and place in a bowl.

title: beef stew
directions: Place potatoes, onions and baby carrots in slow-cooker.
Add bell pepper and beef.
In small bowl, combine broth or bouillon, oregano, paprika, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Pour over meat and vegetables.
Cover and cook on LOW 9-10 hours. Turn pot on HIGH.
In small bowl, dissolve cornstarch in water; stir into cooked stew mixture.
Cover and cook on HIGH 15-20 minutes or until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 or 7 servings.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Skin the chicken breasts and place in a greased baking pan. Place a slice of Swiss cheese over each.
Mix together the soup and the wine; spoon over the chicken.
Crush the croutons and sprinkle over the chicken mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 50-60 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Combine all ingredients except noodles and put into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 20 minutes.
Add chow mein noodles and bake 10 minutes more.

title: amish cookies(melt in your mouth)
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, & oil together; add egg and cream well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and vanilla.
Refrigerate one hour.
Drop by small amount on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press lightly with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Dough can be refrigerated indefinitely.
Yield: 250 cookies.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dice onion and mix into shredded cheese.
Mix mayonnaise in 1 tablespoon at a time until mixture is sticky (not soupy).
Place mixture in a shallow baking plate. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly and light brown on edges. Serve hot in baking dish with Wheat Thins for dipping.

title: aunt dibby's chicken supreme
directions: Wrap each chicken piece in a strip of bacon.
Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch glass pan with beef pieces.
Arrange chicken breasts on beef.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken. Bake at 275°, uncovered, 3 hours.
(May also be baked at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.)

title: black bean and corn salsa
directions: In medium bowl, blend mayonnaise and ranch dressing.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve chilled or at room temperature. Great with tortilla or corn chips.

title: broccoli cheese salad
directions: Combine broccoli, cheese, bacon and onion.
Make a dressing of mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; toss with broccoli mixture.

title: jamaican coconut bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add coconut, sugar, vanilla and beaten egg, beating the mixture well after each addition.
Pour in milk, a little at a time, until dough is firm but not sticky.
(Add a little more flour if it should become so.) Knead the dough
for a few minutes.
Shape into loaves to fit your greased loaf pans to about 3/4 full. Dust tops with fine sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: huckleberry cream pie
directions: Cook and cool.
When ready to put pie together, fold in 1/2 cup whipping cream (whipped).

title: crock-pot pot roast
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Slow cook for 6 hours on high.

title: easy stuffed peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers.
Split lengthwise.
Steam or cook shells in small amount of boiling water about 5 minutes. Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, beaten egg, onion, salt, pepper and one-half can of soup.
Fill peppers with stuffing.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Pour remaining soup over peppers. Continue cooking 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spiced turkey
directions: Sprinkle seasonings over turkey breast and cover with onion rings.
Cover with foil and roast as normal.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift flour, soda and salt onto a platter or waxed paper.
In a large bowl beat oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla at medium speed of electric mixer for 3 or 4 minutes until well blended.
Gradually add flour mixture; beat until smooth.
Fold in pecans and apples.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool on wire rack 20 minutes. If desired, dribble Brown Sugar Topping over warm cake, however, the cake is marvelous plain.
Serve warm or cold.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Sift dry ingredients and add to shortening.
Add rest of ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
After baking you can pour wine or bourbon over cake.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling in 9 x 13 pan.
Arrange pineapple chunks on cherries.
Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple.
Spread melted oleo on cake mix.
Top with chopped nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil and add jello; then cool.
Mix cool whip and buttermilk together; add to jello mixture.
Add nuts and set in shallow baking dish.

title: southern pralines
directions: Combine sugars, soda, salt and buttermilk.
Cook in heavy saucepan or iron pot.
Cook to 230°.
Add butter and vanilla. Beat until thick; add pecans or place one whole half on each pattie after dropped.
Keep over low heat and dip by tablespoon onto waxed paper.
Use
newspaper under waxed paper to keep from sticking to cabinet top.

title: fettucine with smoked turkey
directions: Melt butter in a heavy skillet over medium heat and saute shallots until soft, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Add peppercorns and saute 30 seconds.
Add wine and boil until almost no liquid remains in skillet, about 2 minutes.
Stir in cream, nutmeg and turkey and heat for about 5 minutes until sauce thickens.
Do not boil.
Combine hot fettucine with sauce and toss to mix thoroughly.
Serve on warmed plates and sprinkle with chives. Pass Parmesan cheese separately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cold raspberry yogurt soup
directions: Place raspberries in bowl.
Attach bowl and flat beater.
Turn to speed 6 and mash berries 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients and mix on speed 2 for 1 minute.
Refrigerate until well chilled. Yields 8 servings.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Mix altogether.
Grease with butter (1 1/2-quart dish).
Pour ingredients in dish.
Then melt 1 stick or less butter and pour over bread stuffing in separate bowl.
Cover top of broccoli mixture with stuffing.
Bake 40 minutes with no cover at 350°.

title: french bread casserole
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and Karo syrup.
Spread on bottom of prepared 9 x 13 pan.
Layer bread crumbs on top of mixture. Whisk eggs and half and half together.
Add vanilla and cinnamon; pour over bread, making sure to coat all of the bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Bring dates, raisins, apples and water to a boil in large saucepan.
Cook for 3 minutes; cool.
Combine with eggs, flour, brown sugar, shortening, vanilla and pecans in bowl; mix well. Chill in refrigerator.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown. Remove to wire rack to cool.
Yield:
36 servings.
Make cookies a uniform size to assure even baking.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, cheese, onions, eggs, flour, salt and pepper.
Beat until fluffy.
Bake, uncovered, in a 300° oven for 35 minutes.
During last 5 minutes, cover casserole with onion rings.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 French fried onions.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: carrot dill pickles
directions: Place straight carrot strips upright in sterilized jars, together with red pepper, dill seed and garlic button.
Mix vinegar, water and salt in saucepan; bring to boil.
Pour boiling mixture over carrots in jars.
(Have jars warm so they will not break.)
Screw lids on tight.
Let set for a week before opening.

title: easy pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Make cake mix according to directions on the box.
Heat butter in pan, preferably an iron skillet.
Put in brown sugar and cook slightly.
Place the 5 pineapple slices around pan; one in the middle and 4 around it.
Cook a bit more.
Then, place nuts and cherries on and around pineapple slices.
Continue to cook slightly. Pour cake mix batter in on the pineapple layer.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes until cake tests done.
While still quite warm, turn the cake out onto a large plate.
Serve hot or cool.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Pack ground
beef
in the bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish. Season
with
onion
and favorite spices.
Pour corn on top of meat.
Smooth
soup
over
top of corn.
Arrange Tater Tots in rows over top of soup.
Bake in moderate oven (350° to 375°) for 45 minutes.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in beaten egg and whites.
Add almonds and vanilla; stir well. Gradually add flour, stirring well between each addition.
Drop cookie dough in balls onto greased cookie sheet.
Brush cookies with mixture of 1 egg white, 1 1/2 teaspoons sugar and 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Bake in preheated oven at 325 ° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until light, golden brown.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: salmon stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Wash and decap mushrooms.
Put a teaspoon full of salmon spread into each mushroom head. place the mushrooms in a large pan.
Sprinkle the cheddar cheese on top of the mushrooms.
Pour the wine along side the mushrooms and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Bake in 9 x 13-inch glass dish at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Peel and core apples; sprinkle with Fruit-Fresh.
Place flour in a bowl; with a pastry blender, cut in margarine.
Add oil and maple syrup; continue to mix with blender.
Place in baking dish.
Pat down smoothly with the back of a spoon.
Add apples and seasonings as desired.
Cover top with foil, securely wrapped. Bake, remove foil and cool on rack.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and put in baking dish.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Place chicken on top of soup mixture.
Cook at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Test for doneness of chicken and rice.
This is real good and there is no premixing.

title: penny's punch(2-quart)
directions: In large saucepan, dissolve sugar in water, lemon, cinnamon, cloves, allspice and apple juice.
Cook over medium-high heat for 15 minutes.
Add wine; heat, but do not boil.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: independence day salad
directions: Combine ham, potatoes, celery, lettuce, pickles, green pepper and 2 eggs.
Mix seasonings, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Blend into ham mixture.
Pile onto bed of lettuce.
Garnish with sprigs of watercress, remaining eggs and ripe olives, if desired.
Yields 6 to 10 servings.

title: glory b cake
directions: Mix together. Pour in greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crispy fried carrots
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; set aside.
Beat egg white until foamy; stir in buttermilk and hot sauce.
Dip carrots in buttermilk mixture; drain off excess mixture and dredge in cornmeal mixture.
Pour oil to depth of 1-inch in Dutch oven; heat to 350°.
Fry carrots 2 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve carrots immediately.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: tandoon chicken (roasted chicken)(indian)
directions: Take a big mixing bowl and mix all the ingredients in it.
Mix it very nicely that it becomes like a paste.
Then mix chicken drumsticks in it.
Keep the whole pan in the refrigerator for 4 to 6 hours before eating.

title: super bowl casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Cook macaroni as directed on the package. Drain. Brown meat, peppers and onion in skillet. Pour off excess fat. Mix in macaroni and tomatoes. Put in casserole dish and top with cheese. Cover and bake 20 minutes.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Grill chicken slowly.
Sprinkle lemon pepper over chicken; flip and do the same for side two.
Grill to desired tenderness.

title: marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a jar.
Cover and shake well.
Great for lamb, London broil, chicken, etc.

title: raisin puffs
directions: Boil raisins in water until water is gone. Cream sugar and shortening in bowl and then add eggs. Add vanilla and dry ingredients; mix well. Add the boiled raisins last. Form balls of dough the size of walnuts; roll in granulated sugar and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Rinse medium saucepan with cold water (do not dry).
Pour in milk and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir in rice.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered until rice is tender (40 minutes), stirring occasionally.
Meanwhile, in small bowl combine cream, sugar, egg yolks, vanilla and salt.
Set aside.

title: banana punch
directions: Heat 3 cups water and sugar until dissolved.
Add the other 3 cups water then.
Blend the bananas and pineapple juice in the blender.
Add orange juice, lemonade and water.
Mix everything except ginger ale in a large container.
Divide and pour into wide mouth containers and freeze.

title: sloppy joe casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as label directs; drain.
Prepare seasoning mix with hamburger (cook and drain hamburger), tomato paste, tomato sauce and 1 1/4 cups water.

title: stuffed baked salmon
directions: Melt butter in pan; saute celery and onion until tender, then toss with rice, lemon rind, salt, thyme and lemon juice.
This is enough to stuff a large salmon.
Sprinkle inside of fish with salt; stuff fish.
Spray foil and wrap fish in foil.
Prick holes in bottom.
Measure at thickest part of fish and bake in 450° oven, allowing 10 minutes cooking time for each inch of stuffed thickness.
Serve with lemon slice.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juices from pineapple and mandarin oranges; add to jello mix and mix well.
Add fruits and top real thick with baby marshmallows.
Add cream or Dream Whip, mixed with the mayonnaise. Grate cheese thick on top.
Let mellow overnight, if possible. This keeps for several days in refrigerator if covered.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Add chocolate syrup, then dry ingredients.
Place in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: old fashioned iron skillet chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Melt butter in skillet, add sugar mixture.
Beat eggs and add milk.
Add a little at a time to skillet stirring constantly.
Cook slowly.
When thick enough remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: microwave apples
directions: Take core out of apples and arrange in a microwave safe dish. Put Sweet 'N Low and brown sugar over apples.
Sprinkle a
little apple
pie
spice over them.
Pour water into dish; cover
with wax
paper
and cook for about 6 minutes on High. Check,
if
not done, cook about 3 more minutes.
Every microwave is different. Cook according to yours.

title: kisses kookies
directions: Mix ingredients together in a large bowl.
Roll into 1-inch balls, then in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet 3 inches apart. Place thumbprint in cookie.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, then place a kiss (unwrapped) into the indent.
Put back into the oven for 2 to 5 minutes more.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cookie factory chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix together flour and oatmeal. Put small amount into blender until it turns to powder. Add salt, baking powder and baking soda. Mix all ingredients together. Add chocolate chips and nuts. Make golf ball sized cookies 2-inches apart. Bake at 375° on an ungreased cookie sheet for 8 minutes (or a little longer).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Blend flour and water together until thick.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased casserole dish and bake 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: chocolate sour cream cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, Crisco and cocoa, then add eggs. Stir in alternately the sour cream, flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Add boiling water and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seafood salad casserole
directions: Add seafood to chopped vegetables.
Stir in mayonnaise, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix as for salad.
Put in 3-quart casserole and top with chips.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add one egg at a time; beat thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a well greased and floured large tube pan.
Frost cake with Chocolate Pound Cake Frosting.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press mixture into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Beat Dream Whip according to package directions and fold this into cream cheese mixture.
Spread over graham cracker crust and top with pie filling.
Chill.

title: sand tarts
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Add sugar.
Stir in and blend well the flour, nuts, vanilla and water.
Chill until firm enough to shape with fingers.
Form into small date shaped pieces.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar as soon as removed from oven.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Mix in order, mixing well after each addition.
Drop by small pieces on cookie sheet.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.
Add chocolate chips or nuts, if desired.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan; add cocoa and stir well.
Mix eggs, sugar and salt together.
Alternately stir in melted ingredients and flour into sugar mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour batter into greased and floured 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Remove and spoon on Marshmallow Creme or marshmallows.
Spread with knife to make a layer on top of hot cake.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Tie spices in a cloth.
Add juices and sugar in pot with spices.
Heat until very hot.
Very good and pretty, especially at Christmas.
Remove spice bag after juices are hot!

title: barbecue beans
directions: Cook hamburger in a little water for 1 hour.
Add all ingredients to hamburger except beans.
Cook 15 minutes, then add beans.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Add pie filling and pineapple. Chill until firm.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg, extract, salt and baking powder.
Stir in flour.
Divide dough in half.
Add food coloring to one half.
Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Pinch off chunks of each color dough and roll into 5-inch ropes.
Pinch a red rope and a white rope together; twist and shape into a candy cane.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 or more minutes, depending on thickness.
Don't let them brown.
Makes 20 to 30 minutes.

title: foolproof pastry
directions: Mix together flour, shortening, sugar and salt with a fork. In a separate dish, mix vinegar, egg and water.
Combine the two mixtures, stirring with a fork, until all ingredients are moistened, then with hands.
Mold dough into 4 balls.
Chill or freeze before rolling.

title: cherry punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Stir in fruit juices and soda; mix well.
Chill with ice in punch bowl.
Makes about 3 1/2 qt.

title: gilda's italian omelet(frittata)
directions: Beat eggs in bowl.
Add salt, pepper, parsley, milk and cheeses.
Melt butter in large 12-inch or more skillet over medium heat.
Add sausage, onion, bell pepper, mushrooms and pepperoni. Cook 1 minute.
Add asparagus or green beans; stir and blend. Pour egg mixture.
Turn down heat.
When mixture has set and thickened and only the top surface is runny, about 10 or 12 minutes, on low heat, run the skillet under the broiler for 30 seconds to 1 minute until the top face has set.
Loosen the Frittata with a spatula and slice it onto a warm platter.
Cut in wedges and serve.
Fresh fruit goes good with this frittata.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix all together with mixer.
Spread on favorite crackers.

title: squash casserole(can substitute asparagus)
directions: Mix crumbs and 1/2 cup butter and line casserole pan saving 1/2 cup for top.

title: baked salmon
directions: Clean salmon and remove small bones.
Put foil in pan and place salmon, skin side down.
Mix marinade ingredients and pour over salmon.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: spicey ornaments
directions: Mix together and pat out.
(I use rolling pin. It isn't real easy to work with.
Sprinkle a little cinnamon out on your work area they roll out a little easier.)
Cut with cookie cutters of your choice.
Hint:
It works better when applesauce is at room temperature.
Make a small hole on top of each, big enough to put a ribbon through.
The hole becomes smaller as it dries.
Dry ornament on wax paper for a couple of days.
Turn occasionally. You DO NOT eat these!

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Bake covered 15 minutes and uncovered for 15 more minutes at 350°.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil and bone chicken.
Chop chicken and save broth.
In a large skillet, melt oleo.
Add flour and brown slightly.
Add soup and enough broth to make thick sauce.
Add green chile sauce and add spices and bouillon cubes.
After sauce is ready, add some to chopped chicken and season to taste.
Grate Cheddar cheese.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix together and let set overnight in refrigerator. Serve with chips.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Bake pie crust 5 minutes. Saute onions in butter. Combine remaining ingredients with onions and butter. Pour in pie crust. Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes and then at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: frijoles(southwest pinto beans)
directions: Sort dry beans, removing stones and broken beans.
Wash in saucepan to remove dust.
Cook beans with oil in pressure cooker about 45 minutes or in crock-pot overnight.
When beans are soft, cut up bacon and fry crisp.
Pour bacon and drippings into bean pot and cook a while longer on low heat.
Add salt, if needed. Serve with fresh tortillas.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Soften jello in 1/2 cup of water.
Combine other ingredients and blend all together in electric mixer for at least 4 minutes. Bake in 3 layers for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ham buns
directions: Split buns and layer ham, then cheese, then ham.
In saucepan melt margarine.
Mix in onion, poppy seed, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend together; pour over buns.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or microwave about 1 1/2 minutes.

title: split pea soup
directions: Put peas in pot.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Cover pot with lid; turn off burner on stove.
Let peas sit for 1 hour. Drain peas and place peas back into pot.
Cut up the carrots and onion; add to pot.
Add salt, pepper and a dash of nutmeg.
Pour the chicken broth into the pot.

title: rice salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Add pimentos for color.

title: cut-out cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Blend well and stir in oats.
Chill dough before rolling out.
Roll out to 1/8 inch thick on floured board.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° about 10 to 12 minutes.
Decorate with frosting. Yield:
6 dozen cookies.
Carbohydrate 6 g, protein 1 g, fat 3 g, calories 55.
One cookie = 1/2 fruit exchange, 1/2 fat exchange.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in a large pan.
Saute onion in butter.
Add cream of chicken soup and milk.
Turn on low heat, then add cheese and broccoli.
Cook until cheese is melted and well blended.

title: vidalia casserole
directions: Layer 1/2 onions in greased dish; cover with 1/2 cheese. Cover with 1/2 crushed chips, then repeat.
Pour soup over all. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: long-awaited chicken divan
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice, water chestnuts, curry and cheese.
Drain broccoli; arrange in bottom of greased casserole.
Spread chicken over broccoli.
Spread soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Scald milk; add shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Sprinkle yeast on warm water; stir to dissolve.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour to milk mixture; beat well by hand or with electric mixer at low speed 1 minute.
Beat in eggs and yeast.
Gradually stir in enough flour, a little at a time, to make a soft dough that leaves the sides of the bowl.

title: barbecue ham steak
directions: Slash flat edge of ham at 1-inch intervals, but do not cut into the meat.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Grill ham about 5 or 6-inches above the coals, brushing often with the barbecue sauce.
Cook about 5 minutes on each side before turning, making 3 turns in all.

title: orange beets
directions: Leave root and one-inch of stem on beets; scrub with a vegetable brush.
Place beets in a saucepan; add water to cover. Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 to 35 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Pour cold water over beets and drain again. Trim off roots and stems and rub off skins; slice beets and set aside.
Combine cornstarch and next three ingredients in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil and cook one minute, stirring constantly.
Add sliced beets and mandarin oranges to sauce; cook until thoroughly heated. Makes six servings.

title: individual meat loaves with pineapple
directions: Mix egg, oats, onion and salt.
Add beef and pineapple; mix well.
Divide into individual shapes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top each loaf with sweet and sour sauce.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Drain and cover tomatoes with cold water, Bring to a boil. Scald over low heat for 15 minutes. Drain and add remaining ingredients. Cook 1/2 hour and seal in hot jars.

title: beef pot pie
directions: Softly cook onion, then add rest of ingredients.
Stir constantly until bubbling.
Put in casserole and cover with pie crust.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes or until crust is done.

title: crispy oven-baked chicken
directions: Combine potato flakes and rest of seasonings.
Dip top of chicken breasts in peanut oil.
Roll in potato mixture.

title: pizza
directions: Preheat oven as directed on package.

title: chicken and cornbread dressing
directions: Boil chicken.
Take off of bones.
Make cornbread.
Have ready.
Mix cornbread and light bread.
Cook celery and onion in broth with margarine or butter.
Mix your bread mixture, with sage, salt and pepper, then your celery and onion, broth from chicken.
Last, add eggs, then just punch your chicken breasts down in dressing.
Make sure you have enough broth so that your dressing will not be dry.
Cook for about 1 1/2 hours at 325°, a little longer if needed.
This serves about 15 people.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Heat slightly to melt sugar.
Good for slaw, lettuce or green beans.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix
and
shape
into
balls
(may need to add a little water to mix).
Cook on cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: standard jerky marinade
directions: Mix ingredients.
Marinate at least 1 hour before drying.

title: poppy noodle casserole
directions: Boil noodles five minutes; drain.
Mix all ingredients, except 1/4 cup butter.* Pour into large baking dish and bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Saute almonds in remaining butter.
Pour on top and watch it disappear.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine bread cubes and 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Stir in broth, eggs, salt, celery, onion, chicken and mushrooms. Spread into a greased 2-quart casserole.
In saucepan, melt the oleo. Brown remaining bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy broccoli soup
directions: In large saucepan simmer chopped onion in a small amount of water.
Add milk, soup and frozen broccoli.
Cook together over low heat until warm.
Add Velveeta cheese and stir until melted.

title: chicken salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine chicken, celery, green onions, lemon juice and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Stir in eggs, mayonnaise, sweet pepper and mustard. Cover; chill for at least 1 hour.

title: howling candy corn cookie bark
directions: Spread cookies, pretzels and raisins into a 13x9 inch lightly greased jelly roll pan. Set aside. Cook and stir chips over low heat until melted and smooth. Quickly drizzle melted chocolate over cookie mixture, spreading with spatula to coat evenly. Top with candy corn and colored sprinkles; pressing lightly into mixture. Chill until firm. Brake into pieces and put into treat bags.

title: peach pudding
directions: Sprinkle flour and sugar over mixture.
Next pour boiling water over entire dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until brown on top.

title: apricot pork medallions
directions: Flatten each piece of pork slightly.
Heat the 1 tablespoon butter over medium-high heat in a skillet.
Saute pork about 2 minutes each side. Remove from pan.

title: governor's rolls
directions: Scald liquid.
Combine sugar, salt, shortening and liquid.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast cakes, dissolved in warm water.
Now, add egg; beat enough to mix the egg in thoroughly.
Stir in enough flour to make the dough clean the bowl as you stir (about 5 cups). Now, grease dough and bowl.
Cover tightly and let it rise.
Put in warm place.
In about 1 hour it will be light.

title: milk shake
directions: Blend.
Makes one serving.
Has 1 gram fat, 113 calories.

title: angel biscuits
directions: In small bowl dissolve yeast in the warm water.
In large bowl combine 5 cups flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda. With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in shortening until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in buttermilk and dissolved yeast until dough leaves side of bowl.
(Dough will be soft.)

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Brown sausage and drain well.
Layer bread, sausage and cheese twice.
Beat together eggs, milk and mustard.
Pour over layers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until a knife comes out clean. Cut into squares and serve.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Heat oil
in
skillet or wok.
Fry all ingredients over low heat for
10 minutes.
Add well beaten egg.
Cook and stir 5 more minutes (may add more soy sauce).

title: layered salad
directions: Chop finely lettuce, cauliflower and onion.
In layer put lettuce, cauliflower, onion, bacon bits, Mozzarella cheese and salad seasoning.
Spread salad dressing on top like icing. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and croutons on top.
Sit in refrigerator overnight, then toss and eat.

title: burritos
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain off fat thoroughly.
Add other ingredients and heat through.

title: steak or chicken marinade
directions: Marinate steak or chicken for 24 hours, then charcoal broil. You'll be reminded of a well known restaurant dish!

title: egg roll
directions: Brown meat with onions; set aside.
Blanch bean sprouts by submerging in 2 cups boiling water; drain.
Plunge into 2 cups cold water; drain.
Chop into small pieces.

title: lime salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in reserved pineapple juice over low heat. Add cream cheese to it.
Melt as well as you can (will be lumpy). Prepare jello according to package instructions, but use 1/2 cup cold water instead of 1 cup water.
Combine pineapple, jello and nuts.
Place in mold or pan.
Chill.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips.
Measure nuts and mix with noodles.
Pour nuts and noodles into melted chips; stir until coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: quick n easy hamburger stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion in butter until onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: bishop's chocolate pie
directions: Mix both puddings and milk with mixer on low speed for 3 or 4 minutes.
Fold in ice cream.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell or standard baked crust.
Let it set for an hour or so and then put Cool Whip on.
Take the Hershey bar and a potato peeler and shave it all over the top as much as you like.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: orange cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg; mix well.
Sift soda and flour together and add to the creamed mixture with orange juice. Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 375° oven or until edges are browned.

title: bran rolls
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add boiling water to All-Bran and salt.
Add this to sugar and Crisco mixture.
Let cool.
In a separate bowl, dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water with 1 teaspoon sugar added.
Add 2 cups flour to sugar, Crisco and bran mixture. Add eggs.
Add 2 cups flour.
Add dissolved yeast.
Add 2 cups flour.
This dough may be kept in the refrigerator and used over a period of week.
Let rise 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water. Dissolve in boiling water. Blend cranberry sauce, lemon juice, pecans, pineapple and mayonnaise. Can add a drop of red food coloring.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Put all other ingredients in large baking dish.
Place pork chops on top.
Cover; cook in a 400° oven for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cook, uncovered, the last few minutes.

title: crunchy jumble cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together and set aside.
Beat butter and sugar until well blended and smooth.
Add egg and vanilla, beat well.
Add sifted ingredients and mix until combined.
Stir in Rice Krispies and chocolate morsels.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
(I use a small size cookie scoop.)
Bake in 350 degree oven for 10 - 12 minutes.

title: banana-bran bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter; beat in egg.
Stir in bran.
Combine bananas, water and vanilla; add to mixture.
Sift in flour, baking powder, salt and soda; add walnuts and stir until blended.
Place in 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake at 325 to 350° for about 50 minutes (test with toothpick; do not overbake).

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray 2-quart casserole dish.
Arrange apples in dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and cinnamon.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, brown sugar and oatmeal.
Cut the margarine and spread over fruit.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Whip all ingredients together.
Serve warm with Ritz crackers. (May substitute crab for shrimp.)

title: microwave macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart casserole.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add milk.
Cook 8 minutes on High, stirring every 1 minute. Add cheese and stir.
Cook 1 minute.
Add macaroni.
Cook 7 minutes on High stirring halfway through.

title: biscuits
directions: Stir together all ingredients and drop by a tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden.

title: salmon and egg pizza
directions: Drain salmon and saute with oil.
Add onion and continue to stir until onion has wilted.
Add slightly beaten eggs to pan and stir until eggs begin to set.
Remove mixture to crust.
Sprinkle with pepper and cheese over mixture.
Place pizza in a 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: cool whip frosting
directions: Put Cool Whip in mixer, then add sugar and vanilla.
Add 2 cups of cocoa for chocolate.

title: sally's baked beans
directions: Combine and bake uncovered at 325° for two hours.

title: 3-step chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in 1/2 c. chocolate chips into batter.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle top with remaining 1/4 c. chocolate chips.

title: sugar-free fruit 'n' nut squares
directions: Simmer water, prunes, dates and raisins four minutes.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and walnuts.
Add dry ingredients until well blended.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 16 squares.

title: green pea dumplings
directions: Melt margarine in a large pot. Add milk. Bring to a boil. Drain peas and add to milk and margarine. Separate layers of biscuits. Drop into mix. Dumplings are ready when they begin to roll up. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Lay split ladyfingers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan to cover. Mix and beat pudding and milk.
Fold into pudding mixture 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Pour over ladyfingers.
Top with other half of split ladyfingers.
Spread remainder of Cool Whip on top.
Crumble Heath chocolate bars on top of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: barbecued soya chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in sauce made with other ingredients for at least 1/2 hour, turning frequently.
Broil over hot coals, basting often with sauce.
Great chicken done on the grill on a nice day!

title: fudge mocha cheesecake
directions: Combine wafer crumbs, butter and powdered sugar.
Butter sides and bottom of an 8-inch spring-form pan.
Press crumb mixture evenly onto bottom of pan.
Melt chocolate over low, but not boiling water.
Stir until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, to cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar, mixing until well blended. Add melted chocolate, instant coffee and salt.
Stir until blended.
Turn mixture into prepared pan.
Bake cake at 350° in center of oven for 40 minutes.
Turn off oven and let cake sit in oven for 45 minutes.
Cover and chill for at least 4 hours before serving.

title: busy-day dinner
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce to low heat and simmer, covered, 30 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Fill mug or cup 1/3 full with mix.
Pour boiling water over mix and stir.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix first 8 ingredients in large mixing bowl with fork, then add next 3 ingredients with beater until everything is mixed together, then fold in nuts and dates.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at least 1 hour or longer if needed.
Test with toothpick.
Instead of dates you can use raisins.

title: penticton sandwiches
directions: Mix Miracle Whip with celery, cheese and Fri Chik and spoon onto bread in open-face fashion.
Broil just long enough to melt cheese and serve hot.
Burger buns are a nice substitute for bread.

title: baked chicken with pineapple
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper; roll in flour.
Brown chicken on both sides in fat.
Combine soup and pineapple; pour into baking dish.
Add chicken on top of sauce and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: hamburg and cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage and put in baking dish.
Saute onion and celery. Add hamburg and heat until redness is gone.
Add uncooked rice, tomato soup and water.
Simmer.
Pour over cabbage.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until rice is done.

title: zippy burgers
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Separate hamburger buns and spread 1/2 can tomato paste on all six halves.
Set aside.
Put margarine in frying pan and saute ground beef and onion.
Melt cheese spread in double boiler and season to taste with garlic and oregano.
Spoon beef on buns and cover with melted cheese.
Bake in a 325° oven for 5 minutes, or until cheese browns.

title: little mountain cake
directions: Measure 1/2 cup of the egg whites (about 4 whites) into large bowl of an electric mixer.
With mixer at highest speed, beat whites until frothy, then gradually beat in 1/2 cup of sugar, one tablespoon at a time, until mixture will stand in stiff, but not dry peaks.
Beat in the salt, vanilla and orange peel.
Stir together the baking powder and flour until blended, then sift mixture over beaten whites; fold until smoothly blended.
Fold in the butter until blended.

title: vegetable cornbread
directions: Mix eggs and sour cream; add Jiffy mix, then add cheese, corn and broccoli.
Pour in skillet with oleo.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: fourteen day pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers (unpeeled), slat and 1 gallon water in a crock.
Let stand covered for 1 week.
Drain.
Place back into crock and pour boiling water over to cover.
Let stand 24 hours; drain.
Place back into crock.
Add alum and pour boiling water over to cover.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain.

title: pasta ala dennis
directions: Cook pasta al dente.
Keep warm.
Heat oil, garlic and onion in a medium skillet until onions wilt; add bacon and take off heat.
Stir together cheese and egg.
Add pasta to skillet with oil, onion, garlic and bacon; toss.
Add cheese and egg mixture and return to heat until egg curdles.
Serve with crunchy French bread and enjoy.

title: rhubarb delight
directions: Crust:
Crush crackers.
Combine with 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Double for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon.
Pour into casserole dish. Top with bacon slices.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Fry onions in butter until golden brown.
Soak bread in milk.

title: polynesian meat balls
directions: Mix together beef, bread crumbs, onion powder, garlic powder, salt and pepper, egg, 1 tablespoon soy sauce and milk.
Roll into meat balls.
Brown and drain fat.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix sugar and oleo in skillet.
Add egg yolks, chopped dates and the pecans.
Cook slowly, stirring for about 10 minutes. Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies.
When cool enough to handle, roll into balls the size of a walnut and then roll in coconut.
Makes 40 servings.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Chill. Serve over a block of cream cheese with crackers.
Also good dip for chicken fingers.
You'll wonder how this got its name.

title: baked cinnamon apples
directions: Wash and core apples; remove peeling from the top 1/3 of each apple.
Arrange in dish large enough to hold them.
In a saucepan, bring water, vanilla, cinnamon and fructose to a boil and pour over apples.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Baste frequently. These are especially good, especially for diabetics.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add raisins and walnuts.
Combine egg, vanilla and melted shortening.
Add to other ingredients.
Dissolve soda in the undrained pineapple. Stir until just blended.
Pour batter in greased 8 x 4 x 4-inch loaf pan. Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Serve with cream cheese spread.

title: pecan brittles
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Sift the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on well-greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 11 to 12 minutes, until golden.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: mystery stew
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
Mix all ingredients in pan with a tight fitting lid.
Cover food with foil before covering with lid.
Bake for 3 hours.
Do not lift lid while cooking.
Serve over rice.

title: salsa
directions: Combine tomatoes, peppers, onions, salt, garlic and vinegar. Bring mixture to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Pour into hot jars leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Process 30 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yields about 7 pints.

title: beef loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Put in shallow loaf pan.
Bake about 45 minutes with cover at 400°.
Uncover last few minutes.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Pare eggplant; cut in cubes.
Cook in salted water until tender.
Mix eggs together.
Add crumbs, onion, butter, salt and pepper.
Drain eggplant; mix all together.
Pour into buttered dish.
Bake in a 400° oven until brown.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients.
Add to hot milk and cook until it thickens.
Put in pie shell.
Beat egg whites and white sugar until stiff.
Put on top of pie and bake at 400° until light brown.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix everything together and marinate overnight.
Place wings on foil-lined cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: apple bars
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until crumbly.
Press half of mixture in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put in apples.
Sprinkle rest of mixture over apples.
Press lightly.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: mammy's fruitcake
directions: Mix soda with fruit juice.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 5 loaves.

title: microwave shrimp dip
directions: Place
cream
cheese
in
quart
baking dish.
Heat, uncovered, in
microwave, using Medium, Slow cook or 50% power for approximately
minutes
or until well melted.
Stir one time during
cooking.
Stir
in
soup, onions and baby shrimp. Cook at same
power
as before for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes or until heated through.
Stir 2 to 3 times during cooking.
Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: cheese log
directions: Chop onions, celery and ham.
Mix together all ingredients. Turn out on plastic wrap and wrap.
Squeeze into desired shape. Roll in chopped pecans.
Chill until 1/2 hour before serving.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add carrots, salad oil and eggs.
Beat until well mixed.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Put batter in two large or 3 small loaf pans which have been oiled and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: In one bowl, cream oil and beaten eggs.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda and add to the mixture.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, stir vinegar and buttermilk together.
Mix all ingredients together.
After stirring, add food coloring and stir it in, until well blended.
Pour evenly into three well-greased and lightly floured round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (oven temps may vary).
Add frosting and chopped walnuts.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix with pudding as directed in an oblong pan. When cake is cool, take out of pan.
Use thread or a knife and slice cake lengthwise to make two long layers.
While cake is baking, mix flour with milk.
Cook until thick (about 2 or 3 minutes).
Let cool.
Mix butter and shortening.
Beat 4 minutes with electric mixer.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat 4 more minutes. Add cooled flour mixture and beat 4 more minutes.
Spread this mixture on bottom layer of cake and put top layer back on.
Slice into bars.
This tastes exactly like Hostess Twinkies.

title: toby's favorite dog biscuits
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all dry ingredients, then add liquids. Mix and knead 3 minutes.
Form into a ball and roll into 1/3 to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into shapes.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet until hard and crisp, 30 minutes, at 350°.
(Dough will be stiff.)

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides in ovenproof skillet; pour off drippings.
Stir in soup and water.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar and beat until creamy.
Add oil.
Blend in dry ingredients with zucchini.
Beat on medium speed for 1 minute.
Mix in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake 1 hour in a 350° preheated oven.

title: summer pasta salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, parmesan cheese and milk, mixing well.
Add all other ingredients except lettuce and toss lightly. Chill several hours and serve on lettuce.

title: sweet-sour beef 'n' cabbage
directions: In skillet, cook beef, onions, celery and green pepper until meat is brown; drain off fat.
Sprinkle meat mixture with rolled oats, parsley, 3/4 teaspoon salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Core cabbage; cut into 6 wedges.
Place on top of meat.
In bowl, combine tomato sauce, vinegar, brown sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper; mix well.
Pour over cabbage and meat.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes until tender.
Serve at once.
Makes 6 servings.
(Cabbage tends to water and thin sauce, so best to serve soon.)

title: steak sandwich(open face)
directions: Mix well and set aside.
Toast 5 or 6 slices of bread in broiler.
Spread 1 side with a little butter and prepared mustard. Spread meat mixture evenly over this.
Make sure to get the meat to the very edge of bread because it will shrink away a little. There should be a good covering of meat, but not too thick. Broil just until meat is done.
Doesn't take long.
Important to use very lean hamburger so the grease doesn't soak up the bread. Very tasty and quick to make.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Set aside.
Grease pizza pan.
Press crescent dough on greased pan.
Press to all sides.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes on lower rack (until puffy).
Reduce heat to 350°. Spread sausage over dough and sprinkle cheese!
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or 2 smaller ones.
Mix all ingredients; beat 30 seconds. Pour into pans.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, for 55 to 65 minutes (9-inch pan).
Cool slightly; loosen sides of loaf from pan.
Remove.
Cool completely before slicing.
To store, wrap and refrigerate no more than 10 days.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Butter a 5-cup souffle dish (or 6 individual dishes).
Put all ingredients, except sharp and cream cheeses, into blender.
Whip to blend.
Add cheese by the chunk.
Mix on high for 5 seconds. Bake for 50 minutes at 375° (or 15 to 20 minutes for individual dishes).

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and chill overnight.
Use as a dip with chips or vegetables.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Drain and mash with fork the artichoke hearts.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 minutes in small casserole dish.
Serve hot with chips, vegetable sticks or Melba toast rounds.

title: candy cane cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt pan.
Beat cake mix, oil, water and egg whites on low speed until moistened. Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often for 20 minutes.
Pour approximately 2 cups batter into pan.
Pour approximately 3/4 cup batter into small bowl.
Stir in food coloring and extract. Carefully pour red batter over white batter in pan.
Carefully pour remaining white over red.
Bake until cake pulls away from sides of pan, 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Invert on serving plate.
Cool completely.

title: top of stove meat loaf
directions: Put all ingredients except water and tomato sauce in a bowl; mix well.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Brown loaves on all sides in a greased frypan over medium heat.
Pour off fat.
Add water.
Pour tomato sauce over loaves.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
Add more water during cooking if needed.
Makes 2 servings.

title: scrapple
directions: Simmer sausage and onion in water, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Stir in corn meal gradually.
Add seasonings, stirring constantly. Simmer 10 minutes more, stirring occasionally. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Chill until firm.
Tip out and slice into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Fry in hot oil until brown on both sides. Serve topped with syrup or salsa.

title: zesty italian chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Pour Prego sauce over chicken and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake until cheese is melted.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Crumble biscuits very fine.
Cover with water and let stand for 10 minutes.
Add 1 cup sugar, cocoa, can of milk and margarine.
Beat with electric mixer.
Beat egg yolks and add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake in square pan until done at 375°; let cool.
Beat egg whites and 1/3 cup sugar.
Spread over pudding and cook until brown.

title: low-fat cauliflower salad
directions: Take the Miracle Whip and milk and make sauce.
Pour over salad mix.

title: marinated pork tenderloin(serves 4)
directions: Place pork in a Ziploc bag.
Mix remaining ingredients together and stir well.
Pour over meat, close bag and let marinate in refrigerator 24 hours.
Grill over medium heat for 10 minutes on each side or until just slightly pink in center.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Mix with butter and Parmesan cheese.
Spread in pan like you would for pie.

title: date balls
directions: Cook margarine, sugar and dates until thick.
Remove from heat; add nuts, Rice Krispies and flavoring. Cool and make into small balls and lightly roll in powdered sugar.
These will keep nicely in a covered container.

title: mandarin orange salad or dessert
directions: Mash crackers; add sugar and stir.
Then add margarine; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (do not mash down); leave a few out to sprinkle on top.
Blend orange juice and mandarin oranges; stir in Cool Whip and then the Eagle Brand milk.
Pour into pan and top with remaining crumbs.
Refrigerate.
Make in a dish or pan size 9 x 12.
Makes about 10 or 12 servings.

title: dipped oreos
directions: Melt almond bark according to directions.
Dip Oreos into almond bark.
Transfer dipped cookies onto waxed paper and sprinkle with sprinkles.

title: cheese-chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Reserve 1 1/2 cans broth.
Simmer celery and onion in broth until tender.
Stir in soup and milk. Add cut up chicken and cheese; melt and serve.
(Add pepper and garlic powder to taste.)

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump one ingredient after the other and bake as directed on cake mix at 350°.

title: quick and easy blueberry dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, layer ingredients as follows: whole graham crackers, Cool Whip, blueberry filling and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle graham crumbs on top for garnish.
Chill overnight for best results.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13 glass baking dish. Stir in dressing packets. Add potatoes and stir until coated. Bake in 350° oven until potatoes are soft, approximately 45 minutes. After you remove from oven, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken breasts in a large boiler and add salt and pepper to taste. Cover with water and bring to a boil. When chicken is done, remove from water and allow to cool on a plate. After cooling, tear apart to desired size pieces.

title: fiesta casserole
directions: Saute onion and garlic in salad oil in large frying pan until soft (not browned).
Remove with slotted spoon to set aside. Shape ground beef into large patty and brown (in same pan) on both sides, then break into chunks.
Stir in onion mixture, tomatoes, beans, chili, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Place 3 tortillas (cut in quarters) in 3-quart baking dish.
Top with about one cup of sauce and repeat until all is used, ending with sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Stick several wedges of tortillas on top.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken wellington
directions: Thaw pastry for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle chicken with seasonings. In a medium skillet, brown chicken in 3 tablespoons butter; set aside.
Add remaining butter to skillet.
Add onion and mushrooms; saute until tender and liquid has evaporated.
Stir in parsley. On a lightly floured surface, roll each sheet to 14-inch square; cut into four 7-inch squares.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine cream cheese with mustard; spread over chicken cutlets.
Spread each pastry square with 2 tablespoons mushroom mixture.
Top with chicken breast.
Brush edges of pastry with water; wrap pastry around chicken, pressing edges to seal.
Place seam-side down on ungreased baking sheets.
Brush tops with egg wash.
Bake 25 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bohemian bread dumplings
directions: Mix eggs, milk and salt together.
Add bread and flour.
Flour hands and form into balls.
Drop into rapidly boiling water for about 20 minutes. Remove and drain thoroughly.
Cut in halves with string or really sharp knife. Serves 4.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften the cream cheese and mix well.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
After chilled, shape into ball and roll in pecans or walnuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: tacodillas
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add package taco seasoning mix and water according to package directions.
For each tacodilla, place 1/4 c. shredded cheddar cheese on a soft taco shell.
Break a hard shell in half; place on top of cheese.
Top hard shell with 1/6 of meat mixture; fold in half. Heat 1 tablespoon vegetable oil in large skillet; add 3 tacodillas.
Cook on each side over medium heat until golden brown and cheese is melted.
Repeat with remaining tacodillas.
Cut each tacodilla in half; serve with taco sauce.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix by hand with wooden spoons.
Pour into greased 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: warren's rolls
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender or 2 knives.
Add eggs and milk, one tablespoon at a time.
Mix thoroughly.
Break dough into small pieces to form rolls about 1 1/2 x 3-inches.
Flatten rolls slightly and roll in sesame seed.
Place on cookie sheet about 3/4-inch apart and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans. Spread on bottom of greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box. Spread over pecans and coconut.
Mix together cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Spread over cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Mix in remaining ingredients by hand. Stir in blueberries. Divide batter into 12 small or 6 large muffin cups. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Mix together chicken, celery, onion and cream cheese.
Set aside.
Lay out the crescent rolls and spread them out gently with fingers.
Put about 1/4 cup mixture into each crescent.
Close each up and roll in melted butter and crushed croutons.
Bake at 375°. Turn them after 15 to 20 minutes and bake 15 to 20 more minutes until golden brown.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Place warm water in a bowl.
Add dry milk and mix.
Add sugar and stir until smooth.
In sugar doesn't dissolve well, set bowl in a pan of hot water.
Use in any recipe calling for 1 can of sweetened condensed milk.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger with salt and a little sugar.
Add onion and mango or pepper.
Add a little water and cook until onion and pepper are tender.
Add mustard and catsup; simmer for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: marinated eye of round
directions: Pierce roast in several places with a sharp knife.
Sprinkle salt and lemon pepper seasoning over entire surface of roast. Place in a large shallow dish; set aside.
Combine soy sauce and remaining ingredients in a bowl, stir well.
Pour over roast. Cover and marinate in refrigerator 8 hours, turning occasionally.

title: firecracker casserolenederland, texas
directions: Brown ground meat and taco seasoning.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Mix together.
Cook until as thick as you want.
(Cook slowly.)

title: layered jello salad
directions: Make lime jello as directed; add pineapple and set in square pan.
Combine lemon jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions on package.
(If using whipping cream, add sugar and vanilla.)
Beat softened cream cheese into lemon jello until well blended, then fold in Dream Whip.
Pour over lime jello. Set until firm.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Ingredients for filling are in parenthesis.

title: butterflies or rosettes
directions: Mix ingredients.
Set aside.
Heat oil.
Heat irons or forms in heated oil.
Wipe iron on brown paper bags; dip heated iron into batter, then into heated oil for about 20 to 25 seconds. Remove cookie from iron with fork.
Repeat process until finished with batter.
Powdered sugar or jelly may be added to cookies.

title: fluffy lemon torte
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, butter and 2 tablespoons sugar, pressing into the bottom of an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes. Dissolve lemon jello in boiling water; chill until syrupy. In a medium mixing bowl, beat chilled milk until stiff peaks form. In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Add jello mixture and mix well. Fold in whipped milk. Pour over crust. Chill for at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all together in large mixing bowl.
Spread in greased 9 x 14-inch casserole.
Bake about 25 minutes or until hot through and golden brown.

title: pineapple coconut chess pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
cook at 350° for 40 minutes, cover with foil and continue to cook another 20 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix 2 1/2 bottles of food coloring and sweetened condensed milk well.
Let stand.
Cream together Crisco and sugar; add eggs and color paste.
Beat well.
Add buttermilk and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour and beat by hand.
Add vinegar and soda and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 or 30 minutes.

title: no cook freezer jam
directions: Combine fruit and sugar in a medium bowl.
Set aside for 15 minutes.
Stir in the Pectin for 3 minutes and let stand for 5 minutes.
Put in freezer jars or freezer containers; be sure to leave 1/2-inch space on top of container for expansion.
Cover container and freeze for up to one year.
Makes nine 8 oz. jars.

title: all-purpose tomato sauce
directions: This sauce may be used on spaghetti, lasagna or Sloppy Joes. All you have to add to it is your choice of meat and pasta.

title: meat balls in sauce
directions: Mix meat, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Add eggs.
Mix well. Form into small balls; flatten slightly.
Brown.
Return all meatballs to skillet.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over meatballs.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, and watch to prevent burning.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with cheese and sour cream.
Pour over Tater Tots.
Cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Bake in medium or large baking dish.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Put water and broccoli in a large saucepan.
Add margarine, onion salt, garlic salt and onion and simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Add milk and cheese; stir constantly to avoid sticking.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes more, then mix cornstarch and milk together and add to thicken soup.
Heat thoroughly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: verna's chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk together. Bring to a boil. Let boil 12 to 15 minutes. Pour over nuts, butter, marshmallow cream, chocolate chips and vanilla. Mix together quickly and pour into greased dish or pan. Let cool.

title: honey-lime pork chops
directions: Trim fat from pork chops.
Place chops in shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Combine lime juice and next 3 ingredients.
Pour over pork chops.
Cover and refrigerate about 4 hours, turning pork chops occasionally.
Coat a large, nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add pork chops, reserving marinade.
Brown meat 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Add marinade.
Cover and cook 5 minutes or to desired degree of doneness, turning once.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: In large bowl, combine sour cream, minced onions or chives, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Peel and thinly slice cucumbers; add and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix together popcorn, M&M's and peanuts.
Melt together marshmallows, oleo and oil and pour over dry ingredients.
Stir well.
Press into greased angel food cake pan.
Let set.
Turn out and slice with electric knife.

title: country style baked beans
directions: In a slow cooker, empty the cans of beans.
Do not drain. Finely chop the onion and bell pepper.
Add the onion, bell pepper, sugar and barbecue sauce.
Cover and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Take top off and cook until most of the liquid is absorbed.

title: creamed spinach(microwave)
directions: Microwave spinach in box until thawed, 6 to 9 minutes.
Drain thoroughly and set aside.
Place onion and margarine in 1-quart casserole.
Microwave until onion is tender, 3 to 4 minutes.
Add cream cheese.
Microwave until softened.
Stir in salt, pepper and nutmeg until smooth.
Blend in milk.
Mix in spinach. Microwave until heated through, stirring once.

title: low-fat baked apple french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan lightly with vegetable oil spray.
Slice bread into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Place bread tightly together in one layer in pan.
Beat egg substitutes lightly.
Add milk, 1/4 cup sugar or substitute and vanilla and mix together.
Pour half of liquid over bread.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Cut into rings.
Place apple rings on top of bread to cover.
Pour remaining egg mixture over apples.
Mix remaining 1/2 cup of sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Cool for 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Serve with reduced calorie syrup.
Yields 12 servings.

title: southwestern black bean dip
directions: Mix beans, salsa and cheese together.
Top with sour cream. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown onions, bacon and garlic together. Add other ingredients and simmer 10 minutes. Pour into a bean pot or casserole dish. Add beans (do not drain beans). Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, sour cream, soups and noodles together.
Put in a big casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix first ingredients
together by hand.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Mix oleo or butter, softened cream
cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer.
Add
walnuts
and
stir
by
hand.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Combine soup, cream cheese and gelatin in a saucepan and heat until smooth.
Fold in shrimp, onion, celery and mayonnaise.
Put in a greased mold and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with Townhouse crackers or carrot and celery sticks.

title: herbed simmered beef stew
directions: Season beef with pepper and coat with flour. Heat oil in saucepan. Add beef and cook until browned, stirring often. Add mushrooms, garlic, herbs and bay leaf and cook until mushrooms are tender and liquid evaporates. Add broth. Heat to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes. Add carrots and potatoes. Heat to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat 30 minutes or until done. Remove bay leaf.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Cut hot baked potatoes in half.
Scoop out insides.
Reserve shells.
In large bowl (with electric mixer), beat potatoes and butter until creamy.
Gradually beat in milk, stir in onion, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into reserved shells.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Arrange in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through and cheese melts.
Sprinkle with paprika to serve.
To pile potatoes high in the shells, bake a fifth or sixth potato, add the potato to those to be mashed. Discard shells of fifth and/or sixth potato.
Butter and milk may need adjusted to compensate for additional potatoes.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine sugar and seasonings.
