Add vinegar and egg; beat well. Add 1 teaspoon salad oil at a time until 1/4 cup has been added. Add remaining oil in gradually increasing amounts, beating well after each addition.

title: super hot rolls
directions: Cool scalded milk.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine at low speed the sugar, shortening, salt, milk and yeast mixture. Add beaten eggs and about 1 cup flour.
Increase speed to medium and beat 2 minutes.
Stir in the rest of the flour by hand.
The dough will be soft.
Put dough on a floured board; knead slightly. Put in a greased bowl; let rise for 3 hours.

title: fresh orange cake
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well. Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix thoroughly.
Add juice and rind.
Makes 2 large layers.
Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until done.

title: fried rice with vegetables
directions: In a wok, heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium-high heat until hot.
Add egg and cook, stirring, until firm, about 2 minutes. Remove to a plate.
Cut into small pieces.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Combine zucchini, eggs, cheese, oats, crumbs, steak sauce, mustard, onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape like meat patties and brown on both sides in hot butter.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: glazed apple cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let cool and frost.

title: mystery pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend well.
Pour into greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Top with whipped topping. This freezes well.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef in pan.
Drain well.
Add taco mix according to directions.
Put onion, lettuce, chips and beef in large bowl and toss.
When ready to serve, add dressing and toss.
Serve immediately.

title: baked turkey hind quarters and vegetables
directions: Remove and discard skin from turkey.
Arrange turkey in a shallow, 3-quart casserole.
In a small bowl, combine broth, pepper, paprika, salt and cornstarch.
Set aside.

title: june's alabama biscuits
directions: Mix buttermilk and yeast.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil to buttermilk mixture.
Add wet to dry ingredients mix; turn on floured surface and knead a few times.
Roll to about 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut with small round cutter.
Grease pan with oil. Turn biscuit in oil when placing in pan.
Let rise in slightly warm oven.
Preheat on warm for 5 minutes and turn off.
Bake at 425° in preheated oven about 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon-sugar bagel
directions: Cut bagel in half.
Top with cream cheese.
In microwave, heat on High for 10 to 15 seconds, until cream cheese is spreadable. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Then you have a quick and delicious breakfast.

title: riviera special
directions: Melt
butter,
stir
in flour.	Add milk and cook until thickened.	Add
seasonings, tuna, pimento and onion; heat for 5 minutes.
Cut
top	section off each roll, remove center of bread, leaving
bread shell.
Fill with cream tuna.
Top each roll with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk and yeast.
Store in refrigerator until needed.
Pinch off what you need.
Bake at 400° until light brown.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Prepare pastry for single crust pie, except roll out into a 13 x 8 1/2-inch rectangle.
Cut slits in pastry.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, allspice and salt.
(For a very juicy pie, use 1/4 cup all-purpose flour.)
Add sugar mixture to apples; toss to coat fruit.
Turn into a 12 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish; flute to the sides but not over the edge.
Brush with milk; sprinkle with sugar.
Cover edge of pie with foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Remove foil; bake for 20 to 25 minutes more.
Serve warm in dishes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: relish
directions: Put vinegar, celery seed, sugar, cooking oil, water, salt and pepper in pan.
Cook until dissolved.
Let cool.
Pour over vegetables.
Store in refrigerator in glass jar.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: italian-style minestrone
directions: Saute onion, celery and garlic in oil in a large kettle or Dutch oven until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring slowly to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bring water, onions and butter to a boil. Add broccoli and simmer until thawed. Remove from head; add rice and let stand 5 minutes. Add cheese and soup; stir well. Put in a greased baking dish. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°. Put onion rings on top the last 15 minutes.

title: kitchen sink cookies
directions: Stir together all dry ingredients.
Beat the eggs in a small bowl.
Measure the oil, honey and molasses in the same measuring cup.
Beat all the liquid ingredients thoroughly.
Pour the liquid into the dry ingredients and combine.
If mixture seems too dry, add some milk or water until the dough is of a drop cookie consistency.
Drop onto an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Saute onions in butter; add cream cheese and milk.
Stir over low heat until cream cheese is melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Serve hot with chips or crackers.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and put in buttered casserole dish. Top with cracker crumbs; drizzle margarine over crumbs.
Sprinkle poppy seed on top to taste.

title: shrimply divine dip
directions: Add sour cream to cream cheese gradually, blending thoroughly. Add other ingredients and blend well.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Makes 1 2/3 cups dip.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add egg and mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, chopped apples and nuts.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: lazy wife's cobbler
directions: A rich bar cookie with a sweet pastry crust and a tart lemon custard filling.
They are best the day they are made.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix vinegar and beet juice.
Cook all ingredients until thickened.
Add 1 can diced or small beets and 2 tablespoons melted oleo.

title: out of this world pie
directions: Combine in a pan the pie filling, sugar, pineapple and juice and cornstarch.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Stir well.
When cooled, add nuts and bananas.
Pour into 2 baked pie crusts.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: taco and fritos casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper.
Add to drained meat and add tomatoes and taco mix.
Put Fritos in bottom of 9 x 12 pan.	Spread meat mixture on this and top with cheese and lots more Fritos.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° (glass 325°).
Family recipe serves 4 to 5.

title: waldorf salad(serves 8)
directions: Whisk together mayonnaise, sugar and lemon juice.
Combine apples and pear (stored in fruit fresh or lemon juice and then drained.
Add apples, pear, celery, raisins and walnuts.
Chill.

title: best bread sticks
directions: Soften yeast and honey in warm water in large bowl.
Add malted milk powder and salt.
Add flour gradually.
Divide dough into 12 pieces and roll on floured surface to make sticks about 10 to 12-inches long.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Brush with egg; sprinkle with desired toppings.
Allow to rise, 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until browned. Brush with melted butter or olive oil immediately after baking to keep bread sticks soft.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar 4 times.
Beat egg whites, salt, cream of tartar and flavorings until soft peaks form.
Add rest of sugar in 4 additions, beating each time until blended.
Sift in flour mixture in 4 additions, folding in with a large spoon each time. Turn bowl often.
Pour batter into ungreased pan and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Invert on bottle to cool.

title: cranberry slush
directions: Dissolve Jell-O into 1 cup boiling water. Add remaining ingredients and stir well. Freeze.

title: carrot raisin muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl stir together both flours, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and ginger.
Make a well in the center, set aside.
In a small bowl stir together eggs, undrained pineapple, carrot, raisins, corn syrup and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir only until moistened.
Spray 12-cup muffin pan with nonstick spray coating.
Divide batter evenly among 12 cups. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes.

title: shelly's green chili cheese grits
directions: Slowly stir grits into the boiling water.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes. Pour the cooked grits into a large mixing bowl and add eggs, butter, cheese and chilies.
Mix well, then transfer to a flat baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: hot n' cheesy clam salad rolls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and spread the mixture on rolls.
Wrap in aluminum foil and bake for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: sour cream corn pudding
directions: Mix well.
Pour into 2 quart
casserole
dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (325° for a glass
dish), uncovered.
Yields 2 quart casserole dish.

title: cheese spread
directions: Blend together cream cheese and butter; add Worcestershire sauce, horseradish and sherry.
Add small amount of Wispread cheese.
Beat all in mixer until well blended.
Refrigerate overnight before serving with crackers.

title: bobandy pie
directions: Mix the two sugars, then blend in the next 4 ingredients.
In a separate bowl, whip eggs, milk and vanilla together.
Add to the dry mix.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
It will look puffy like a souffle when done.
It will fall as it cools.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, milk and cocoa in a saucepan and boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and 1 teaspoon of vanilla flavoring, stirring until peanut butter melts. Stir in oatmeal and drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper. Let cool.

title: bean soup
directions: Rinse and soak beans overnight in 4 to 6 cups water, changing water once or twice. In a large pot or Dutch oven, place ham bone, sausage, onion, celery and 3 or 4 cups water. Simmer for a couple of hours. Remove from stove. Refrigerate overnight. Next day, return soup to stove after removing most of fat which rises to top. Heat on medium-low and remove ham bone, leaving as much ham in the pot as desired. Add tomatoes, carrots, additional water if needed and potatoes. Increase heat to medium and cook for 1 hour. Drain and rinse beans and add to soup, simmering for 2 hours. Season with black pepper or a dash of hot sauce, if desired. Preparation time: 30 minutes. Cooking time: 4 to 5 hours.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender; blend until smooth. Pour into an unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: chocolate frosting or fudge sauce
directions: Melt shortening in saucepan and add cocoa to dissolve.
Add rest of ingredients; stirring constantly, bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute and 15 seconds.

title: helen jones' mama's baked beans
directions: Fry bacon in large, heavy pot until crispy; set aside.
Saute onions and pepper in bacon fat until soft.
Add ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and dry mustard.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; add beans.
Simmer until desired thickness.

title: torte
directions: Combine water, butter, salt and flour in a microwavable bowl and cook for about 1 minute or until the ingredients form a smooth ball when stirred. Let stand for 3 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat until smooth. Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at
400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until puffed and golden brown. Cool completely on a wire rack.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, pudding mix and milk until smooth. Put cooled puff on a serving platter and spread pudding mixture over the top.
Refrigerate for 20 minutes or until set. Spread with Cool Whip. Refrigerate until set. Drizzle with chocolate syrup just before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: peppermint delight
directions: Place crushed vanilla wafers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: sour cream chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Place butter and 1 cup of sugar in a food processor. Process until smooth. Beat in eggs until light and fluffy. Add next four ingredients and mix until smooth. Fold in chips. Pour half of batter into a 10 inch spring form pam. Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle half on batter. Gently pour rest of batter and sprinkle with remaining sugar and cinnamon. Bake for 35 minutes. Allow to cool in pan.

title: dester neal's chess pie
directions: Melt margarine; set aside.
Add brown sugar, then eggs, milk, flour and white sugar; beat real good.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix everything and pour in pie shell.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes; check often.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla together. Add remaining ingredients.
Roll in ball.
Chill.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 13 minutes.

title: peach crisp
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, and cinnamon.
Cut the butter into the mixture until it becomes crumbly.
Put peaches into a shallow baking dish and sprinkle mixture over them.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: old fashioned tea cakes ii
directions: *If no buttermilk, you can curdle a cup of milk with a tablespoon of vinegar.

title: turkey meatballs
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except cooking oil. Mix thoroughly.

Shape mixture into 1 to 1 1/2-inch meatballs. Brown meatballs in 2 tablespoons cooking oil, heated on medium. Once browned, add jar of gravy and simmer on low for 1 hour, covered, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice or noodles. Serves 4.

title: too easy fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fruit in 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Cut crusts from bread slices and cut each slice into five fingers. Place bread over the fruit.
In bowl, mix sugar, flour, egg and margarine.
Pour over bread.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg to taste.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: treasure chest bars
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Cream brown sugar, oleo and granulated sugar.
Add 2 eggs (beat one at a time) and vanilla.
Beat creamed mixture until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and the 3/4 cup milk alternating each.
Add chopped nuts, cherries and chocolate chips.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325° in a greased cookie sheet.
Frost when cool.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put in casserole dish and bake until tender the apples, lemon juice, sugar and cinnamon.
Mix flour, brown sugar, margarine and oatmeal.
Mix well and top apples with this crust.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: irish oatmeal bread
directions: In large bowl mix flour, oatmeal, baking powder and salt.
In small bowl combine beaten egg, honey and buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well and bake in an 8-inch cast-iron skillet that you greased with margarine for 45 minutes to 1 hour, depending on your oven, at 350°.
Dust top of bread with flour and make a cross on the top before baking.

title: corn bread dressing for turkey
directions: Mix together; fill turkey cavities and bake as any turkey.

title: low-fat spaghetti
directions: Cook turkey and onion until turkey is brown.
Add sauce and simmer.
Cook noodles and drain.
Combine sauce and noodles. Enjoy!

title: hot rolls
directions: Scald milk; add butter, sugar and salt; let cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add eggs to milk mixture, then to yeast mixture.
Add flour, mixing after each addition.
Cover dough and let rise.
When doubled in bulk, punch down.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter that has been dipped in butter.
Let rise 1 hour and bake at 400 for 10 minutes.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash the okra, trim off their ends.
Pack them tightly and vertically into hot, sterilized half-pint canning jars.
(Pack the okra snugly to prevent them from floating and possibly spoiling the seal.)
Add a pinch of red pepper flakes and a garlic clove to each jar.

title: cheese ball
directions: Shape into a ball.
Roll in pecans and refrigerate.
Soften cheese and add rest of ingredients.
Form 1 large ball or 2 small balls and chill.
Roll in finely chopped pecans in addition to those that go in the cheese ball.
Serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir soup until smooth.
Gradually add milk (not cooked), green beans and onion into soup mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes more or until bubbly.
Sprinkle remaining onion soup over top and bake 5 minutes.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Crust: Crumble Pecan Sandies and combine with butter.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Peel onions and slice into 1/4-inch rings.
Separate rings carefully.
Soak in milk 15 minutes.
Then drain rings.
Mix first 5 ingredients.
Stir and blend thoroughly.
Dip onion rings and fry in deep, hot oil until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: grandmother's caramel cake icing
directions: Using a heavy iron skillet, melt 1 cup sugar in the oven (400° to 450°), stirring occasionally.
While sugar is melting in the oven, put the remaining 3 cups sugar and the milk in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
When the hot syrup has reached boiling, add it slowly to the caramelized sugar.
Add butter and cook until it reaches the soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and beat until creamy and ready to spread on a 3 layer cake.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Grind tomatoes, onions, cabbage and peppers.
Mix with 1 cup salt.
Let stand overnight.
In morning, drain thoroughly.
Chop carrots and cook until nearly tender.
Chop celery fine and add all together and cook 20 more minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini in 1/2-inch pieces, boil until transparent looking around center, drain.
Place zucchini in 8 x 12-inch pan. Spread mushrooms over top.
Cut up Little Smokies.
Brown little tiny pieces and layer over mushrooms.
Pour tomato sauce over that. Slice cheese into 1/2-inch wide strips and divide each kind over top (can be grated cheese).
Heat in oven until hot and cheese melts well (375°), 15 to 20 minutes.

title: snicker bars
directions: Melt 1 cup of milk chocolate chips, 1/4 cup of butterscotch chips and 1/4 cup of peanut butter.
Spread in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding mix and pineapple.
Then add Cool Whip and marshmallows.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except lettuce; chill.
Serve on lettuce.

title: indiana bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate and serve cold.
This is delicious and great for summer cook-outs and picnics.

title: homestead biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mammy's cutout cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and brown sugar.
Cream well.
Beat eggs with water and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with wet ingredients to creamed butter and sugar. Chill at least 1/2 hour before rolling.
Roll on floured board and cut into shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken in mushroom gravy
directions: Place chicken in crock-pot.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix broth with soup and pour over chicken.
Add mushrooms.
Cover and cook on low 7 to 9 hours (or high 3 to 4 hours).

title: tabboula
directions: In a large earthenware casserole with a lid, put the cracked wheat and salt.
Cover the boiling water and put the lid on while you prepare the other ingredients; leave covered for 3/4 of an hour.
Drain off excess water and toss wheat with other well prepared ingredients.
Leave it to marinate for an hour.

title: delicious pork loin
directions: Crisscross 2 strips bacon.
Top with 1 slice of pork tenderloin.
Top with 1 thin slice of onion, 1 slice of green pepper and 1 slice of tomato.
Bring bacon strips up and crossed over top and fasten with a toothpick.
Bake on rack in a shallow pan for 2 hours in a 325° oven.

title: braised sirloin tips over rice
directions: Cut up beef and brown in oil.
Dissolve bouillon and add wine, garlic, soy sauce and mushrooms.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour until tender.
Add water chestnuts and pea pods.
Blend cornstarch and water, then stir gradually into mixture of meat.
Continue to cook, stirring constantly until thick.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate coconut bars
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar, butter and press in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix coconut, milk, nuts and spread over crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°, cool.
In small saucepan melt candy bar and peanut butter over low heat, spread over bars. Cool until set.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain off fat; in same skillet add all ingredients.
Mix well; cover.
Let simmer about 15 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Makes 6.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a 350° oven until it doesn't wiggle.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Mix noodles, green onions, cottage cheese and sour cream together.
Mix hamburger, salt, pepper and tomato sauce together. Layer noodle mixture and hamburger in casserole dish.
Top with cheese and bake until hot.

title: praline squares
directions: On a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan, arrange graham crackers one layer deep.
Melt butter; add brown sugar and boil for 2 minutes while stirring constantly.
Stir in nuts.
Pour liquid mixture over graham crackers.
Bake for 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cut into squares while warm.
Cool to room temperature before serving.

title: pace-setting enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic.
Drain.
Add picante sauce, spinach, tomato sauce, tomatoes, bell pepper, lime juice and salt. Simmer uncovered for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: herb-stuffed pork chops
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Combine onion and dressing.
Mix with enough water to moisten.
Fill pockets of chops with mixture and close with toothpicks.
Dredge chops in flour and brown in oil in a frypan.
Place chops in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour soup over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shredded chicken salad
directions: Add first six ingredients together in large bowl. This is the marinade.

Shred chicken breasts and place in marinade. Mix around and let sit for a bit. Shred lettuce. Place marinated chicken on top of lettuce. Garnish with two of your favorite fruits (ideas include grapes, cantaloupe, strawberries, raspberries or mandarin oranges-- I recommend raspberries & mandarin oranges) Great for spring or summer.
Serves 4.

title: dronning maud dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatine in hot water; cool slightly.
Whip sugar and egg yolks until smooth.
Add gelatine and whipped cream.
Layer with shredded or shaved chocolate.

title: buttermilk congealed salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine pineapple, Jell-O and gelatine.
Stir to mix well.
Over medium heat, heat to boiling point to dissolve Jell-O and gelatine.
Pour into large bowl and cool.
Place in refrigerator until mixture is the thickness of mayonnaise.
Add nuts and buttermilk and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and mix well. Refrigerate and cut in squares for serving.
This makes a very large salad, a long casserole will hold it nicely.
Delicious!

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Pour soup into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Stir in 1 soup can of water.
Mix until smooth.
Sprinkle rice over soup.
Rinse chicken pieces and place on top of rice.
Mash package of Lipton soup mix to distribute spices evenly, then open envelope and sprinkle over chicken.
Cover dish with foil.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni.
Melt Velveeta cheese with 1/2 cup of milk. Melt butter.
Beat eggs.
Mix 1/2 cup milk with cream cheese. Combine macaroni, butter, Velveeta cheese, Cheddar cheese, eggs and cream cheese.
Pour last 1 1/2 cups of milk and mix well. Pour in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fork cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll in balls and press down with a fork. May add dates or raisins in any amount.

title: crock-pot roasted beef or venison
directions: Sear roast on all sides in hot skillet.
Place in crock-pot. Pour frozen mixed vegetables over meat.
In a medium mixing bowl, mix together crushed tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and brown sugar.
Stir well and pour over vegetables and meat.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.

title: double cranberry relish mold
directions: Combine raspberry and lemon gelatin with sugar in a large bowl.
Pour boiling cranberry juice over, stirring to dissolve. Stir in cold water, undrained pineapple and lemon juice.
Chill until as thick as unbeaten egg whites.
Put cranberries and orange through food grinder.
Combine with celery and nuts.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Pour into an 8 1/2-cup mold or a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Chill until firm.
Unmold onto serving platter.
Garnish with celery tops and sugared whole cranberries, if you wish.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Put each chicken breast, bone side down, on wax paper.
Pound with mallet to flatten to 1/4-inch thickness.
Put a ham slice and cheese stick on each piece of chicken.
Fold edges over cheese to cover completely.
Roll up tightly and secure with wooden pick or string.
Coat chicken with flour seasoned with salt (and pepper to taste).
Brown in 2 tablespoons of butter in 10-inch skillet. Sprinkle chicken with remaining flour.
Add wine and chicken bouillon cube to skillet.
Heat, stirring, until bouillon is dissolved.
Cover skillet and simmer until chicken is tender (20 minutes).
Remove chicken from skillet; sprinkle with paprika and keep warm.
Add half and half to pan drippings.
Cook, stirring, until sauce thickens.
Blend in peas.
Spoon sauce over chicken. Serve with rice.

title: puppy chow
directions: In a large bowl, put the cereal.
Melt first 3 ingredients, stirring until melted.
Pour over cereal.
Mix well until all is coated. Put in a large paper bag and shake with the powdered sugar.
Can be stored in plastic bags.
Keeps good.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bring oleo, water and cocoa to a boil. Pour into mixing bowl.
Add sugar, flour, baking soda, eggs and sour cream.
Pour into greased sheet pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: carly's biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, sugar and salt; melt butter and mix in until crumbly.
Mix in the milk (pouring into middle of the flour mix).
Drop onto baking sheet by spoonful, about the size of a golfball.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken and yellow rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Break chicken in bite-size pieces and mix with rice.
Top chicken and rice with cooked small green peas for garnish on rice dish.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Add flour mixed with soda, alternately with bananas.
Use tube or large aluminum pan.
It makes a very large cake, it can be divided for smaller cake.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add oil and eggs; mix well.
Add flour, cream of tartar, vanilla, salt and baking soda.
Mix well. Form into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with glass that has been dipped in sugar, if desired.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 13 to 14 dozen.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Bring pepper juice, Sure-Jell, vinegar and hot sauce to a hard boil (boil that can't be stirred down).
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; continue to stir every 5 minutes or so until cool.
Pour into jars.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 4 cups.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Grease bottom of a roaster and sprinkle rice over the bottom. Place chicken on top of the rice and pour onion soup mix over chicken.
Over this, pour cream of celery soup which has been mixed with 2 cans of water.
Put lid on roaster and cook 20 minutes at 400°.
Turn oven down to 300° and cook for 1 hour.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown turkey in a large pan sprayed with Pam.
Add green pepper and onion.
Reduce the heat and cover.
Cook over medium heat until peppers are tender.
Add beans, tomatoes and chili mix. Simmer for 10 minutes and serve.

title: tamale
directions: Put first 8 ingredients on stove and heat; stir often.
Add milk, eggs and corn meal.
If this does not seem thick enough, add a little more meal.
Salt to taste.
Bake an hour at 375°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together with mixer.
Taste great with any type fruit. Makes enough for a large fruit tray.

title: quick and easy cobbler
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Pour fruit into dish.
Mix flour, sugar and butter in bowl until well blended (mixture will resemble corn meal).
Sprinkle on top of fruit evenly and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: three day sauerkraut salad
directions: Day 1:
Combine sugar and vinegar in saucepan, bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Pour into a container and store in refrigerator overnight.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix well and put into freezer; freeze like ice cream.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add molasses and egg. Beat well. Add dry ingredients.
Mix well. Cover and chill.
Form in 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Cook on greased cookie sheets in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: uncle bob's chicken and rice(foil cooking for 1 person)
directions: No matter how you like it, peel skin off thighs.
Now, if you like, throw skins in bottom of pouch.
Next, add rice, water and salt.
Mix up vegetables and toss in (after they are cut up).
Add dash of salt.
Stand thighs on top of everything.
Salt and pepper thighs.
Seal top of foil and place directly on charcoal.
Cook no more than 30 minutes.
Two points of caution:

(1) run sharp knife down each side of thigh bone through meat and (2) when foil pouch looks as if it is going to explode, or break the folds, take a very sharp knife point or toothpick and puncture a small hole in pouch at top.
If hole is too large, leave toothpick in hole. This is the steam pressure escape valve.

title: quick coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to manufacturer's instructions.
Make three layers. Cook sugar, milk and flavoring until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over layer.
Add coconut.
Repeat layers until stacked.

title: wedding icing
directions: Mix with food processor or mixer.
Store in plastic in refrigerator until needed.

title: bread-dough ornaments
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
Add enough water to enable you to roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Once cut, make a hole near the top of the cutout shape with a toothpick.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.
When cooled, paint and thread ribbon or thread through the hole to hang.

title: cajun chicken diane
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with hot water, then cold water.
Mash 4 tablespoons of butter in medium bowl and combine with poultry seasoning and chicken.

title: oat waffles
directions: Blend the oats, water, oil and salt in blender for about 30 seconds.
Add oat bran.
Blend briefly.
Let stand for at least 10 minutes.
May stand overnight.
Blend again briefly just before pouring onto hot waffle iron that was sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Makes 4 large waffles.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk; spoon into pie shell.
Slice bananas over cream cheese mixture.
Add pineapple over bananas and top with whipped topping.
Decorate with cherries and add nuts it desired.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine together first five ingredients. Mix thoroughly. Mix in milk and flour. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Let cool remove from pan.

title: walnut strip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch).
Mix sugar, margarine and egg yolk.
Mix in flour and cinnamon.
Press into pan.
Beat egg white and water until foamy. Brush over dough.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Bake until very light brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Immediately cut into strips about 3 x 1-inch.
Makes 50 cookies.

title: downeast beans
directions: Amounts will vary according to the number you are cooking for.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add pie filling and pineapple.
Refrigerate to congeal.
Combine cream cheese with sour cream until smooth.
Add sugar.
When gelatin is congealed, spread cream cheese mixture on top and sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: puffy oven pancake(more like a popover than a pancake.)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4 inches, in oven:
brush butter over bottom and side of pie plate.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine celery, seasonings, bread cubes and onion.
Mix well.
Stir in eggs.
Layer dressing and chicken in buttered large casserole.
Pour gravy over top.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: busy lady pickles
directions: Fill gallon jar half full with sliced cucumbers. Put cloth with spices in center of jug. Finish filling with cucumbers. Add salt and alum. Fill with vinegar. Put top on jar and let stand 6 weeks. At the end of 6 weeks drain off vinegar and take out spice bag. In large pan stir 8 cups of sugar with cucumber slices until sugar is dissolved and makes syrup. Return cucumbers and syrup to jar, cover and use pickles as needed. Chilling the pickles before you use them will give a crisper texture.

title: cheese cake - crumb crust
directions: Mix ingredients together and reserve 3/4 cup crumb mixture for the top of cheese cake.
Press remaining crumb mixture on bottom and around sides of cheese pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook onion in a skillet until tender. Stir all ingredients together; add salt and pepper, pour in casserole dish. Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt together; cut in shortening.
Mix water, vinegar and egg together.
Add to flour mixture.
Separate into 3 balls and roll out.
Can freeze separate balls or after has been rolled out.
Makes 3 balls.

title: dill dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together; chill.
May be made several days ahead of time.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: apple cobbler cake
directions: Sprinkle 1/4 cup dry cake mix over apples and toss until coated.
Spoon into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Add remainder of cake mix, sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Drizzle melted margarine or butter over mixture.
Mix until it forms large crumbs.
Sprinkle over partially cooked apples.
Bake uncovered 20 minutes until top is puffed and golden.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: butter pecan ice cream pie
directions: Blend milk and ice cream in a bowl.
Add pie filling mix. Beat slowly at low speed until blended, about 1 minute.
Pour immediately into pie crust. Chill until set, about 3 hours. Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on pizza pan like pizza dough.
Bake at 350° until golden brown; let cool.
Mix dry dressing mix and sour cream together.
Spread on cooled crescent rolls.
Add chopped and sliced vegetables on top of sour cream mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese and serve.
(You can substitute or leave out vegetables of you choice.)

title: angel cookies
directions: In medium size saucepan, combine butter, sugar and dates. Boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add nuts, cereal and vanilla; mix well.
Form 3 or 4 at a time into 1/2 to 3/4-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Continue until all of mixture is gone.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add the creamed mixture along with the mashed bananas and vanilla.
Stir in nuts. You may add a little water if dough seems too stiff.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix together cake mix, salt, soda and oil.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove from oven and cool.
Prepare pumpkin as instructed on pumpkin can for pie. Pour over crust and bake 30 minutes at 350°; cool completely. Spread Cool Whip on top of pumpkin mixture.
Spread chopped nuts on top of Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.
Real good.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Fry beef; drain grease.
Put in bottom of casserole dish. Drain green beans; put on top of beef.
Spread soup over top of green beans; cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until Tater Tots are brown.
Put cheese on top and bake another 5 minutes or until melted.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in a buttered 3-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: homemade egg substitute
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Stir with fork or wire whisk until thoroughly combined.
Store in refrigerator up to 1 week.
Or freeze in 1 egg portions.
In recipes, use 1/4 cup egg substitute for each whole egg required. Makes 1 cup.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter over low heat in cake pan 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Mix in brown sugar; drain pineapple and add to sugar mixture.
Prepare cake mix.
Pour over pineapple mixture. Bake 35 to 45 minutes.
Place serving plate on top.
Let cool a few minutes before turning over.
Serve warm or cool, plain or with whipped cream.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with fish, oysters, shrimp, etc.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Separate eggs, placing whites in bowl and yolks in a large bowl.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Arrange slices in a single layer so that they fit tightly into a shallow baking dish.
Beat all remaining ingredients together and pour the mixture over the bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, grill slices on each side and serve with butter and maple syrup.
Serves 4.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in milk until smooth. Beat in the food coloring. Coarsely crush 16 cookies; stir into the cream cheese mixture. Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into the crust. Cover and freeze overnight. Remove from the freezer 15 minutes before serving. Garnish with remaining cookies. Yield: 8 servings.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix oil, eggs, sugar and buttermilk together.
Add spices. Add flour and apples.
Mix well; fold in nuts.
Use two loaf pans sprayed with Pam or greased.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rich alfredo
directions: In a nonstick skillet, saute mushrooms in butter.
Stir in basil and garlic.
Cook on low heat until mushrooms are soft. Stir in sour cream and 1/2 of the grated cheese.
Stir until blended smoothly.

title: souperburger
directions: In
skillet,
brown
beef
and cook onion in shortening until tender;
stir to separate meat.
Pour off fat.
Add soup and seasonings.
Cook 5 minutes;
stir now and then.
Serve on buns. Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: coach taylor's mexican chili
directions: Combine beef, ground pepper, onion and garlic in a Dutch oven; cook over medium heat until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain drippings.
Add kidney beans and remaining ingredients; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
If desired, serve with shredded Cheddar cheese and corn chips.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Trim chops; heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Place chops in pan and brown on each side.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients to pan.
Stir; cover pan tightly and let braise and simmer until chops are tender, approximately 45 minutes.
Baste essence in pan over chops occasionally as they cook.
Skim off fat and serve sauce over chops.
Good with rice and dried noodles.

title: cherry cola mold
directions: Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Dissolve Jell-Os in boiling water.
Stir into cheese mixture, blending well.
Drain cherries and pineapple, measuring 1 1/2 cups syrup. Then add syrup and cola to gelatin.
Chill until very thick.
Fold in cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart mold. Chill until firm.
Unmold.
Makes about 6 1/2 cups or 12 servings.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: In a large frying pan, brown the ground beef and onion.
Add soup, water and rice; mix well.
Add seasoning.
In a 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole, place 3/4 of the shredded cabbage.
Add beef, rice and soup mixture.
Cover with remaining cabbage.
Bake, covered, at 375° for an hour.
Serves 4.
(This dish freezes well.)

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix first four ingredients and mold into buttered dish.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over top.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and margarine.
Beat until smooth. Add egg yolks, beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour in greased sheet pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: charleston squash casserole
directions: Cut and cook squash in small amount of water until tender; mash well.
Add salt, pepper, butter, bouillon cube and grated onion.
Fold in well beaten egg.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole which has been greased.
Sprinkle a topping of crumbs, cheese and paprika over casserole.
Bake in an oven preheated to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tony's taco dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese into a glass 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Spread can of chili on top of cream cheese layer.
Top chili layer with grated cheese.
Microwave for 1 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbling on top.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix the dry ingredients in a bowl and cut in butter.
Mix milk with batter and stir into dry ingredients.
Knead on a board for about 30 seconds.
Roll dough to 1/2 inch thick; cut into circles with glass or biscuit cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Allow to rise 30 minutes.
Brush with melted butter or milk and bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mini barbecue riblets
directions: Mix all ingredients except riblets.
Put riblets into shallow container and cover with marinade.

Cover and chill overnight. Preheat oven to 375°; put riblets and marinade into a roasting pan and bake for approximately 1 hour, until riblets are tender and marinade has reduced to a dark, sticky glaze.

title: rice casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Stir after 30 minutes.

title: tortilla-black bean casserole
directions: In a large skillet, combine first 6 ingredients; tomatoes undrained.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Stir in beans.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, spread 1/3 of bean mixture over bottom.
Top with 1/2 tortillas, overlapping as necessary and 1/2 cheese.
Add another 1/3 of bean mixture, then remaining tortillas and bean mixture.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Top with choice of optional ingredients.

title: crock-pot barbecue ribs
directions: Salt and pepper ribs and broil to brown and remove excess fat. Put sliced onion in crock-pot.
Place ribs on onion and pour barbecue sauce over them.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours or on high 4 to 5 hours.
Serve with corn on cob and tossed salad.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Wash and stem the berries.
Measure 1 cup sugar to 1 cup of berries; let set overnight.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash peppers.
Slice tops off; clean out.
Mix all ingredients together; fill peppers.
Cook at 10 pounds pressure in pressure pot for 15 minutes; reduce pressure every 5 minutes.
(Cook 20 to 25 minutes for more peppers.)

title: blueberry salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello.
Add enough cold water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup.
Add other ingredients; let stand until real firm.

title: krusciki
directions: Cream eggs and oleo.
Add sugar, salt and sour cream.
Add flour with baking powder.
Mix.
Add vanilla and knead a little. Dough will be a little sticky.
Roll out and cut.
Fry in deep fat (Crisco).

title: vegetable and black-eyed pea soup
directions: In 5-quart pan, add oil to heat.
Add ham, carrots, celery and onion.
Stir frequently until veggies are tender, about 10 minutes.
Add zucchini and cook 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir in peas, tomatoes, chicken broth, pepper and 3 cups of water. Cook over high heat to boiling.
Simmer about 10 to 15 minutes. Low cholesterol and low-fat!

title: parker house rolls
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 1/4 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Add 1/2 cup butter or margarine.
With mixer at low speed, gradually pour 2 cups hot tap water (120° to 130°) into dry ingredients.
Add eggs, increase speed to medium, beat 2 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Beat in 3/4 cup flour or enough to make a thick batter; continue beating 2 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl.
With spoon, stir in enough additional flour (about 2 1/2 cups) to make a soft dough.

title: sarah's pear-pecan salad
directions: Drain juice from pears, reserving 1 cup.
Boil 1 cup of juice and add lemon Jell-O.
Chill until partially set.
Place pears and cream
cheese
in
blender
and
cream
to a creamy consistency. Stir in Jell-O mixture and add nuts.
Whip cream and pour in mold. Whipping cream can be omitted.

title: butch's taffy
directions: Put sugar, water, syrup and vinegar in pan and stir constantly until comes to a boil.
Then add cream of tartar.
Cook until it forms a hard ball in cold water - a brittle test.
Add butter and pinch of baking soda and flavoring just before taffy is done.

title: polish cajun cabbage rolls
directions: Bring to a boil 2 quarts salted water. Remove core from head of cabbage.
Place cabbage in boiling water. Remove each leaf as it wilts and place on towel to dry and cool.
Wash rice in cold water and stir into 2 quarts of boiling salted water. Boil 10 minutes and strain.
Run cold water through rice in strainer. Saute onion and celery in butter until transparent.
Do not let it turn yellow. Add meat, egg, rice and seasonings and mix well. Place mixture on cabbage leaf.

Bring ends together, roll and fasten with toothpick and set aside until all mixture is used up. Chop up the remainder of cabbage and place on the bottom of a greased baking dish. Rinse can of sauerkraut in cold water. Squeeze out excess water and layer over chopped cabbage.
Lay prepared cabbage rolls on top.
Mix the ketchup in 1 cup water and pour over the rolls.
Sprinkle with caraway seed and place in preheated oven at 300° for 1 hour with cover.
Baste from time to time.
Add water, if needed.
Uncover and bake another hour. Serving the next day is even more delicious.

title: peanut butter-chocolate bars
directions: Melt peanut butter and 1/2 cup of the margarine together on stove top or in microwave.
Stir in vanilla and graham cracker crumbs.
Add powdered sugar (sift if lumpy).
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Press into greased pan (10 x 15-inch or 9 x 13-inch).
Chill until firm.
Melt chocolate and 1/4 cup of margarine; stir them together.
Spread over peanut butter base. Let stand until chocolate sets up (chill if necessary, but it's easier to cut at room temperature).
Cut into squares; store in airtight container.
(In warm weather, refrigerate if necessary.)

title: new englander's special
directions: With
electric
mixer or rotary beater, gradually blend soup, chili sauce and onion into cream cheese.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or chips.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: twenty-four hour fruit salad
directions: Work cream cheese and mayonnaise into a paste; add unwhipped cream.
Fold in apples, pineapple and marshmallows.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: In a small saucepan, melt shortening and add sugar.
Cool. Place in a mixing bowl.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to batter (batter will be stiff).
Turn into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal, sugar, oil and egg.
Stir well.
Add coconut, raisins, salt and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes in 325° oven.

title: alicia's bacon-tater bits
directions: Cut bacon in half; wrap around Tater Tots and secure with a toothpick.
Bake according to directions on Tater Tots until bacon is crisp.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all fruit in large bowl; sprinkle dry pudding mix over all.
Pour pineapple juice on top and mix well.
It's great!

title: date and nut cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt; mix with dates and nuts. Beat egg yolks and sugar.
Add vanilla and brandy.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and bake in two loaf pans which are greased and lined with brown or waxed paper.
Grease and flour paper.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 2 hours.
It is best to put a pan of water in the oven.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat eggs and flavorings, add to mixture.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Spread half of mixture into greased pan.
Pour in pie filling, then remaining batter. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and pumpkin until smooth.
Add raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Sift together the dry ingredients. Mix well and drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Brush canned milk on top of cookies before baking.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 10 minutes. (If a large spoon is used for dropping cookies, it may take 15 to 20 minutes.)

title: pigs in blankets
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Gently smooth dough into a ball on floured cloth-covered surface.
Knead 5 times.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: *Use packaged thin sliced meat.
Cut each slice in half; fold over onto bread.
Use one to two packages per loaf.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Saute in large skillet the oil, onion and green pepper.
Add cabbage and cook, covered, for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until done.

title: yellow angel food
directions: Beat eggs yolks and slowly add boiling water.
Beat until eggs stand in peaks.
Fold in sugar, sifted 4 times.
Add flour, sifted 4 times, then salt and lemon juice or extract.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375° in angel food cake pan.

title: red, white and blue dessert
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and extracts until fluffy.
Fold in the whipped cream.
Place a third of the mixture in a 4-quart bowl.
Reserve 20 strawberry halves and 1/2 cup blueberries for garnish.

title: four minute brownie pie
directions: Put eggs, sugar, margarine, flour, cocoa, vanilla and salt in a bowl.

Beat for 4 minutes. Stir in nuts and pour into a greased 8-inch pie pan. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until done. Pie will settle like a meringue when cooled. Cut into wedges. Top with ice cream or whatever you wish.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a large bowl. Work in shortening with pastry blender. Stir in milk.
Add raisins and seeds.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface.
Knead for 20 minutes.
Place dough in greased 9-inch round pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and eggs together until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°. Turn oven off and leave cake in for 1 hour.
Remove cake from oven and let stand for 1 hour at room temperature, then refrigerate. Serve cold.

title: ain't your mamas banana pudding
directions: Mix cool whip and cream cheese together. Mix pudding mix as directed. Then mix pudding with cool whip and cream cheese mixture. Add can of condensed milk to mixture. Slice bananas up in a bowl then squeeze lemon juice over bananas to keep them from turning black. Place a layer of cookies in a flat dish. Then place bananas. Then put your filling mix on top of the bananas. Then put more cookies on top of filling. Then refrigerate.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Trim off large leaves of broccoli.
Peel tough stalks and wash thoroughly and drain.
Cut the flowerets and stems in bite-size pieces.
Place in large bowl.
Add bacon, green onions, raisins and water chestnuts.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Add dressing to broccoli mixture and toss gently.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Heat oven to 325° and place mixture in a Bundt cake pan, pressing evenly.
Bake, covered with foil on cookie sheet for 1hour.
Remove foil and continue to bake an additional 30 minutes.
Remove liquid with a basting bulb and invert meat loaf onto a serving platter.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: peach pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and salt.
Add to peaches. Sprinkle on lemon juice.
Toss lightly.
Pour into a pastry-lined 9-inch deep dish pie pan.
Dot with butter.
Adjust top crust, flute edges and cut steam vents.
Wet top crust with water and sprinkle with sugar.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Wash peas in cold water. Boil fatback in a large pot of water on medium heat for about 30 minutes or until water is low and well seasoned with fatback flavor. Add peas, onion and enough water to cover peas. Cook on low to medium heat for about 1 hour. When peas are soft, season with salt and pepper. Remove onion and add rice. Add more water, if necessary, to cook rice (about 5 cups is needed).
Cook for another 30 minutes and adjust seasonings. Serves 10.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix dry ingredients except sugar.
Beat egg white until frothy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Continue beating for 3 minutes.
Stir in zucchini; mix lightly.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on rack.
Remove from pan after 10 minutes.
To serve, cut into 18 slices about 1/2-inch thick.
Makes
1 loaf, 110 calories per serving.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add enough turkey broth to make the consistency of cornbread.
Bake about 40 minutes at 375°.

title: whipped jello salad
directions: Jell the jello medium thick and whip with electric blender until light and frothy.
Add the already whipped cream and other ingredients.
Fold gently.
Pile lightly into dessert dish and serve with plain sugar cookie.

title: german style franks and potatoes
directions: In skillet, brown franks and onion in butter until tender. Stir in seasonings; add gravy, vinegar and potatoes.
Heat and stir.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: pizza quiche
directions: Prepare pie crust according to directions using a 9-inch pie or quiche plate.
Heat oven to 400°.

title: cheesy rotini and tuna
directions: Prepare rotini according to instructions and drain.
In medium skillet, melt butter.
Add mixed vegetables and garlic.
Cook until vegetables are tender and garlic is golden.

title: swedish pound cake
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Add flour and baking powder.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Pour in a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Test with a toothpick; very difficult to get done in the center.

title: pecan-chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix sugar, syrup and eggs in bowl.
Add butter, vanilla, chocolate chips and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour in two pie shells.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 12-16 servings.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix well.
For	1 cup, add 1/4 cup mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: farmers casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Partially cook noodles; drain. Mix all ingredients in large casserole. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Everything is to taste.
May add sour cream or mayonnaise to make dip go farther.

title: hot bean soup
directions: Combine sausage and beef in a Dutch oven; cook until browned, stirring to crumble.
Add beans and remaining ingredients.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pineapple cranberry mold
directions: Drain crushed pineapple; reserve juice.
Combine reserved juice with pineapple juice, (1 3/4 cups) in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Break up cranberry sauce and add to gelatin; stir in Port.
Chill mixture until slightly thickened.
Add crushed pineapple and remaining ingredients, except garnish.
Pour intil 2-quart mold.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours or overnight.
Unmold onto serving plate, garnish with sliced pineapple.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Microwave chocolate and margarine in a large bowl on High for 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Stir in sugar.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: the chili pot
directions: Cook beef, onions, red pepper and garlic in 3-quart Dutch oven over medium heat until onions are tender and beef loses pink color.
Add rest of ingredients.
Reduce heat to low and simmer uncovered until flavors are blended.
Serve with toppings.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cucumber chip dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: seven layer squares
directions: Layer in pan in order listed.
Do not stir.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: salmonburgers
directions: Combine salmon and its liquid with remaining ingredients and form into 4 patties.
Pan-fry in small amount of oil until golden brown on both sides.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix warm water, 1 teaspoon sugar and yeast together.
Add remaining ingredients and enough flour to make soft dough (5 to 6 cups).
Let rise and roll out.
Cut rolls and let rise again. Bake on a greased sheet pan.
Leave in a 250° oven for 10 minutes and then raise temperature to 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: post office candy
directions: Put sugar in 2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Add boiling water and white vinegar.
Cook to hard crack stage.
Add pecans; mix and spread on buttered platter.

title: cathe's taco meat
directions: Brown ground beef over medium heat.
Add onions and cook a couple of minutes.
Then add garlic salt, pepper, chives and butter.
Stir, then slowly add Cheddar cheese, stirring as you add it.
Can be used for burritos also.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Crush in blender and put in jar.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to use.
Then mix:

title: simple stroganoff
directions: Parboil potatoes.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain. Combine soups, salt, pepper and water.
In crock-pot, layer potatoes, beef and soup mixture.
Cook on low 2 1/2 hours.
Add milk at end, if desired creamier.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients together on high speed.
Add carrots, pecans, raisins and pineapple.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: pressure cooker stew
directions: Cut chuck roast into 1-inch cubes.
Place flour, salt and pepper in bag with meat and shake until coated.
Add cooking oil to bottom of pressure cooker.
Heat until hot.
Place meat in hot oil and brown, stirring to brown all sides.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain off grease.
Add red pepper and chili powder.
Mix well.
Remove from heat.
In a large bowl, tear lettuce into bite-sized pieces.
Add meat mixture and all other ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in salted water for about 45 minutes.
Debone chicken; save broth.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Set aside 1/3 cup broth.
Cook noodles in remaining broth.
Saute celery and onions in butter until tender.
Mix celery, onions, 1/3 cup broth, pepper, cubed cheese, chicken and noodles.
Spoon into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake for 5 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Shape sausage into 1-inch balls.
Combine onion and water in large kettle; bring to a boil.
Drop in sausage balls.
Cover; reduce heat.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Skim fat from sausage broth; add tomato juice.
Bring to a boil.
Add noodles; cook until noodles are tender.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: hopscotch crunchies
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in a double boiler over hot (not boiling) water along with peanut butter.
Stir to hasten melting. Remove from heat and stir in chow mein noodles and marshmallows. Drop by spoonfuls on a cookie sheet covered with wax paper.
Makes about 30 crunchies.

title: dieter's egg drop soup
directions: Bring chicken broth to a boil.
Add mushrooms and scallion. Beat egg.
Then pour slowly so eggs form shreds.
Add soy sauce to taste.

title: egg noodle broccoli cheese soup
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan.
Add onion and saute over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally until cubes are dissolved.
Add noodles so that broth mixture continues to boil.
Cool, uncovered, for 3 minutes.
Stir.
Add broccoli and garlic powder.
Cook 4 minutes more.
Add milk, cheese and pepper and continue cooking until cheese melts, stirring constantly.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Make 9 x 13-inch cake.
When cool, cut cake in pan into bite size cubes.
Prepare mousse according to package.
Crush candy. To assemble layers, using a deep bowl, start a layer of cake cubes, using 1/2 of the cake.
Spread 1/2 of the mousse over cake. Spread 1 tub Cool Whip over mousse.
Sprinkle 1/2 of candy over Cool Whip.
Repeat process for second layer.
Refrigerate.

title: virginia's onion soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add the onion and saute for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Add the beef broth, salt and pepper to taste and bring to a boil.
Cook 10 minutes.
Put in a casserole (add broken pieces of French or Italian toasted bread if desired).
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and cook for 35 minutes at 400°.
Top with grated Mozzarella cheese in mugs while hot.

title: carol spack's split pea soup
directions: Rinse the dry peas in a bowl, removing any foreign matter. Add the peas to a large, heavy bottomed soup pot.
Add 8 cups spring water.
Bring the water to a boil; immediately turn down the heat and simmer for approximately 30 minutes, or until the peas are very soft.
Add the chopped carrots, coriander, salt and pepper; simmer for 25 minutes.
Chop the onion and garlic very finely.
Saute in olive oil until soft; transfer to soup.
Add final 2 cups of water to soup to thin.
Stir with a wooden spoon; simmer until carrots are soft and flavor is smooth.
Serve hot; garnish with Russian Rye Bread Croutons.

title: virginia's cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling salted water until tender; drain thoroughly.
In a large skillet, saute onion in 5 tablespoons margarine until tender.
Add soup (undiluted) and mix well.
Add cheese; heat and stir until melted.
Remove from heat and stir in cabbage.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour in a 2-quart casserole dish. Brown crumbs in 1 tablespoon margarine.
Put on top of casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cream cheese dough
directions: Place all items in wide topped bowl and using a gripping motion, work with hand until a smooth mass is ready.
Wrap in plastic and chill for 1 hour. Press out into pan of choice and bake at 350°.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook roast until tender and break into small pieces. Saute onion in butter in frying pan. Add broth, tomato sauce, paprika, mustard, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper and simmer until well blended. Add sauce to roast pieces and work in well with spoon. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: pot pie dough
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Beat egg, add it to dry ingredients.
Add enough milk to make a soft dough.
Roll dough paper thin, cut into 2 inch squares.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 350°.
Mix coconut and milk and spread on crust. Bake 15 minutes.
Break chocolate bar into small pieces and place on bars.
Return to oven just to melt chocolate, then spread.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Bring orange juice and juice from peaches to boil and add jello, lemon juice, salt and sugar; cool to room temperature.
Cut up peaches and blend with other fruits.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, Hellmann's mayonnaise and sour cream until smooth and well blended.
Blend into cooled jello and chill about 1 hour.
Stir fruit and nuts into jello mix.
Pour into pans or Pyrex dishes and freeze.
Allow to stand at room temperature about 30 minutes before serving.
Serve on crisp lettuce and garnish with whole strawberries.
Serves 20.

title: cabbage sausage
directions: Brown sausage; remove from skillet.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Fry onion and green pepper in fat until tender. Add cabbage and cook until limp.
Return sausage to skillet and add rice.
Heat, covered, for 10 to 12 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serves 8.

title: brownies
directions: Grease a 9-inch square pan; dust with cocoa.
In a saucepan, melt the margarine.
Add the sugar and cocoa; blend well.
Pour into the prepared pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Partly skin potatoes; run knife or peeler around middle, leaving top and bottom peel intact.
Boil for 20 to 25 minutes. Place potatoes in baking pan.
Put sticks of butter in pan and place in warm oven until melted.
Spoon butter over potatoes, then sprinkle remaining ingredients, turning until well coated.

title: sausage and noodles
directions: Brown sausage meat in skillet; drain off fat.
Stir in soup mix, tomatoes, celery and sugar.
Bring to a boil and stir in noodles.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Stir in peas.
Cover and cook 5 minutes more. Serves 4.

title: fruit balls
directions: Mix well all the ingredients, except the jello.
In pan, empty jello.
Place balls in jello.
Shake and coat well.
Great party goodies.

title: l.s. ayre's luscious lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add butter, lemon rind, lemon juice and egg yolks.
Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick.
Fold in sour cream.
Place in pie shell.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serve with whipped cream and chopped walnuts.

title: chocolate oatmeal bars
directions: Combine flour and cinnamon in small bowl; beat butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in large mixing bowl until creamy.
Beat in egg.
Gradually beat in flour mixture; stir in oats, 3/4 cup morsels and 1/2 cup nuts.
Spread into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 22 to 28 minutes or until center is set.
Immediately sprinkle with remaining morsels; let stand 5 minutes or until morsels are shiny.
Spread morsels; sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: baked salmon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a square pan.
Put thin layer of crackers on bottom.
Drain salmon; remove skin and bone. Alternate layers of crackers and salmon.
Dot with butter, salt and pepper.
Add just enough milk until slightly soggy.
Cook 1 hour until brown on top.

title: chocolate lover's brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together in microwave or over low heat on stove.
Set aside to cool.
Beat the eggs with the sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in chocolate mixture.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Place in bottom of 8 x 8-inch or 13 x 9-inch pan. Place chicken over broccoli.

title: frosting
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Take off stove and add the marshmallows. Stir until the marshmallows melt.
Add the powdered sugar, nuts and vanilla. Frost cake!

title: maple-pecan bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In large bowl, whisk sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg. Scoop out 1/4 cup sugar mixture and reserve for topping. To sugar mixture in bowl, add cream, milk, eggs, syrup and vanilla; whisk thoroughly. Add bread; stir until evenly soaked. Pour bread mixture into 8 or 9-inch cast-iron skillet or 9-inch square baking pan. Sprinkle with reserved sugar mixture, then pecans. Place butter pieces evenly on top. Bake 40 minutes, until golden brown and custard is just set (knife inserted into custard comes out clean). Let cool 15 minutes. Spoon onto dessert plates. Dust with confectioners sugar. Top with scoops of ice cream, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: "just in case" pie
directions: Prepare crust as directed.
Sprinkle gelatin over water in small saucepan; let stand one minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved, about 3 minutes.
Stir in one cup of the heavy cream.
Heat to a boil.
Then pour into a blender.
Add the chips and process until the chips are melted, about one minute. When processing, add another 1/2 cup of cream, eggs and vanilla; process until well blended.
Pour mixture into large bowl, chill for 15 minutes until thick.

title: russian tea
directions: Put the water and tea bags into a pan.
Let water boil. Remove tea bags.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Let mixture come to a boil, then serve.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix beef, onion and tomato sauce; cook 20 minutes.
Cook 1/3 box of noodles until tender. Mix sour cream and cottage cheese together.
Layer noodles on bottom of dish, then meat, sour cream, cottage cheese and cheese. Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: artichoke balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Roll in extra cheese using same kind as in balls.
Heat in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Don't let them get too dry.
Can make ahead and freeze.
Makes 40 to 60 balls.

title: nicole's texas apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar, beaten eggs and rest of ingredients.
Bake in well-greased tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Cool and sprinkle with sifted powdered sugar or top with a glaze.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the
shortening
and sugar. Add eggs and bananas. Stir sifted flour, salt and soda. Add and mix. Stir in chopped nuts. Bake at 325° in glass or 350° in metal for 1 hour.

title: clam or quahaug chowder
directions: Boil about 4 medium size potatoes (cubed) in water until half cooked.
Fry 1 small onion and 3 stalks celery (chopped) in bacon fat until soft.
Add to potatoes, plus 1 can clams and 1 can stewed tomatoes.
Season.
Bring to boil and serve.

title: train wreck
directions: Saute hamburger, onions, peppers and garlic; drain.
Add all other ingredients except macaroni.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour. Add macaroni; cook 15 minutes more.
Serve.

title: caribbian frost bite
directions: Combine milk and pineapple, pina colada mix and ice in blender.
Whir until thick and frothy.
Garnish.
Makes 3 (8-ounce) servings.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl, stirring until items are well mixed.
Pour into a pie shell.
Cook in a preheated oven at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: death by chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla 2 minutes at medium speed. Add in eggs; beat well. In separate bowl, stir flour and cocoa. Add gradually dry mixture to butter mixture, beating until blended. Stir in semi-sweet and white chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 minutes.

title: grandma's pancakes(servings:  6 to 8)
directions: Beat eggs well and add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook on a hot griddle and enjoy.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix baking powder and flour together and set aside.
Mix well beaten eggs with brown sugar, then add dry ingredients including salt.
Last add vanilla.
Bake in a square pan about 9 x 9-inch at 325°.
This pudding will be waxy and will be less than 1-inch thick.
Eat with whipped cream on each square.

title: chewy raisin walnut shortbread bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease an 8-inch square pan. Combine flour and sugar.
Using pastry blender or fork, cut in butter until mixture resembles fine meal.
Press into greased pan. Bake for 20 minutes or just until edges are lightly golden.

title: cinnamon zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and sugar.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to egg mixture; mix well. Stir in nuts, raisins and zucchini.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Can be made into cupcakes (2 dozen).
Can also be put into bread pans or divided and baked into any of these.

title: potato icebox rolls
directions: Bring to a boil first 4 ingredients.
Allow to cool until lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture.
Add 4 cups flour sifted with baking powder and soda.
Mix well and set aside until double in size. Stir dough down.
Add salt and 3 cups flour.
Mix well, dusting board well with flour and lightly knead dough.
Place in well-greased container; put oil on top of dough.
Cover and put in refrigerator.
Make out as needed or they can be made out and frozen after dough is thoroughly chilled.
Will keep in freezer for a few days, but not too long.
Roll out thin, cut dough out and fold over.
Brush melted butter or oil in before folding.

title: triple layer chocolate bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup cocoa, sugar and butter.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In large bowl beat milk, flour, remaining cocoa, egg, vanilla and baking powder.
Stir in nuts.
Spread over crust and top with chocolate chips.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until set.
Cool and cut into bars.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix together.
Spray bundt pan with Pam. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: onion bake potatoes
directions: In plastic bag add all ingredients.
Shake.
Coat potatoes well.
Empty potatoes into baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender or golden brown.
Good with barbecues.

title: salsa
directions: Chop up tomatoes and put with juice into bowl.
Chop onion, garlic and bell peppers; add to tomatoes.
For mild salsa, remove all seeds from chili peppers.
Slice peppers and add.
For hotter salsa, add a few seeds.
Add salt and pepper.
Do not cook.
Place all ingredients in a quart Mason jar.
Refrigerate.
Allow 24 hours for all flavors to blend.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix well.
Great with dip chips or flour tortillas.

title: strawberry smoothee
directions: Blend on high until smooth.

title: basic pizza dough
directions: Mix yeast in water and stir until dissolved.
Add salt, oil and 2 cups flour.
Mix
until
"soupy".
Add
remaining
2 cups flour and mix by hand.
(May
need	to
add more flour if too sticky.) Lightly grease
baking sheets with Crisco.
Rub a little Crisco on hands and pat out dough in pan.
Makes enough dough for 2 pizzas.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt 2 sticks margarine in boiler pan.
Add 1 cup peanut butter, stir together.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 box 10x sugar, 1/3 at a time.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cut.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Place Doritos over chicken.
Mix other ingredients in a bowl, then pour over chicken and Doritos.
Bake at 350° until cheese becomes bubbly.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: In large mixer bowl, mash hot potatoes.
When all lumps are removed, add cream cheese in small pieces and then the butter. Beat well until cheese and butter are both melted and completely mixed.
Mix in the sour cream.
To milk, add the eggs and onion (if desired).
Add to the potato mixture along with the salt and pepper.
Beat well until light and fluffy.
Place in a greased 9-inch round casserole and refrigerate several hours or overnight. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes until lightly browned on top.

title: honolulu's best coconut ice cream
directions: In a saucepan, scald milk.
Add sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until mixture is the thickness of cream.
Cool completely.
Add coconut milk.
Pour into container of ice cream freezer and freeze according to manufacturer's directions.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: May add 1 teaspoon mustard, mushrooms, green pepper or onion.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Serves 6.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and Ritz crackers last.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick and easy dessert
directions: Slice pound cakes in 12 slices and stack in baking dish. Combine all other ingredients.
Pour over cake.
Refrigerate for several hours.
When ready to serve, cover cake with whipped topping.
Top with your favorite fruit or pie filling.
This is also good with bananas (cut-up) and place on cake.

title: cajun hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Drop with a large spoon into hot oil in a deep fat fryer.
Cook until golden brown, turning with a long wooden spoon.
Great with fish or chicken!! Makes 4 servings.

title: cooked apples
directions: Put the ingredients in a saucepan.
Put about 1-inch of water in the pan.
Cook the apples until they are soft, then let them sit for about an hour.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch and peanut butter together.
Stir in noodles and marshmallows.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: hanky pankies
directions: Brown meat well and drain.
Add cheese to hot browned meat. Mix spices well into meat/cheese mixture.
Place rounded teaspoonful of mixture on each slice of bread.
(Do this on cookie sheets.)
Freeze.
Place in plastic freezer bags until ready to use.
When ready to cook, broil carefully 5 to 15 minutes.
(Too long and you have carbon crunchies!)

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute onion, parsley, celery and bacon in margarine.
Add clam broth, then potatoes.
Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add clams.
Cook slightly, then add all but 1 cup half and half to soup.
Add 3 tablespoons flour and 2 tablespoons cornstarch to remaining cup of half and half.
Shake in jar, then add to soup. Simmer to thicken.

title: banana bread
directions: In electric mixer, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and continue beating.
Add bananas, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Mix well.
In separate bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
At low speed, gradually add flour mixture to creamed mixture, alternating with milk.
Stir in chopped nuts. Bake in greased bread tin 60 minutes at 350°.
When cool, wrap in foil.

title: miss annie's pecan pralines
directions: Place sugar in heavy skillet or saucepan over low flame.
Add cream, water and vanilla.
Cook and stir constantly.
Place candy thermometer in pan and continue to cook until bubbly.
Add butter and pecans.
Cook until thermometer reads 250° (hard ball).
