Pour out onto greased waxed paper and let set until cold.
Ready to eat.
May also be dropped by tablespoon onto waxed paper.

title: baked rockfish stuffed with crab meat
directions: Wash rockfish thoroughly.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter or margarine over low heat.
Combine with dry mustard.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Stuff rock with crab mixture and sew or skewer opening closed.
Place on greased aluminum foil in shallow pan; brush with remaining melted butter or margarine.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 60 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with fork.
Garnish with lemon slices dipped in parsley.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Cut wings in 3 pieces, using tips for stock.
Spread wings on cookie sheet and sprinkle with garlic, Accent and salt.
Let stand for 2 hours, but no longer.
Roll in cornstarch.
Dip in 3 beaten eggs.
Fry until golden, then dip in sauce.
Place on flat pan. Pour remaining sauce over wings.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350° or at 325° for 1 hour.

title: tea cakes
directions: Beat Wesson oil, margarine, sugar and eggs together.
Sift the flour, soda, baking powder and cream of tartar together and add to first mixture.
Beat well and add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 325°
oven for 15 to 20 minutes until brown.

title: chicken stuffing balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, blend together egg, butter and water.
Stir in stuffing crumbs, sauce mix packet and cheese until blended.
Press and shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes until brown.
Makes 3 dozen balls.

title: coconut mounds
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill in refrigerator until firm.

title: bob's easy casserole
directions: Crumble ground beef in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chop onion very fine.
Over this, pour the soup (undiluted).
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy chocolate cherry bars
directions: By hand, mix eggs, water, extract and cherries.
Fold carefully into dry cake mix, trying not to smash the cherries, but getting the lumps out of the cake mix.
Spread into a greased and floured jelly roll pan (15 x 10-inch).
It will be very thick. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost with your favorite frosting and cut into bars or squares.
Can frost with Fudge Frosting.

title: spinach salad
directions: Dissolve jello in the water.
Stir in the vinegar and mayonnaise.
Cool until like egg whites.
Beat well and fold in the rest of ingredients.
Chill.

title: favorite fruit salad(low calorie; serves 6)
directions: Drain juice from canned fruit.
Pour gelatin over juice to soften; stir.
Heat until dissolved.
Cool.
Add ginger ale and refrigerate until thickened.
Mix all fruits together and fold into the gelatin mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: coconut pies
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, flour and pudding together.
Add coconut, melted butter and milk.
Mix again.
Stir in flavoring and pour mixture into three 9-inch pie shells.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 3 pies.

title: tea punch
directions: Boil water; add tea bags.
Let cool (very important).
Steep to medium strength.
Add sugar, 7-Up and undiluted lemonade concentrate.
Stir and serve over ice like regular tea.
Garnish with mint leaves.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
The longer it sets, the better it tastes.
Shake well before serving.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes and cut in half.
Using a spoon, scoop out potato into mixing bowl.
Add other ingredients except milk and paprika.
If mixture is too thick, you may thin it with some milk. Make sure your mixture is not too thin.
Mix well.
Put mixture back into potato hulls.
Top with paprika and bake at 350° until bubbling hot.
Very tasty.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart covered saucepan, simmer vegetables in water until tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and heat (do not boil).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: honey mustard marinade
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl until well blended.
Reserve 1/4 cup for basting.
Pour marinade over meat, poultry, hamburger or seafood.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: christmas trees
directions: Melt the butter and the marshmallows and stir.
Remove from the heat and add green food coloring.
Fold in the Cheerios. Butter hands.
Shape 2/3 of mixture into a tree.
Add gumdrop slices and a star on a toothpick.
Serves 6.

title: nutty cereal crunch
directions: In a Dutch oven or large saucepan, melt butter; stir in brown sugar and cinnamon until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat. Combine cornflakes and nuts; add to sugar mixture and stir to coat. Spread onto two greased baking sheets. Cool and break apart.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix sugar, salt and vinegar and spices.
Mix well until clear. Wash and sterilize jars.
Pack cukes and onions into jar.
Pour syrup over.
Screw lids tightly.
Refrigerate at least 5 days before using.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meats, onion and garlic in large skillet.
Stir in salt, pepper, oregano and parsley.
Add tomato sauce, paste, steak sauce and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Mix cottage cheese, egg and milk together.
Alternate layers of noodles (2 layers), cottage cheese mixture, sauce mix and shredded cheese in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil.
Add broccoli and steam 10 minutes over low heat.
Add soup and milk, then add rice and cheese.
Bring to a boil.
Pour in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: tuna casserole(for microwave)
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add rice, onion, and drained tuna. Mix well.
Melt margarine; add to tuna mixture.
Add thyme and bread crumbs.
Mix well.
Spread mixture in glass pie plate which has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Cover with waxed paper. Microwave on High approximately 10 minutes.
Serve in wedges.

title: broccoli rice dish
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Mix everything together in a bowl and put in an ovenproof pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Mix all together and shake well. Pour half of the mixture over the chicken pieces.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, covered with foil.
Uncover and pour the rest of the sauce over.
Bake, uncovered, 1/2 hour more.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a pot.
Bring to a boil and then cool completely.
This makes a syrup.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Pour syrup over top and mix.
Refrigerate; overnight is best.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Lightly grease a 13 x 9 x 2 pan with vegetable oil or cooking spray.

title: sweet potato praline
directions: Mix together potatoes, sugar, eggs, 1/2 stick oleo, vanilla and sweet milk and pour into casserole buttered dish. In separate bowl, mix together brown sugar, flour and nuts. Then pour 1/2 stick melted oleo and mix until you have a crumbly mixture. Spread over potato mixture and bake at 350° until topping is light brown.

title: louise's main-dish pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Omit salt.
Drain. Combine with next 11 ingredients.
Toss well, chill 1 hour.
Spoon into lettuce leaves that line dish.
Arrange tomatoes on top and egg wedges around and garnish with parsley sprigs.

title: triple bean casserole
directions: Cook onion in reserved bacon drippings until tender.
Combine all ingredients in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 40 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes more until desired consistency.
Serves 12.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Mix all ingredients together (save 1 cup cheese and 1 cup crackers for topping).
Pour into a casserole dish; top with remaining cheese and crackers.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Boil shrimp in crab boil and let cool.
Mix all other ingredients together; add cut up shrimp.
Chill thoroughly.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Combine zucchini and oil in large bowl.
Add flour, sugar, eggs, salt, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, nuts, allspice and nutmeg.
Mix until just blended.
Turn into 30 well-greased or paper lined muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 30 muffins.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients and roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Serve with bite-size pieces of rye bread.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer over low heat 1 hour.

title: yum yum
directions: Mix and bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan 15 minutes in 350° oven. Cool.

title: grandma's beef with chocolate gravy
directions: Cube meat into bite-sized pieces.
Place in roasting pan and cover completely with undiluted cream of mushroom soup.
Place the uncovered pan in a 325° oven for several hours; meat should be fork-tender when done.
This is an excellent chafing dish recipe. May be served with noodles, mashed potatoes or rice.
Add water only if needed to keep meat moist and covered with the gravy.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg yolks until light; add milk, flour, baking powder, salt and paprika. Stir lightly. Stir in corn and egg whites. Drop by tablespoonful and fry in deep fat (oil) until golden brown on each side. Drain on paper towels. To serve, drizzle with a warm butter and syrup mixture.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix together and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: raspberry chiffon pie
directions: Drain raspberries.

Add water to syrup to make 2/3 cup. Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add lemon juice and raspberry syrup. Chill until partially set. Beat until soft peaks form. Fold in raspberries and whipped cream. Add dash of salt to egg whites. Beat until soft peaks form.
Add sugar gradually. Beat to stiff peaks.
Fold into raspberry mixture.
Pile into cooled pastry shell. Chill.

title: mushroom velvet soup
directions: In a wide frying pan over medium heat, cook mushrooms, onion and parsley in butter until mushrooms are soft and pan juices have evaporated (about 5 minutes).
Stir in flour and cook 1 minute to brown lightly.
Slowly stir in broth; bring to a boil, stirring. In a blender or food processor, puree soup with sour cream, a portion at a time, until smooth.
Reheat, don't boil!

title: french casserole
directions: Saute bacon in a large pan until fat starts to cook out. Remove and drain on paper towels.
Shape ground beef in a large patty.
Brown for 5 minutes on each side in same pan.
Pour off drippings, then break meat into chunks.
Stir beans, carrots and tomatoes into meat.
Add seasonings.
Heat to boiling.
Spoon into a 10-cup baking dish.
Place bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
In oblong baking dish, shape beef mixture into loaf.
Microwave on Medium-high 20 to 24 minutes. Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: tropical salad
directions: Place in top of double boiler the hot water, marshmallows and lemon gelatin; set aside.
Whip the cream; mix into cream cheese. Add pineapple; add to gelatin mixture.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan; let set.
Add the raspberry gelatin to a pint of hot water. Cool and pour over first mixture.
Let set for several hours or until firm.

title: glumkies (cabbage rolls)
directions: Core cabbage; place in boiling hot water until leaves soften and peel off.
Set aside to cool; after all leaves are off.
Mix ground meat, onions, seasonings and rice thoroughly.
Place 2 to 3 tablespoons meat filling in each leaf; roll tightly.
Stack in large pan which has a rack or line bottom of pan with leftover cabbage and core and leaves.
Cut ham hocks into small piece and put all meat and bones in between and around rolls.
Add tomato sauce and enough water to cover rolls.
Cook covered at slow boil for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Test for doneness.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Melt margarine and saute chopped mushroom stems, onions and garlic.
(Saute until onions are transparent.)
Mix together sauteed mixture and remaining ingredients (parsley, salt, bread crumbs and cheese).
Turn mushroom caps bottoms up and fill each. Broil 8 minutes or until caps are tender.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease cast-iron corn stick pans.
Bake at 450° until golden brown, 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 14 corn sticks.

title: tropical carrot cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients, except sugar.
Mix carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and beat in sugar.
Stir in oil, dry ingredients, carrots and pineapple; mix well.
Add nuts and coconut.

title: wild game stew
directions: Cut ducks in small pieces and soak in salt water for 5 hours. (Do not soak chicken if used.)
Put ducks on to boil and at the same time, add vegetables and the pickled pork.
Cook for 1 hour. Add the tomatoes and mushrooms and cook for 30 minutes longer.
Add the spices and bay leaves.
Stir in; mix well.
Peel and cut potatoes in small pieces and add when stew is nearly done.
Add olives, Worcestershire sauce and ketchup.
Lastly, thicken stew with a little flour.
Let stew stand 30 minutes after cooking to give spices a chance to blend.
Serves 12.

title: huckleberry house stuffed mushrooms
directions: Dip mushroom caps into melted butter.
Place on baking sheet. Fill with spinach ball mixture and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° until lightly browned, 15 to 18 minutes.

title: sausage balls(club member: laine shoemake)
directions: Grate cheese. Mix ingredients well. Roll into small balls and bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sausage hash
directions: Saute sausage, onions and green peppers until brown.
Add tomatoes, rice, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Put in large casserole.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pastry crust
directions: Beat 1 egg and mix with 1 tablespoon vinegar and 1/2 cup water.
Add to flour and shortening mixture.
Mix well.
Makes 2 (9-inch) double crusts or 5 (9-inch) single crusts.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Combine first four ingredients and cook until tender.
Stir in potato soup, milk, corn and cauliflower.
Just before serving you may add the cheeses.

title: sugar cookies(i usually double recipe)
directions: Cream margarine and 3/4 cup sugar.
Blend in egg and vanilla. Add flour that has been sifted with cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Chill dough.
Roll out balls, about the size of an English walnut.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten with bottom of large glass that has been buttered on bottom and dipped in granulated sugar.
Bake in 400° oven 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool and store in large covered jar.

title: fresh mushroom and spinach salad
directions: Mix vinegar, salt, pepper and garlic in a large salad bowl. Toss with mushrooms.
Let stand 15 minutes. Toss spinach and oil until leaves glisten. Toss mushroom mixture with spinach.

title: easy quiche
directions: Put all but cheese and bacon in blender.
Pour into a greased quiche pan.
Add cheese and bacon to the top.
Wait 15 minutes and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corn bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add sour cream, oil, and corn; mix well.
Stir in cornmeal just until combined.
Pour into a greased and floured 9-inch round pan.
Bake at 425° for 20-25 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool 10 minutes in a pan before removing to a wire rack.
Yield: 6-8 servings.

title: irene's seven layer salad
directions: Cover bottom of dish with 1/2 head of lettuce.
Make layers of green pepper, celery, onion, peas, mayonnaise and sugar.
Add rest of chopped lettuce.
Sprinkle with bacon bits and croutons, then sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: kathy's cranberry party chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle chicken with garlic salt and pepper to taste.
Arrange chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking pan; set aside.
In a medium bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover with foil; bake for 30 minutes. Remove foil; continue baking 30 minutes longer.
Turn oven off; let chicken sit in oven for 10 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and butter.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well.
Add milk and dry ingredients alternately.
Add vanilla.
Pour in tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Scald milk and add sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 2 cups flour, egg and yeast.
Beat well.
Add more flour to make a soft dough.

title: mother's favorite biscuits
directions: Sift
flour;
add baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening;
add
milk.
Stir until dough follows spoon around bowl.
Work
lightly.
Turn out on floured surface.
Knead 1/2 minute.
Roll
out	3/8-inch thick; cut with cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet; bake 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.	Mix pretzels, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Spread out in 8 x 12-inch glass casserole pan and
bake 10	minutes.
Cool.
Beat
cream
cheese and sugar. Beat
in whipped
topping.
Gently spread over cooled pretzel crust	and chill.
Add boiling water to gelatin.
Chill until it thickens. Stir in defrosted strawberries.
Pour over cheese layer and chill until firm.

title: vegetable-pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Drain.
Combine pasta and remaining ingredients, except lettuce, tossing well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Spoon into a lettuce lined bowl.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Grease potatoes lightly; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove and cut in half long-ways and scoop out inside.
Mash and add salt, butter, sour cream and chives; blend well.
Re-fill potato shells and sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Bake for a few minutes more until lightly brown.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Add strawberries and juice (defrosted), 4 beaten eggs, 1 1/4 c oil. stir until mixed thoroughly. Bake in 2 greased loaf pans, or you may use 3 smaller pans. Bake at 350 for 45-60 minutes, depending on pan size.

title: apple-zinger tea
directions: Pour 1 quart boiling water over tea bags and steep about 10 minutes. Add apple juice. Add extra water to taste. Chill and serve.

title: fiori's fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flour and fruit; mix well. Gradually add flour until batter is very thick.
Dip fruit in batter and fry in hot oil.
It is sometimes hard to get the batter to stick to the fruit, so using 2 spoons helps to keep batter in place until you slip it off with 2nd spoon, into oil.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Scorch brown sugar until quite dark.
Add boiling water; cook until it forms thick syrup; set aside and let cool.
Cream sugar and butter; add egg yolks.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder. Mix sugar mixture with flour mixture.
Add cold water; mix well. Add burnt sugar mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in 2 layers.
Put together with caramel filling.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well.
Melt the cheese and mix all the ingredients together.
This is good served warm on nacho chips or Doritos.

title: rice casserole
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart casserole, combine boiling water, wild rice and bouillon; let stand for 15 minutes.
In large skillet, cook celery, onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Add to rice mixture with seasonings and long grain rice; mix well.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat and onion. Add potatoes, tomatoes, tomato can of water, tomato sauce, small cans of water and salt and pepper to taste. Cook for 15 minutes. Add frozen vegetables. Cook another 20 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Set clams aside.
Combine clam juice, potatoes, onions, margarine and water.
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Simmer until heated.
Stir in clams.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: w. w. pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and regular margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Melt margarine in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Pour 1/2 of batter in pan. Pour 1/2 of sugar/cinnamon mixture on top.
Pour remaining batter on top following with remaining sugar/cinnamon.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind together peppers tomatoes and onions. Boil for 15 minutes and drain through a cloth bag.
Put into another cloth bag cinnamon and cloves, boil in the vinegar for a few minutes, remove spice bag.
Add to the vinegar, the salt, mustard seed, sugar and vegetable mixture, which has been drained.
Bring to a good boil and seal in hot sterilized jars while relish is still hot.
Very good.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake according to the directions on the box.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake according to box.
After baking, while still warm, punch top full of holes (use large fork).
Pour can of pina colada mix over cake.
Cool, then cover top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle coconut on top.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole #1
directions: Combine water chestnuts with chicken.
Make sauce of sour cream, soup and water.
Add to chicken.
Melt margarine and add to stuffing mix.
Place 1/2 of mixture over top.
Sprinkle rest of herb stuffing on top.
Lay piece of foil on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: homestyle potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar, salt, sugar and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; chill.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs and fruit cocktail.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper on pork chops and dredge with flour. Heat shortening in skillet and brown pork chops.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Cover with tomato soup.
Cover and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Delicious served with baked potatoes.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Slice Twinkies longwise and lay filling side up in a 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Cover with pie filling.
Slice bananas over the pie filling.
Cut the pineapple tidbits in pieces.
Pour the juice over the top.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate until cold.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: honey wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water in large mixing bowl. Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in egg and next 5 ingredients.
Add whole wheat flour.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Stir in enough all-purpose flour to make stiff dough.
Turn onto floured board.
Knead 5 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place until doubled.
Punch down.
Divide in half. Shape into 2 loaves.
Place into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: risotto primavera
directions: In a large pan, bring chicken broth to boil over high heat. Add rice, reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
In a large skillet over medium heat melt butter.
Add onion and cook 3 to 4 minutes until tender. Add mushrooms, carrots and zucchini.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Add asparagus and basil.
Place rice in serving bowl.
Stir in cheese, salt, pepper and vegetables.
Very good.

title: stuffed chicken shells
directions: Mix chicken, pepper and stuffing with mayonnaise.
Stuff shells with chicken mixture.
Spray large casserole dish.
Mix 2 cans of soup and 1 can of water; mix until well blended.
Pour 1/2 of soup into dish.
Lay stuffed shells on top of dish.
Pour remaining soup mixture over shells.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: quick and easy fudge
directions: Line an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with foil.
Butter foil.
Combine sugar and milk in a medium-size saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved and mixture comes to boiling.
Boil, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.

title: oatmeal molasses bread(from "the hungry hiker's book of good cooking")
directions: *Available at health food stores.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix and boil 6 minutes
the first 3 ingredients.
Remove from heat.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Stir until foamy.
Pour over 5 to 6 quarts popped corn.
Mix well.
Spread over 2 (12 x 18-inch) jelly roll pans.
Bake for 1 hour in 225°
oven, stirring occasionally.
Remove from oven and cool, stirring a bit at first so it doesn't stick to pan as it cools.
Other large similar pans can be used.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar, milk, 3 tablespoons water and peanut butter.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until a few drops form a small ball dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into buttered pan and cool.

title: fruit jello dessert
directions: *One box each of cherry, raspberry, peach, lemon, mixed fruit and strawberry.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions and bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine undrained pineapple and sugar and heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil about 2 minutes.
When cake is done, remove from the oven and puncture all over with a fork. Pour pineapple over hot cake.
Make pudding according to package directions.
Fold in sour cream and spread over cooled cake.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Store in refrigerator.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Saute the
onion
and
mushrooms in melted butter.
Add the soups, Ro-Tel tomatoes, garlic and chili powder.
Stir and simmer a
couple
of
minutes.
Meanwhile,
place	the torn up tortillas in	the
chicken
broth for 10 minutes to absorb the moisture. Place the
pieces in the bottom of the shallow 13 x 9-inch oblong baking dish.
Fill the casserole with alternate layers of diced chicken, sauce and cheese.	Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or microwave cook at 75% power for about 12 minutes. Serve with	a
green
salad
for a complete meal.

title: oyster pot pie
directions: Grease a glass baking dish with butter or margarine and then line with crackers.
Place onion and oysters in dish.
Season with seafood seasoning, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with more crackers and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until liquid boils, about 10 minutes.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and seasonings.
Add tomato paste and sauce, water.
Bring to a boil, simmer 10 minutes.
This is a thin mixture.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, ladle about 1 1/2 cups sauce across the bottom.
Place a layer of uncooked noodles (fill in empty spaces with noodle pieces).
Ladle sauce and sprinkle with 1/3 of the cheese.
Make 3 layers.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: ben getti
directions: Cook hamburger, sausage and onion.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Drain fat; mix in tomato, mushroom and cheese soup.
Add cooked noodles.
Top with grated cheese and bake until bubbly at 350°.

title: beer battered onion rings
directions: Mix flour and beer; let sit for 3 hours.
Dip onion rings into batter and fry in oil until golden brown.
To keep warm, put in 200° oven on brown bag.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix 6 times and cook in frypan 15 minutes or until black.
Put syrup on them and eat them while hot and drink pop with them.

title: spinach spoon bread
directions: Prepare onions in cream sauce according to package directions. Set aside. Cook spinach according to package directions and drain well.
In a large mixing bowl, mix onions, spinach, eggs, sour cream, butter or margarine and salt. Stir in corn muffin mix. Pour mixture into large greased casserole dish. Bake in a
350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean. Sprinkle Swiss cheese on top of corn bread and bake for 2 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: unleavened bread(for communion)
directions: Mix ingredients into stiff dough.
Let stand or set in refrigerator about 30 minutes.
This makes dough easier to roll. Roll out into thin sheets.
Mark checks in dough after rolled. Cook on cookie sheet at 375° until crisp.

title: different squash casserole
directions: Boil onion and squash in 1/2 cup water until tender.
Season with mayonnaise, salt, pepper and margarine.
Add eggs, cracker crumbs and cheese.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Roll in melted butter and cinnamon-sugar mixture. Layer biscuits into well-greased Bundt or cake pan.
Put any remaining butter and cinnamon mix on top and bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: tagliarini
directions: Saute onion, garlic and green pepper in oleo.
Add meat.
Cook on top of stove in Dutch oven.
Add tomato sauce, water and noodles; cook 10 minutes.
Add sliced cheese, corn and olives. Pour into large buttered dish; sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake, covered with foil, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla and nuts and bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat, add vanilla and pecans.
Mix and pour out onto a buttered cookie sheet until cool.
Separate nuts.

title: aunt pearl's meatballs
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and form into balls (approximately 15).
Place meatballs into a 2-quart saucepan.
Add soup and bring to a boil.
Lower heat, cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: no crust sweet potato pie
directions: Mash potatoes. Add other ingredients. Press firmly in 9 inch pie plate. Bake at 350° until bottom is golden brown. Marshmallows may be placed on top the last 5 minutes of cooking if desired.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers.

title: cookies in a jiffy
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the first 4 ingredients. Stir in the M&M's or chips. Drop by tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Immediately remove to wire racks to cool. Yield: 2 dozen.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Season and dredge with flour.
Brown chicken thoroughly on all sides in heated olive oil. Add onion, pepper, pimento, garlic and tomatoes; season lightly. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add mushrooms and simmer 20 minutes longer.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: kentucky fruit punch
directions: Chill well and serve over choice of sherbet or ice ring.

title: punch
directions: In 6-quart container, mix first seven ingredients.
Loosely cover and freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 4 hours before serving.
Add ginger ale; stir until slushy.
Makes 28 (6 ounce) servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix confectioners sugar and smooth peanut butter until crumbly. Spread 1/2 of crumbly mixture on bottom of pie crust. Pour prepared pudding on top of mixture in the pie crust. Cover pudding with Cool Whip. Sprinkle remaining crumbly sugar/peanut butter over Cool Whip. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: heath bar coffee cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, white sugar, flour and margarine together until crumbly.
Reserve 1/2 cup and set aside.
Add egg, vanilla, 1 cup buttermilk (with 1 teaspoon baking soda mixed with buttermilk) and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant and soak for 30 minutes in salt water. Drain and fry slices in bacon drippings.
Layer eggplant, corn, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Top with cracker crumbs and drizzle melted margarine over the top.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: ethel myer's angel dessert
directions: First take the brown crust off the angel food cake.
Tear the cake into egg size pieces.
Mix the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Whip cream and mix with cheese mix.
Fold into cake pieces and stir until well blended.
Place in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: skillet enchiladas
directions: *If you don't like the Monterey Jack cheese, just use all sharp cheese.

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Layer ingredients in order in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: orange delight cake
directions: Mix orange juice with enough sugar (approximately 4 tablespoons) to make a syrup.
Set aside to dissolve.

title: aurelia's lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly, spooning off excess fat. Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Cook noodles until tender. Drain and rinse with cold water. Combine cottage cheese with next 5 ingredients.
Place half of the noodles in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Spread half the cottage cheese mixture over the noodles.
Add half the Mozzarella cheese and half the meat mixture.
Repeat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: roasted red bell peppers
directions: Place whole peppers on a baking sheet.
Place under broiler, turning the peppers as the sides become charred.
When all the peppers are charred all over, place in a sealed plastic bag and let steam for about 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato crunch casserole
directions: Blend sweet potatoes in a blender until liquid.
Add the sugar, 1/2 cup margarine, evaporated milk and eggs.
Blend all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan or casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until firm.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-qt casserole dish mix soup, milk, soy sauce, pepper, pimento, 2/3 C onion rings and pepper, mixing well. Dot top with couple pats of butter. Bake at 350 for 25 minutes or until hot. Stir. Sprinkle remaining 2/3 C of onion rings over top. Bake 5 minutes longer or until onion rings are golden. Serves 6.

title: curried fruit
directions: Melt butter, brown sugar and curry powder.
Butter pan; add fruit and raisins.
Pour mixture of butter, sugar and curry over the fruit.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: saturday night chicken
directions: Salt chicken with both salt and garlic salt.
Sprinkle paprika on thoroughly.
Spread it out in one layer in a shallow baking pan.
Dilute the soup with the cream and pour it over the chicken. Sprinkle the chopped parsley evenly on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate lover's delight cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix and bake.

title: fricadillis
directions: To the meat add the eggs. Mix well. Take one slice of bread and soak in warm water. Squeeze moisture out of bread and add to the meat. Season with salt and pepper. Add the chopped onion. Mix well and fry to a nice brown. Any kind of meat scraps can be used, but lean, fresh pork is better than boiled meat.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan.
Stir in brown sugar and add the pineapple slices.
Pour prepared yellow cake mix over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool, then flip cake over.

title: sauce for chicken or beef
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add all other ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
Serve over baked chicken or beef.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti to desired doneness and add melted butter. Brown meat, add tomato sauce, salt and pepper. Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onion, and green pepper.
Spread 1/2 of the spaghetti in bottom of casserole dish.
Add 1/2 meat, then cheese mixture, remaining spaghetti and ending with remaining meat.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Beat together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and molasses. Sift together and stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill dough overnight or at least several hours. Roll into balls. Dip in water, then roll in granulated sugar.
Place on cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen cookies.

title: crumb-top coffee cake
directions: Combine margarine, flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
To the remaining mixture, add the combined egg and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm or cooled.

title: lou ann's hush puppies
directions: Mix together as listed and drop by teaspoonfuls in hot oil until brown.

title: "sticks to the ribs" barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour over ribs or chicken.
Place in oven at 350° approximately 1 hour.
This may also be used on the grill.

title: gay's good corn
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients; mix the rest of the ingredients and add to the corn mixture.
Pour in baking dish and bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: rolled chicken breasts
directions: Roll 2 slices dried beef in with chicken breasts.
Wrap with slice of bacon.
Mix soup and sour cream and spread over chicken. Cover and bake at 275° for 3 hours.
Serve with Uncle Ben's long grain wild rice (original recipe).

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Core cabbage.
Cook whole in a pot which will allow you to completely cover cabbage with water.
Cook until tender

title: caramel breakfast ring(microwave oven)
directions: In glass measure, mix brown sugar, butter and water. Microwave (High) 1 minute.
Add nuts and cherries; set aside.
In 1 or 1 1/2-quart round casserole, place small glass in center (open side up).
Spoon half of sauce mixture in bottom of dish. Separate biscuits; arrange in overlapping ring around glass.
Spoon rest of caramel mixture over biscuits.
Microwave (High) 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Remove glass; invert on serving plate.
Serve warm by pulling sections apart.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: party mix
directions: Bake for 2 hours in a 225° oven.
Stir about every 1/2 hour.

title: pineapple cherry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans, together and pour in a long dish.
Refrigerate.
This can be made ahead of time and frozen.

title: texas pound cake
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients. Add the flour and almond paste. Bake in greased pan dusted with bread crumbs or graham cracker crumbs.

title: calico ham 'n cheese bake
directions: Combine Shredded Wheat and butter.
Sprinkle half over bottom of 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Cover with overlapping ham slices, then with half of vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese, then with remaining vegetables.
Beat together remaining ingredients.
Pour over top.
Bake in a preheated moderate oven (350°) for 25 minutes. Sprinkle remaining cereal mixture around edges.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes longer or until done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lomi lomi salmon
directions: Cover salted salmon with water and soak overnight.
Drain and rinse.
In a large bowl, combine salmon, tomatoes, onion, and green onion; mix well.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Mash bananas and add.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Pour batter into two greased bread pans. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate at least 4 hours. Best if used the next day.

title: dinner club enchiladas
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and tomatoes.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning and mix.
Dip tortilla in hot soup mix and fill with meat, cheese and onion.
Roll and put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour remaining soup mixture over enchiladas. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cup of cheese and return to oven.

title: theresa rose's chicken marsala
directions: Wash chicken breasts and pat dry.
Cut into bite-sized pieces. Combine flour, Parmesan, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Toss chicken pieces in flour mixture.
Set aside.

title: miracle pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and whipped margarine with sugar; cream well. Add half of flour, half of milk and blend.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating one minute after each egg.
Add remaining flour and milk; blend well.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour in tube pan that has been greased and floured well.
Bake in cold oven at 325° starting for one hour, then turn oven to 350° and bake 20 minutes longer. Do not open oven until done.

title: chocolate passion
directions: Cut brownies into 1/2-inch cubes.
Layer in 3-quart serving bowl 1/2 the brownies, 1 cup strawberries, 1 sliced banana and 1 tub topping.
Repeat layers.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Recipe can be halved.
Serves 16.

title: miss polly's butterscotch pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thick. Remove from heat; add white sugar, then add butter and pecans. Pour into a baked shell and top with meringue. Brown meringue at 350°.
This recipe came from my husband's Aunt Polly McDougald.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: In
a
medium saucepan, mix all ingredients.
Heat over medium heat for 15 minutes, then add meatballs.
Simmer on low for 2 hours.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake.
Crumble 1/3 of the cake into a punch bowl, 1/3 pudding, 1/3 cherry pie filling and 1/3 Dream Whip.
Repeat steps ending with Dream Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: amaretto pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well.
Stir in egg yolks one at a time.
Add baking soda to flour.
Add flour and sour cream alternately to creamed mixture.
Add Amaretto, stirring well. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into Amaretto mixture.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Let stand 15 minutes before taking out of pan.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring to hard boil; turn fire down and let simmer for 25 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Mix milk and eggs together, one at a time.
Drizzle mixture in cooked rice slow; stir.
Then place back on stove over low heat.
Cook until it starts to thicken, about 2 minutes.
It will coat your metal spoon.
Optional:
1/2 cup raisins and 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: mini dogs
directions: Roll biscuits flat; spread with mustard.
Cut in quarters. Wrap each wiener in quarter of biscuit; hold with toothpick. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: fresh strawberry cheesecake pie
directions: In a small bowl, combine cream cheese and 2 teaspoons sugar. Beat until smooth; spread on bottom of crust.
Puree half of the strawberries.
In a 2-quart saucepan, combine pureed strawberries, remaining sugar and cornstarch.
Cook and stir over medium-low heat until mixture thickens and becomes clear (about 7 to 10 minutes); remove from heat.
Stir in rest of strawberries; let cool 10 minutes and pour into crust.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours; serve with whipped topping.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin-banana nut bread
directions: Combine pumpkin, banana, sugar and oil; mix well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, salt and nuts.
Beat well.
Pour into 2 greased 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake in 450° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes in pans.
Remove and cool completely before slicing.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Fry onion
golden brown in butter.
Add crumbs and fry until mixture is browned.
Use half this mixture in bottom of buttered baking dish.
Add fillets.
Season well with salt and pepper (and a bit of oregano).
Cover with layer of drained tomatoes, then the balance of the crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven until fish is flaky.

title: mary's mushroom soup
directions: Melt butter in large pan. Add onion and garlic, stirring over medium heat until onion is soft (about 3 minutes). Mix in mushrooms and stir about 5 minutes. Add flour and stir for another minute. Pour in milk and beef stock, stirring well until combined and bring to a boil; reduce heat to low. Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes or until mixture has reduced, is thickened and mushrooms are tender. Add parsley. Serve with a dollop of sour cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in greased loaf pan for 60 minutes at 350°.

title: orange julius
directions: Put in blender.
Blend 10 to 12 seconds.

title: sparkling fruit punch
directions: Mix tea, concentrated orange juice and lemonade in punch bowl. Pour ginger ale over ice in punch bowl.
Float oranges and halved strawberries on top.
Decorate ice block with cut fruit if desired.

title: fruit swirl coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease jellyroll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch) or 2 square pans, 9 x 9 x 2.
Blend sugar, butter, shortening, baking powder, vanilla, almond extract and eggs in large mixing bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in flour. Spread 2/3 of batter in pan.
Spread filling over batter.
Swirl rest of batter over top of pie filling.
Bake 45 minutes.
While warm, drizzle with glaze of 1 cup confectioners sugar and 1 to 2 tablespoons milk.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Spread on tortillas. Roll up jelly roll style. Refrigerate. Slice crosswise and serve with salsa.

title: kayleigh t.'s no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cocoa and butter in a medium saucepan. Cook over medium-high heat.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Mix in peanut butter.
Add oats, blend thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool completely.
Store cookies in an airtight container.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: homemade lava
directions: Combine water and baking soda in a glass.
In another glass, combine soap, food coloring and vinegar.
When ready for the eruption, add baking soda solution to the soap/vinegar solution and watch it foam and flow.

title: hot shrimp dip #2
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Simmer until cheese is melted.
Stir often.
Pour into bread which has been hollowed out.
Arrange bread that has been taken out in cubes around loaf.

title: e-z chili cheese burritos
directions: Thaw burritos according to package instructions.
Place in single layer in baking dish.
Cover with chili (for hotter taste, use 1 can of hot chili).
Place in preheated oven at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.
Serve with sour cream and chile peppers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in lightly salted water just until tender, drain.
Combine eggs, milk, soup, mayonnaise and cheese, stir in cooked broccoli.
Pour into a greased 2 quart casserole dish and sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool 15 minutes before serving.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix together the sugar and cinnamon.
Rub Bundt pan with butter or margarine.
Cut each individual biscuit in half.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture and line Bundt pan with sugared biscuits. Melt the stick of butter or margarine.
Add remainder of sugar mixture to the melted butter.
Drizzle over biscuits and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Recipe can be easily halved.

title: bruce's vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, corn, celery, onion and mayonnaise well.
Put in casserole dish.
Melt margarine and mix with crushed crackers. Sprinkle over the casserole.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: microwave divinity fudge
directions: You will need an 8-cup measuring cup as cooking bowl.

title: cranberry mint tea
directions: Combine tea bags and water.
Steep 5 minutes.
Remove and discard tea bags.
Let cool.
Stir in cranberry juice.
Serve over ice.

title: ritz delights
directions: Cook milk and dates while stirring until thick; scorches easily.
Add pecans.
Spread on Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Mix together with mixer.
Pour into graham cracker crumb crust.
Pour cherries on top after mixture has been chilled. Refrigerate.
